{"id": "1673", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1673", "title": "Artemis/Quotes (Hades)", "text": "\"The following are quotes from &lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Hades%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;\"\nFirst Meeting.\n Zagreus: \n\"There's only one heavenly archer I know of. Well, several, really. Anyway! In the name of Hades! Olympus? I accept this message.\" \n Artemis: \n\"I heard about you. Look, I'm not like all the others on Olympus. The power of the hunt helps keep me company, so... maybe it'll help you, too!\" \nKeepsake Dialogue (&lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Arrowhead\"&gt;Adamant Arrowhead&lt;/a&gt;).\nKeepsake Equipped.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, that's my Adamant Arrowhead on you! Normally, it's for killing things, but in your case it makes it even easier for me to hunt you down, even in the dark. Now that I found you... here!\" \nReactions.\nSeeing &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; at Low Health.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, you all right there, Zagreus? Wouldn't do to have you die on me just moments after meeting here like this.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"\"Oh\"! Look at you, you're hurt there pretty bad, but, just stay focused on the hunt, and it'll help to keep the pain at bay.\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"Look, I'm just goddess of the hunt, not medicine, so... I don't know if this is going to help right now, but, here!\" \nDialogue 04.\n Artemis: \n\"Your hunt has evidently not been going very well so far, I see. Though, maybe we can still turn it around.\" \nDialogue 05.\n Artemis: \n\"Well, one good thing about all of the blood you've lost is it was even easier to track you down this time!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; (Rejection).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Why would you side with...?! \"Ugh\", why do I even bother with some lesser god!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"I thought we had an understanding, Zagreus. But, this wouldn't be the first time I was wrong about someone.\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"\"Huh\", so that's your choice! Maybe you're more like my relatives than I'd care to admit.\" \nDialogue 04.\n Artemis: \n\"Good shot, there, Zagreus! I guess you got me. Now why don't you go take a shot at \"this\".\" \nDialogue 05.\n Artemis: \n\"Don't be messing with my feelings, Zagreus. My loyalty's hard-won, and quickly lost.\" \nDialogue 06.\n Artemis: \n\"You really missed an easy shot, here, Zagreus. But I will not. You'll see.\" \nDialogue 07.\n Artemis: \n\"Ah, good! Just when I had almost forgotten what an arrow to the back felt like!\" \nDialogue 08.\n Artemis: \n\"Am I some kind of pushover to you, Zagreus? Is that what you think?\" \nDialogue 09.\n Artemis: \n\"Oh, look, turns out it's time for target practice once again! Start running, Zagreus.\"\nDialogue 10.\n Artemis: \n\"What made you think I'd stand for this, from you?\"\nDialogue 11.\n Artemis: \n\"\"Ah-hah\", I knew you'd pull this old maneuver, Zagreus. And I am ready for you, now.\" \nDialogue 12.\n Artemis: \n\"You're getting quite predictable when you betray me like this, Zagreus! Start running, then.\" \nDialogue 13.\n Artemis: \n\"Oh really, that's the way it's going to be? You Underworld gods are all alike!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; (Making Up).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Fine, I'm not angry anymore, not really anyway, but you just watch yourself with me, you got it?\"\nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"Oh you're still there I see. Well then, all right, let's call it even for the moment and get on with this.\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"All right, all right, I'm going to forgive you now I guess, no need to beg, you just think twice next time OK?\" \nDialogue 04.\n Artemis: \n\"Got to say you handled yourself pretty well back there. I can't stay mad after a show like that.\"\nDialogue 05.\n Artemis: \n\"Good hunting just now, Zagreus. You passed my little test, so now we're good, just like it never happened.\" \nDialogue 06.\n Artemis: \n\"So you survived, so what. Here, why not take a Boon, and then be off?\"\nDialogue 07.\n Artemis: \n\"I will admit mistakes were made back there, so you just don't make them again, next time all right?\" \nDialogue 08.\n Artemis: \n\"You know what, I decided not to kill you, Zagreus. No sport in cornered prey, so here, get on with it.\" \nDialogue 09.\n Artemis: \n\"Good thing you're nowhere near our mountaintop or I'd have shot you for that stunt, myself.\" \nDialogue 10.\n Artemis: \n\"Well, Zagreus, it turns out you need all the help that you can get, so here's a pity Boon for you!\" \nDialogue 11.\n Artemis: \n\"I could keep hunting you until you're dead, but there's too little meat on you to make it worth my while.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; (Killing &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"You may be good at running, Zagreus, but you're bad at hiding.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"You make me mad, I'll hunt you like a stag. You heard of those?\"\nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"Don't anger me next time, won't shoot you dead, is it a deal?\"\nGeneric Greetings.\nLong Lines.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey. You're not alone. You're not alone down there, OK? Here, let me show you.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"The dead must make a rather easy target, wouldn't you say? Let's see what you can do to them, given your choice of these.\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"You busy, Zagreus? Thought maybe I could interest you in some of these old hunting tricks of mine.\" \nDialogue 04.\n Artemis: \n\"How fares the hunt this time around, OK? I bet it could be better, so, \"erm\", here! Maybe this'll help.\" \nDialogue 05.\n Artemis: \n\"Let's take a little hunting expedition, yeah? You'll do most of the work, but hey, I'll be with you in spirit!\" \nDialogue 06.\n Artemis: \n\"Sorry you're still stuck down there. Sometimes I feel stuck myself, but, a good hunt always sets me straight.\" \nDialogue 07.\n Artemis: \n\"When I am on the hunt, my mind is clear, and nothing stands between me and my target. Though, have a blessing just in case you can't relate!\" \nDialogue 08.\n Artemis: \n\"I'd love to know about your life down there. I'll try and help you live through it this time so that way you can tell me?\" \nDialogue 09.\n Artemis: \n\"The wretches whom you face down there have died already, sometimes more than once. Should make for easy targets, right?\" \nDialogue 10.\n Artemis: \n\"I've never come across a target I couldn't take down. I expect the same of you, you hear me? Hopefully you hear me.\" \nDialogue 11.\n Artemis: \n\"Good hunting, Zagreus! The sooner you get out of there the sooner you can save me from my insufferable relatives. Please?\" \nDialogue 12.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, Zagreus, good luck out there, this time. I'd tell you \"'may your aim be true' \"but I can guarantee it, actually.\" \nDialogue 13.\n Artemis: \n\"The hunt requires utter concentration, so, I'll leave you to it, and... just watch your every move in silence over here...\" \nDialogue 14.\n Artemis: \n\"You want to make it out of there, you... don't have to listen to a word I say, to be quite honest, but... my huntress blessings ought to help.\"\nDialogue 15.\n Artemis: \n\"Well, Zagreus, you getting out of there this time, or am I going to have to keep on hunting by myself for the time being? Probably?\" \nDialogue 16.\n Artemis: \n\"Looks to me like you could use a little help, so I'll just have a look in my big bag of blessings here, and, \"oh\"! Here's just the thing.\" \nDialogue 17.\n Artemis: \n\"The hunt comes down to kill-or-be-killed. Except for us immortals, who have to live with our shame, which is worse?\" \nDialogue 18.\n Artemis: \n\"Those wretched things harassing you throughout that Underworld just won't give up, will they? Well, just keep killing them, I guess!\" \nDialogue 19.\n Artemis: \n\"Need a hunting partner, Zagreus? Not that I'm able to join you myself down there, or even hear you respond for that matter, but, anyway, here.\" \nDialogue 20.\n Artemis: \n\"Need a hunting partner, Zagreus? Not that I'm able to join you myself down there, or even hear you respond for that matter, but, anyway, here.\" \nImproved Relationship Lines.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Zagreus, it's me! I'm here to join the hunt with you again. Let's show them what we can do.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"Hello again, you ready for this hunt? Me, I've been looking forward since last time, so, let's get on with it.\" \nAbout Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"Your name, it means great hunter, Zagreus! I guess your mother Nyx must have expected someday that you'd pick up a few pointers from myself!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Megaera\"&gt;Megaera&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"That Fury down in Tartarus has been a real problem, hasn't she. I see the huntress instinct in her. She thinks she knows your weaknesses. Don't let yourself become predictable.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Achilles\"&gt;Achilles&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, I once heard Lord Hades has in his employ the greatest hero of the Trojan War, you happen to know anything about that? I'm kind of a fan. You see Achilles, tell him he's the best for me!\"\nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"So, I have heard that Achilles, himself, taught you how to fight! No wonder you can hold your own down there, that is amazing...! You be sure to honor him from time to time, got it?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Callisto\"&gt;Callisto&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n\"Not everybody on Olympus is a total disappointment, Zagreus. Why, someday maybe you could meet Callisto, she goes hunting with me all the time! Bet you don't see many woodland nymphs down there.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey Zagreus, that Nectar you sent? Callisto and the nymphs and I, we popped it open recently, and it was really good! Had us positively frolicking about. So, thanks!\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"You must have a friend or two, don't you? It's hard being alone all of the time. At least I have Callisto and the other nymphs, and... I have you! A distant friend is still a friend, isn't that right?\" \nDialogue 04.\n\"Hope you don't mind, I told Callisto all about you recently! Don't worry, I was quite discreet about it, the two of us were on the hunt, not like I just shouted out your story from the mountaintops!\" \nDialogue 05.\n Artemis: \n\"Zagreus, if only you could turn yourself into a woodland creature and just fly or burrow out of there! My Callisto, she can turn into a bear, you ever seen those? Monstrous, furry things, quite huggable, if they don't kill you first!\" \nDialogue 06.\n Artemis: \n\"You've never even seen the woods, have you? I hope you do, someday. You could meet Callisto and the others! It's quite beautiful, and green, and calm, it's... anyway.\"\nDialogue 07.\n Artemis: \n\"Don't know what it is about you, Zagreus, but I feel like I can be me with you, you know? Maybe it's that you don't constantly talk over me like everybody else, besides Callisto and the nymphs I guess. Not that I can even hear you, but, you know what I mean, right?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"Ah, good old Father Zeus, he must have blessed you with his lightning bolts, did he? Always looking out for everyone.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"So Aphrodite reached you first, did she? Sounds exactly like something she'd do. She has a knack for trouble. So, let's just stay focused, here!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"You're pretty close with Ares, aren't you? And here they said it couldn't be done. If I were you I'd watch myself with him.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Dionysus\"&gt;Dionysus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"That lush and lecher, Dionysus, counts you as a friend? I'm hoping that there must be some mistake, yeah, Zagreus?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"You seem particularly light on your feet, there, Zagreus. I'd figure Hermes, himself, was speeding you along, except I've not seen him about in... been a while, really.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"Uncle Poseidon blessed you, didn't he. To think that big, fat oaf is your own father's brother. I'm told to be respectful near him, but it's hard.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis: \n\"So even Demeter's become involved in this! Didn't think she would. Though you'll be glad she did! Provided you stay on her warm and fuzzy side, of course. Working on that, myself!\" \nWith Other Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, \"uh\", Zagreus! There's something I've been wondering, and don't take this the wrong way or anything, OK? Oh, no. It's her.\"\n Aphrodite: \n\"Why, Artemis, you're absolutely tongue-tied! Due to our little godling in the Underworld, or a little due to me? \"Hm-hm\", you shall figure it all out I'm sure!\"\nDialogue 02.\n Aphrodite: \n\"Oh dearest! I have brought you keen-eyed Artemis, who, in her focus on the hunt, has not developed social graces suitable enough to come to you herself!\"\n Artemis: \n\"Social graces, she says! Going about like \"that\"! I'm sure you know that I can find you when it's necessary, Zagreus. Though, how to get away from Aphrodite, I have no idea.\"\nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"\"Erm\", Zagreus, despite my hunter's instincts here, it seems I was unable to elude Aphrodite in this particular case, who insisted that we present ourselves to you at the same time, for whatever reason...\"\n Aphrodite: \n\"Oh, come now, Artemis! I'm sure you're very capable of hiding from a common beast, but I can see you plain. Why not be honest with yourself, next time?\"\n&lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Athena: \n\"If you've a moment, Zagreus? One of my relatives has claimed that I usurp your time. So I invited her to contact you.\" \n Artemis: \n\"Um, hello, Zagreus... Athena here is grandstanding or trying to prove a point, or something. I don't know. Anyway, nice talking to you.\" \n Athena: \n\"Well, I suppose that's settled, then. I am afraid such interactions aren't uncommon here amongst my family; but what's a family without flaws?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"You know my father and my uncle, by now, right, Zagreus? I don't know which of them is worse. \"Uh\", I mean... superior! Superior, despite technically spending most of his time in the seas, beneath Olympus, isn't that right, Uncle?\" \n Poseidon: \n\"Oh, Artemis, you needn't boast to little Hades there on my account! Besides! Whether you're in the sea, above it, or beneath, makes little difference to your measure as a god! You two are young as yet! Keep at it, and you'll soon be practically as great as I!\"\nDialogue 02.\n Poseidon: \n\"The thing about me, Nephew, is I get along with everybody, here! A skill apparently that's rather rare! Take my niece Artemis, for instance! Can't ever take a simple jest, at all! You won't easily attract a mate with such a sour look about you, girl!\" \n Artemis: \n\"Oh, and wouldn't that be such a pity, Uncle Poseidon. I wonder what could be the cause of this sour look that I perpetually have up here? Maybe Zagreus knows.\" \n Poseidon: \n\"\"Hahaha\"! See exactly what I mean, Nephew?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Zagreus, I wish we all could hear you so that good Lord Ares here might be persuaded that my powers are entirely for different purposes than his!\" \n Ares: \n\"Perhaps our skillsets once were meant for different purposes, dear Artemis; but who are we to doubt the end result? Observe what shall transpire once we grant our kin our combined might.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"Zagreus, I was just hoping for a little privacy before this hunt, which is consistently my preference here, except, you see, Lord Ares always seems to come sniffing about, first sign of any hunting instruments!\" \n Ares: \n\"Why, my dear Artemis, the hunt is but a prelude to a war, is that not so? For if all mortalkind knew naught of hunting, why, they would not be nearly so adept at killing one another.\" \n Artemis: \n\"Look, Lord Ares, if I lend you better marksmanship ability, you think that you could bother someone else?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Oh, hi there, Zagreus, I was just failing to persuade the Lady Demeter to ease up off the snowy stretch that we've been having for a while. Some of the mortals are quite weary of it now, and it sure doesn't make the hunting any easier!\" \n Demeter: \n\"The mortals are resourceful, Artemis. Their one redeeming quality, perhaps! They'll find a way through our long winter here. They ought to, since they brought it on themselves.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Demeter: \n\"Why, Zagreus, my gentle Artemis here was just saying how concerned she was for your predicament! I'm sure she'd like it if we both could help you in this case.\" \n Artemis: \n\"Concerned? I don't see anyone concerned, you have this, Zagreus! You don't need anybody's help, and you can get through this all on your own, though just in case, and I mean just in case! Um, here.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Dionysus\"&gt;Dionysus&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Oh, great, it's you, Zagreus! Here, let me offer you some fine new Boons, as well as Lord Dionysus here, who I am sure would love to talk your ear off just as much as mine!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"\"Eh\", tells me I'm being awful loud, and to back off, all sorts of nasty stuff like that, what can you do, though, right?\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Zag, man, I was just attempting here to get our good friend Artemis to finally make an appearance at one of my feasts, it's just... wouldn't you know, she's all preoccupied, something about a hunt?\" \n Artemis: \n\"That's right, Lord Dionysus, a \"hunt\"! Which requires lots and lots of \"total quiet\", and clear-minded focus. So, if you'll excuse me?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"\"Tsk\", \"um\", Zagreus... rather than greet you as I normally would do, instead, allow me to present you my illustrious, kind, generous lord father, your greatest Uncle Zeus!\" \n Zeus: \n\"\"Erm\", thank you for the introduction, Daughter! Now, you run along, go frolic with your nymphs, or something! Leave me to assist my nephew, here. Bestow on him your faint blessing, if you must.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Zeus: \n\"Now, Zagreus, once you arrive, we'll have to find for you a suitable mate, won't we? Fine young man such as yourself! Normally, there's much to choose from around here, with some exceptions, of course... such as my cunning daughter, Artemis. Willfully uninclined to take a mate, at all!\" \n Artemis: \n\"Yes, Zagreus, in spite of all these perfect, chiseled prospects everywhere about, yearning to marry or embarrass me, for some reason, I prefer to spend my time mostly alone or with my nymph friends in the woods!\" \nBeing Invited to the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt; (Pre-Epilogue).\n Zagreus: \n\"Found you, Huntress, here. In the name of Hades! Olympus, this is an official message! Especially for you, Lady Artemis!\" \n Artemis: \n\"Some kind of special message for me...! Oh, looks like there's one for everybody on Olympus, then. Felt rather special for a moment, there! And now you're making me check in with all the others. Great!\" \nPost-Epilogue Dialogue.\n Artemis: \n\"Have to say, I had a pretty decent time with everybody at our little visit recently! Met you, Uncle Hades, even great Achilles! Still don't quite appreciate you tricking us, but \"eh\"! I can get over it eventually. Anyway, you still could use assistance from me, right?\"\nMiscellaneous Conversations.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; Clearing a Run.\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, hold a moment, Zagreus, I could have sworn... you were so close, before, but now you're back? Ah, must have tripped up just when victory was close at hand, it happens all the time. We'll get you out of there, you'll see!\" \nBuying Boon at &lt;a href=\"Charon\"&gt;Charon&lt;/a&gt;'s Shop.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"You know, one thing I'll say for Charon there? He doesn't talk too much. And since neither do you, I'm letting you have this.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"I guess this means you must have paid the boatman's ransom here, and whatever price he charged you, it was worth it.\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"Even there in your Underworld, it seems quality hunting gear doesn't come cheap, apparently!\" \nDialogue 04.\n Artemis: \n\"You hunted down a real bargain there in Charon's shop, though how about we try a slightly bigger deal on for size right now?\"\nHigh Affinity Dialogue.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"I think you might enjoy it on Olympus, there's... a lot of feasting here, I guess, and the air is cool and crisp, and it's much brighter than it is down there. Sounds like a dream, right?\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"I hope that once you make it to Olympus we'll go hunting sometime, you and I, you know? I like being on my own and all, but it's been nice, talking to you like this.\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"I grow so tired of the others here, you know? Much rather be out with the woodland nymphs than with these gods upon this mountaintop. You must know what it's like.\"\nPost-Flashback Dialogue.\n Artemis: \n\"Living on Olympus here, I'm surrounded by my family, but I always felt alone. I know that's not the same as your experience, but, I'm just saying I relate to what you're going through.\" \nAbout Legendary Boon.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"All right, get ready for this, Zagreus, because I seldom share the greatest of my hunting secrets like I am about to.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"All right, no need to keep on toying with your prey. Here comes one of my finest blessings, \"now\"!\" \nDialogue 03.\n Artemis: \n\"I don't reveal my greatest hunting techniques for just anybody, Zagreus, so you better appreciate what you're about to get, and use it to go far!\" \nDialogue 04.\n Artemis: \n\"How about we not take any chances this time, Zagreus? So here, this is the best I've got. You better not waste it!\" \nAbout Backstory.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Something's troubled me a little, about you. You fight so desperately. At first I thought you simply lacked in patience. But now I see it's urgency that drives you. What is it that you're after, really...?\" \nAbout Run Progress.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Let's see. You blundered headlong into danger for the past six chambers or more. And you made such a racket I could almost hear it from Olympus. I have to say, your hunting skills are rather unconventional.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"I'm with you every step till you arrive here, Zagreus. Then I will probably ignore you like the rest. Just warning you ahead of time, all right?\" \nAbout &lt;a href=\"Gigantic%20Vermin\"&gt;Vermin&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Say, were you hunting vermin near the surface lately, Zagreus? That's practically just like the real thing! It must have been a thrill!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"You've become a right accomplished vermin hunter, Zagreus! Maybe you'll get to use those skills against worthier creatures soon enough.\"\nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Heart-Seeking%20Bow\"&gt;Coronacht&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01 (&lt;a href=\"Heart-Seeking%20Bow%23Aspects\"&gt;Aspect of Rama&lt;/a&gt;).\n Artemis: \n\"Um, Zagreus, did you attempt to chat with Coronacht just yet? Remember, tell the bow \"I see you drawn in the arms of the seventh avatar! \"Something good's supposed to happen if you do, some divine archer-person's aspect I should think? You going to try it soon, or not?\" \nDialogue 02 (&lt;a href=\"Heart-Seeking%20Bow%23Aspects\"&gt;Aspect of Rama&lt;/a&gt;).\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, look at that! The message must have worked! Practically can see that shiny bow from here! I've never wielded Coronacht myself, at least not yet. Though if the Fates are sending visions to me of its past or future bearers, why, I guess I'm bound to get my shot eventually!\" \nDialogue 03 (Revealing &lt;a href=\"Heart-Seeking%20Bow%23Aspects\"&gt;Aspect of Rama&lt;/a&gt;).\n Artemis: \n\"Now listen, Zagreus, admittedly this is a little strange, even from me. I have a message for your bow! That's right, just go on up to Coronacht next time, and tell it with a firm, commanding voice, \"I see you drawn in the arms of the seventh avatar! \"Let me know how it goes, OK?\" \nDialogue 04 (&lt;a href=\"Heart-Seeking%20Bow%23Aspects\"&gt;Aspect of Chiron&lt;/a&gt;).\n Artemis: \n\"That's not the Coronacht I know, isn't that... Chiron the centaur's bow? So that was Coronacht, as well? Seems every decent bow was just a version of that thing! Except for mine, of course.\" \nDialogue 05 (&lt;a href=\"Heart-Seeking%20Bow%23Aspects\"&gt;Aspect of Hera&lt;/a&gt;).\n Artemis: \n\"Say, that's the bow Stepmother Hera herself once wielded, isn't it? Her aspect of Coronacht! I'd know it from the... frankly rather sinister skulls all over it. It's very Hera, trust me.\" \nDialogue 06 (In General).\n Artemis: \n\"Hey, how'd you get your hands on a nice bow like that? You take good care of Coronacht for me, so I can try it too once you're up here.\" \nDialogue 07 (In General).\n Artemis: \n\"Have to admit, you're very capable with Coronacht. Now I can hit a bull's eye in my sleep, but you'll be right there with me if I don't keep practicing I think!\" \nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Fists\"&gt;Twin Fists&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"When did you get your hands on Malphon, the Twin Fists? Hands \"in\", I ought to say! I heard that one time, Demeter, she smacked her father right square in the face with those! Bet you can probably relate.\" \nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Rail\"&gt;Adamant Rail&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis: \n\"Well, look at you, with Exagryph, the Rail of Adamant! Seems much too noisy-complicated as a hunting weapon when you could just use a nice quiet bow, but hey, to each her own.\" \nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"Lady Artemis, I hope that you'll accept this offering, for all your kindness and support.\" \n Artemis: \n\"Hey thank you for this, really. And, I've just the thing to offer in return. It's just a gift, OK?\" \n\"Artemis gives &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Arrowhead\"&gt;Adamant Arrowhead&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n Zagreus: \n\"Lady Artemis, you honor me.\"\n2nd Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"My lady Artemis! This is nothing, next to all your grace and favor.\" \n Artemis: \n\"Hey wait, this is an offering, for me? I, \"oh\", that's very kind, though, let's get back to hunting, now, OK?\" \n3rd Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"Lady Artemis! I am indebted to you, for the strength and cunning you have given me.\" \n Artemis: \n\"Look, Zagreus, I don't know what to say, except for... thanks!\" \n4th Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"My lady Artemis, your favor's been invaluable to me. No finer huntress ever walked the surface of the earth, or underneath.\" \n Artemis: \n\"You're being very nice to me, and that makes me suspicious, understand? So, you want more of that... you keep this up.\" \n5th Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"At the risk of incurring your wrath, Lady Artemis, I hope you will accept this from me, and see that my gratitude for all you have done for me is genuine.\" \n Artemis: \n\"What do you know, another gift of Nectar, that's... quite thoughtful of you, Zagreus! Normally don't care much for the stuff, but, every now and then, I mean... why not?\" \n6th Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"In your honor, Lady Artemis! Your mighty blessings have helped me through so many trials now, and I always welcome your level-headed presence here.\" \n Artemis: \n\"Look, I like being worshiped just as much as anybody, Zagreus, though bear in mind that you can always leave the worship of me to the forest nymphs, all right?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Ambrosia\"&gt;Ambrosia&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"I know you have no shortage of Ambrosia on Olympus, Lady Artemis, but I imagine it's less often that the stuff go all the way from there to here, and back. What can I say? You make me proud to be a member of this family.\" \n Artemis: \n\"I never felt like I could be myself with everybody on this mountaintop, you know? So much posturing, and bickering, and... I just head out to the woods most of the time. Maybe you understand me better than the rest, I've no idea still. But I appreciate you've made attempts to try.\" "}
{"id": "3871", "revid": "55184635", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3871", "title": "Artemis/Quotes (Hades II)", "text": "The following are quotes from &lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nFirst Meeting.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis : It's been too long, Sister. Look at you, on your great hunt! Not the ideal circumstances but you've finally begun. Know that the family has your back, surprised as they are about this.\n Melino\u00eb : No shortage lately of surprises on Olympus or below. It's good to see you again, Artemis. But, I must be off. Time's against us, and all that.\n Artemis : Time's an old fool to busy besieging the mountain of the gods to sense the threat headed his way. Go get him.\nDialogue 02.\n Artemis : \"Hey Melino\u00eb, I just wrapped a debrief here with Sister &lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;. This place has changed a \"lot\" since last I checked!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Hi Artemis, welcome! We've had to scramble a bit to make ready for everything. Can I show you around? Have you said hi to &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;?\"\n Artemis : \"Oh, \"no\", I have to go. Olympus needs me back up top, at least a little while. Maybe next time, all right?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I hear you. Bye for now.\"\nKeepsake Dialogue (&lt;a href=\"White%20Antler\"&gt;White Antler&lt;/a&gt;).\n Artemis : \"Brought the White Antler with you just in case! The stag who gave it up, it was his time. And I vowed to him I'd make it quick. His Shade and I, we still commune every so often!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Artemis, your tales have this remarkable capacity to warm the heart and yet disturb the mind. In case you ever need a calling other than the hunt.\"\n Artemis : \"If none of this works out, I was thinking \"songs\" and \"music-making?\" If Apollo can do it, so can \"I.\" Though we've not tired of the hunter's life just yet.\"\nAbouth the Scenery.\n&lt;a href=\"Erebus\"&gt;Erebus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"Poor wretches, left to linger here. Could be relaxing in Elysium, or Asphodel at least. No wonder they're upset.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Chronos claimed it was an act of magnanimity, unsealing the Underworld gates, letting the dead roam free. This can't possibly be better than when my father ruled.\"\n Artemis : \"Hey, at least it means I can set foot in these parts without inciting some huge territorial dispute! Setting aside the fact that we're already in the middle of one.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Oceanus\"&gt;Oceanus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"Fine mess we made! Not many hiding-places here compared to Erebus. Might be the end of the line for me... I'm a huntress, not a fisher.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Fishing is a form of hunting, isn't it? Anyway I appreciate the backup, and understand if you're now at the limit of your range. Olympus probably expects you back.\"\n Artemis : \"They'll want to hear from me! About the situation, and about {#Emph}you{#Prev}, too. You know they still take me and Hermes for their spies? Although, we do tell them a lot...\"\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Surface\"&gt;The Surface&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis : \"You made it quite a ways up on the surface recently, Sister Selene said. Did it live up to all your hopes and dreams?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I tend to have a lot of nightmares, and it did live up to those. The dead are left to linger there. They should be safely in the Underworld!\"\n Artemis : \"Well, Chronos evidently has other ideas for how things should be governed. I know your main objective is below, though... thank you for any aid you can provide up top.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Artemis : \"So much for visiting the surface, huh? Not seen a trace of you up there! Don't feel bad. You have nice woods here, too!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I'm not supposed to be up there... could hardly breathe. But there might be something I can do. Hermes wouldn't have asked me to go if it wasn't important.\"\n Artemis : \"No, I guess not. I'd offer to escort you though Olympus wants me to stay out of sight. And I won't bother saying not to push yourself too hard...\"\n&lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Ephyra\"&gt;City of Ephyra&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis : \"Look at \"you\", Sister! Your brother once had us all convinced he was trying to fight his way to Olympus. Now none of us can believe you're trying to do it for real.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I've known Hermes about as long as you, and can count the number of favors he's asked of me on one hand. Besides, I could use the change of scenery.\"\n Artemis : \"Then by all means! What a time, that you're on your way up to the mountain while I'm on my way down to the Underworld. At least we crossed paths!\"\nDialogue 02 (loose dialogue in the files).\n Melino\u00eb : \"Hermes wouldn't have asked me to go if it wasn't important. Besides, I could use the change of scenery.\"\nMiscellaneous Conversations.\nAbout Mission.\nDialogue 01.\n Melino\u00eb : \"Why has Olympus sent you all the way out here, anyway? I thought you'd have gone back by now. You're always welcome in the Crossroads!\"\n Artemis : \"Appreciate it, Sister, and I might stop by, but... I don't mind the woods. As for why I'm all the way out here, mostly to spy on you! Olympus likes to be informed.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I'm certain that they do. Do you ever slip up with them? By now the other gods must have their suspicions about you and Hermes.\"\n Artemis : \"Depends on who you're talking about I guess, but for the most part they just think we're young and flighty. But we're the best they've got.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Melino\u00eb : \"So when you're not aiding me in my repeated failures, what else have you been up to, Artemis? Some special quarry you're after?\"\n Artemis : \"There might be. Olympus has been shaking, for reasons unknown. Sister Selene asked that I look into it. Surely it's nothing, right?\"\nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Sisters\"&gt;Silver Sisters&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"When I became one of the Silver Sisters, I figured all we'd really do was stalk in shadows, make occasional reports... but this is a full-on \"worst-case scenario!\"\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"You sound excited rather than dismayed. You must have known it'd come to this eventually. Not like Headmistress would band us together just for ceremony's sake.\"\n Artemis : \"No, I guess you're right. Still, we've been together biding our time for so long... I got to thinking we might never get the opportunity to strike. Yet here we are!\"\nAbout Family.\nDialogue 01.\n Melino\u00eb : \"You've been so far from home for so long. Don't you miss being on Olympus? If not now, then... back before the Titan's siege?\"\n Artemis : \"What, you mean being with my father and stepmother, my perfect twin brother, and all the rest? Just because I'm willing to aid them doesn't mean I'm willing to live with them again.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Artemis : \"So what do you think of the family? Most of them are stuck on their mountaintop, though... you've seen what they're like.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Oh they don't seem so bad! Especially things being as they are. But you can't stand any of them...\"\n Artemis : \"Hey I wouldn't go \"that\" far! Though, yes, they can get under my skin. They're going to owe us \"big\" once all of this is over.\"\nAbout the &lt;a href=\"Sister%20Blades\"&gt;Sister Blades&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis : \"Those blades of yours doing you any good? Let me know if you need any, \"erm... pointers...?\"\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"The Sister Blades are almost like having you by my side in every fight. Though, you can shoot a lot farther than I can throw...\"\n Artemis : \"\"Oh\", don't be so hard on yourself, I can shoot farther than anybody! Especially Apollo. Well, just keep going for their vitals, and you'll be fine.\"\nDialogue 02 (Aspect of Artemis).\n Artemis : \"Hey, I recognize those blades! Didn't want to let on before, but... now I guess you know. You best be taking care of them! \"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Not to worry. I am, I swear! So, \"you\" were the bearer of the Sister Blades yourself? Did you have to give them up because of me...?\"\n Artemis : \"I gave them up because I did what needed to be done. Hecate so likes her little tests. Anyway I'm glad to see old Lim and Oros in good hands.\"\nAbout the Moon.\n Artemis : \"A full moon... Sister Selene's power at its peak. On nights like this, I truly feel my immortality. May our combined strength be enough.\"\nExtended Send-off.\n Melino\u00eb : \"Hey, Artemis. Is everything all right?\"\n Artemis : \"So much to talk about, so little time, Sister. I'm needed elsewhere, but I wanted to make sure to send you off.\"\nAbout Progress.\n Melino\u00eb : \"Any progress yet with your investigation?\"\n Artemis : \"Not near as much as I'd like. Here, let me give you a boost. Maybe you'll get somewhere even if I don't.\"\nAbout Retrying.\n Melino\u00eb : \"You've likely heard I didn't get there, Artemis. Didn't even come close.\"\n Artemis : \"Sister, I have \"every\" faith in you, but not even \"I\" believed you were going to vanquish Chronos straightaway. Let's be a little realistic here?\"\nAbout Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Apollo\"&gt;Apollo&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"Has my little brother lived up to his shining reputation so far? At least he did his part. Soon as I told him about you, sure enough he was plenty eager to let all Olympus know.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Apollo was very kind. Though, easy for me to say, I'm not his twin. What'd you tell him anyway?\"\n Artemis : \"Only the truth! That I ran into the reclusive Witch of the Crossroads while scouting out our foe... and that she introduced me to a secret \"Titan killer\" she's been training up.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"You just didn't tell him how long ago that was. So now they really think this long-lost relative of theirs is going to find Chronos and slay him?\"\n Artemis : \"Oh, they think you don't stand a chance! But they don't have a lot of options, so... they'll support you anyway, especially since you're family and all. And you know \"I\" will.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"You bested Sister Hecate! She told me so herself, and with dare-I-say more than a hint of pride. Though, she's intent on testing you still?\" \n Melino\u00eb : \"She always said I can't beat Chronos if I can't beat her. And so we spar. I think she's gone easy on me, to boost my confidence.\"\n Artemis : \"Well, I can plainly see she failed. Gone \"easy?\" If there's one thing the Witch of the Crossroads hasn't ever done, it's that.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Selene\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis : \"I can often depend on Sister Selene's light to guide me on my hunts. But where you're going, she can't follow, can she? Nor can I.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"And Headmistress Hecate is needed at the Crossroads. I alone have the authority to enter the House of Hades. If I can make it there.\"\n Artemis : \"Hey, what do you mean \"if?\" It's a matter of \"when\", as far as I'm concerned. I'm thinking maybe very \"soon\", in fact.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Artemis : \"I can often depend on Sister Selene's light to guide me on my hunts. But where you're going, she can't follow easily, can she? Nor can I.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Sister Selene has her ways, though I know it's difficult for her, and Headmistress is needed at the Crossroads. I alone have the authority to enter the House of Hades. But I'd have never gotten there without you all.\"\n Artemis : \"Could \"really\" use a proper hunting party for this one! Fortunately it's kind of our thing as Silver Sisters to not have to be in the same place at the same time.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"Hermes finally got a hold of you, did he? Sounds like things have really taken a turn on Olympus. Glad I'm not there!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Artemis, how can you say that? It's your home. I'm going to see if I can head up there and lend a hand.\"\n Artemis : \"Is that even possible for you, born of the Underworld and all that? Then again, you're a witch! Must have a remedy for everything!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \"You haven't seen Nemesis tonight, have you? Not that she should be anywhere near here, as opposed to keeping watch over the gateways at the Crossroads.\"\n Artemis : \"I haven't seen her, no. But I was tracking her! Those footprints are only slightly harder to spot than \"she \" is. She's not supposed to be out here, is she...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"...That she is not. She's just trying to make herself useful, I get it. And the Fates themselves know that I probably could use the help. Though, how have you two been?\"\n Artemis : \"We each need company, we each need solitude, the same old thing. She's frustrated, which can go a couple of ways depending on the night. Anyway, she's a big girl!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Fates\"&gt;The Fates&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"It's really true about the Fates, that Chronos somehow got to them? Doesn't want to take any chances anymore. Did the Fates prophesize their own captivity...?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"How can you be so casual about this? If the Fates themselves couldn't stop Chronos, we won't have an easy time! We're beholden to chance ourselves.\"\n Artemis : \"So what if we are! You know not even \"I\"always hit my mark. What do I do if I miss? \"I take another shot.\"The greater the skill, the less is up to chance.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Artemis : \"It's strange, isn't it? He's our own grandfather... Chronos, I mean. But, I feel no connection to him at all! I just want him gone.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Doesn't matter who he is; he's a threat. We're the Silver Sisters. We'll \"make\" him gone. For the sake of the realms.\"\n Artemis : \"Strictly business then, is it? Even still, funny how it falls on \"us\" to settle the older generation's scores.\"\nDialogue 02 (Lost Battle).\n Artemis : \"Got all the way down to the House of Hades, so I heard. Must be nice having fated authority over the lowest reaches of the Underworld... unless you're Chronos.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"He was most certainly annoyed. Wields a scythe that's twice my height, surrounds himself with feral Satyr-worshipers ready to die for him. I'm not surprised it once took both our fathers and more to bring him down.\"\n Artemis : \"No reason to compare yourself. They're high and mighty lords of the heavens and the Underworld, but they fought Chronos by necessity. You were trained to do \"precisely this.\"\"\nDialogue 03 (Won Battle).\n Artemis : \"You found Chronos... sank your fangs into his throat. Sister Hecate gave me the gist. How'd you do it...? Found some exploitable weakness, something like that?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Mostly I just kept evading a lot. He's very powerful, but must have underestimated my ability to resist his tricks.\"\n Artemis : \"He won't always underestimate you, though. Must have his vulnerabilities. \"The old are seldom wise, and often weak\", right? He's bloodied... go for the kill.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"Hey, is it really true Moros himself showed up at your Crossroads because you \"summoned\" him? As in, you \"literally invited Doom...?\"\"\n Melino\u00eb : It doesn't seem the wisest course when you put it that way. Chronos once was brought low by a prophecy of the Three Fates. I felt they might be willing to intervene again.\"\n Artemis : \"And they did so by sending you the embodiment of misfortune and unforeseen consequences. Well if that's what the Fates have in store, you're going to need \"this.\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Polyphemus\"&gt;Polyphemus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"That massive Cyclops Polyphemus... saw him fast asleep the other night! Then \"you\" were able to sneak up and incapacitate him, just like \"that!\" I stay far downwind of him, myself.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I'm tempted to just smile and nod through this one, Artemis, but my dealings with the Cyclops haven't involved much stealth. Though at least I can get past him, at this point.\"\n Artemis : \"And how do you get through the Rift beyond the docks, you \"swim?\" You still like doing things the hard way. The \"only\" way!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Eris\"&gt;Eris&lt;/a&gt;.\n Artemis : \"You probably know \"Eris\" has been buzzing around Olympus recently? One good lightning bolt from Father Zeus would normally take \"care\" of that, but... he's been occupied.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"One good lightning bolt, how about one good arrow? We'd be saved a lot of trouble if Eris were to be plucked from the sky one of these nights.\"\n Artemis : \"I'd gladly volunteer, it's just that Father has everything \"well under control.\" Says I'm needed way out here instead. But if I do spot the wings of Strife... they're going down.\"\nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \"It's been a pleasure to have worked more closely with you, Sister Artemis. This is hardly worth the gift of impeccable precision, though I wanted you to have it.\"\n Artemis : \"Doing the old traditions now, are we? Well sure, then I accept your offering, Sister Melino\u00eb. And I've an offering for \"you\", in kind!\"\n\"Artemis gives &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"White%20Antler\"&gt;White Antler&lt;/a&gt;.'\n Melino\u00eb : \"Truly? You're the best.\"\n2nd Time.\n Artemis : \"You do know we have \"barrels\" of this stuff up on Olympus, right? Used to, at least. Damn near forgotten what it tastes like, come to think...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"May the good memories come flooding back! Whenever you have the time for it, of course.\"\n3rd Time.\n Artemis : \"What's all this extra generosity from you lately? It's putting me on edge. Don't you go acting like this is goodbye...!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"It's merely that the arrow-riddled remnants of my foes give me occasion to reflect! I tell myself never to take my dear friends for granted.\"\n4th Time.\n Artemis : \"I can't exactly drink this on the hunt, you know! But I can squirrel it away for safekeeping. Maybe once all this is settled, we can share a bottle and get properly caught up.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Or, failing that, we could always keep on teaming against vengeful spirits and the like! Although it's nice to keep the possibility in mind.\"\n5th Time.\n Artemis : \"Hey, thank you! Sure enough, Olympus started running a little low on this stuff. I'll be sure to lord it over the others, long as you don't mind me exploiting your good graces.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I don't recall anything about exploiting one another's good graces in the bylaws of the Silver Sisters, so you should be fine! May you enjoy it either way.\"\n6th Time.\n Artemis : \"...Hard making friends with goddesses, but I have what {#Emph}I {#Prev}need. We can be on our own without feeling alone, you know? I hope you know. That's how it is for me.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"I do know, and feel much the same. When we're not watching one another's backs, we have Selene and Headmistress watching over us. Still, it's always good to see you face-to-face.\"\n Artemis : \"You, too. Most of my family I can do without most of the time. You're an exception! We may not be sisters by blood, but... you'll always be Sister Melino\u00eb to me.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Likewise, Sister Artemis.\""}
{"id": "2488", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2488", "title": "Artemis/Relationships", "text": "Family.\nZeus.\n&lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's father.&lt;br&gt;She strives to be an obedient daughter, going so far as to make a grand presentation for him, even though long speeches are not her strong suit. However, Zeus often responds with indirect criticisms, suggesting that he may not fully understand her. At the same time, Artemis feels that her father likes to invade her personal space and constantly leaving her red-faced in front of &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; with embarrassing paternal comments.\nShe kept &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;'s existence a secret from her family, especially her father, which shows their untrustworthy nature.\nApollo.\n&lt;a href=\"Apollo\"&gt;Apollo&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's younger twin brother.&lt;br&gt;Artemis and Apollo share a bond as twin siblings. Artemis likes to affectionately refer to him as her \"little brother\". Despite being like night and day, Artemis entrusted Apollo firsthand with the revelation of Melino\u00eb's existence on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Olympus\"&gt;Olympus&lt;/a&gt;, a secret that her brother quickly spread. This indicates the great consideration that Artemis has for Apollo, despite not always trusting him, making him one of the few men, alongside Zagreus, with whom she shares a strong relationship. Melino\u00eb acknowledges that she lacks the twin connection to fully understand their twin bond.\nHera.\n&lt;a href=\"Hera\"&gt;Hera&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis' stepmother.&lt;br&gt;Likely out of loyalty for her biological mother Leto, Artemis prefers to keep her distance from her stepmother.\nAthena.\n&lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's half-sister.&lt;br&gt;Artemis comments to Zagreus that she's never sure if Athena is showing off or trying to prove something. Athena retorts, commenting that such interactions between the two are not uncommon for sisters; \"and what is a perfect family without routine fights?\"\nAphrodite.\n&lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;: The Goddess of Love and Beauty.&lt;br&gt;Artemis finds Aphrodite invasive, and Aphrodite knows that Artemis isn't honest with her feelings, and may also tease her for being nervous in Zagreus' presence. Though even Aphrodite acknowledges that this could also be due to her frequent night outings. She can be quite a hypocrite, claiming that Artemis is so focused on the hunt that she has forgotten to acquire \"social graces\". Artemis retorts that walking around naked is hardly a show of social graces.\nAres.\n&lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's half-brother.&lt;br&gt;In his Duo Benefit with Artemis, he is happy to try to work together, as he considers Hunting and War quite similar domains. Artemis finds her older half-brother's comments chilling, cringes and does not share the same feelings.\nHephaestus.\n&lt;a href=\"Hephaestus\"&gt;Hephaestus&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's half-brother.&lt;br&gt;\nHermes.\n&lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's half-brother.&lt;br&gt;She usually turns her back on him, not out of disdain, but because she is quiet and he is very talkative. Hermes considers Artemis a very cool distant big sister and comments on how skilled Artemis is, although he is faster, she is still very fast.\nThey both were key figures in Melino\u00eb's childhood and kept her existence a secret from the rest of their family. This shows that despite their opposite personalities, they trust each other.\nDionysus.\n&lt;a href=\"Dionysus\"&gt;Dionysus&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's half-brother.&lt;br&gt;He regards Artemis as a kind of hermit. Dionysus has tried more than once to include her in his usual feasts and revelries, but she cannot stand the noise. She disapproves of Dionysus' inconsequential lifestyle. In her dialogues with Zagreus, she warns him not to get involved with her partying half-brother.\nDemeter.\n&lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's foster aunt.&lt;br&gt;Though they share similar views of Athena, they don't have the same assessment of mortals, Artemis complains how the snowy weather is making their hunts difficult. Demeter warns that humans are resourceful and deceitful and will nonetheless find a way to survive.\nHestia.\n&lt;a href=\"Hestia\"&gt;Hestia&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's foster aunt.&lt;br&gt;\nPoseidon.\n&lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's uncle.&lt;br&gt;Artemis seems to have a low opinion on her uncle, dodging him as much as she can, insulting him by calling him a big fat oaf, and wondering as to who is worst; him or her father Zeus. Because of this, she has been told to be more respectful around her uncle, something that she considers to be hard. Poseidon in turn, considers Artemis to be too stiff, unabled to take a simple jest and that her sour looks makes it harder for her to attract a potential mate. \nFriends.\nCallisto.\n&lt;a href=\"Callisto\"&gt;Callisto&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's best friend.&lt;br&gt;Although Callisto does not appear in Hades, she is mentioned by Artemis many times. She will begin telling Zagreus stories of her adventures with Callisto, the forest nymph who can mysteriously transform into a bear. Artemis notes that she considers Callisto and the other nymphs her closest friends. Later, Artemis also tells Callisto about Zagreus' adventure. Eurydice points out that nymphs are often treated as lesser deities, so the fact that Artemis treats them as equals is quite telling for a goddess of high status.\nChthonic Gods.\nThe Gods of the Underworld.\nZagreus.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's cousin.&lt;br&gt;In her relationship with Zagreus, she is the only one who refrains from using affectionate terms, addressing him solely by his name. He may perceive her as a distant role model, although deep down she experiences considerable nervousness and uncertainty in his presence. Artemis doesn't hesitate to reprimand him whenever he engages in actions that she disapproves of, such as succumbing to Dionysus' influence. However, if Zagreus manages to cultivate a stronger bond with her, she will reluctantly acknowledge, with a touch of disdain, that he holds a place among her closest confidants, although not a priority to her.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;, after Zagreus is captured by &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;, she grows relatively close to his younger sister, Melino\u00eb. Assuming the role of Melino\u00eb's protector, she assists her in the mission to defeat Chronos, serving as both a mentor and an older sister figure, a role that Zagreus couldn't fulfill.\nMelino\u00eb.\n&lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's cousin.&lt;br&gt;She was a key figure in Melino\u00eb's childhood, and alongside Hecate and Selene, they're part of the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Sisters\"&gt;Silver Sisters&lt;/a&gt;. She kept her cousin's existence a secret from the rest of the family until it was deemed worthy of being known. Artemis will aid Melino\u00eb out in field whenever possible, and both can engage in conversations afterwards. She affectionately calls her cousin \"Sister Melino\u00eb\".\nHecate.\n&lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's maternal cousin.&lt;br&gt;They both belong to the Silver Sisters, besides already having a familiar connection. Hecate allowed Artemis to take part in Melino\u00eb's childhood, showing great trust in her ability to keep it a secret.\nHades.\n&lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's uncle.&lt;br&gt;Achilles believes that of all the Olympians, Hades would get along the best with Artemis, and indeed, the two have much in common. \nEven though Artemis doesn't spend as much time away from her Olympian relatives as her equally solitary uncle, it is also asserted that Hades approves of Artemis, as she doesn't care about being praised and is dedicated to her work, much like he is.\nIn the Epilogue she finally met her uncle and is excited, although she doesn't like him hiding many things, but she is willing to forget everything to maybe get to know each other better.\nNemesis.\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;: Retribution Incarnate.&lt;br&gt;Artemis is the only Olympian who outright grants boons to Nemesis. They're familiar with one another, and share some similarities, like wanting to be left alone every now and again. It's implied their relationship is currently a little strained.\nUnderworld Residents.\nAchilles.\n&lt;a href=\"Achilles\"&gt;Achilles&lt;/a&gt;: The famed warrior hero of the Trojan War.&lt;br&gt;Artemis is a huge fangirl of Achilles. She admires his combat style and will recognize the Aspect of Achilles; she will talk excitedly about how many mortals have been \"completely slaughtered\" by him and will ask Zagreus to pass on her regards. If Zagreus comes into contact with her while using Coronacht, she will eagerly tell him to take it to Olympus so she can try it out.\nEurydice.\n&lt;a href=\"Eurydice\"&gt;Eurydice&lt;/a&gt;: A nymph musician.&lt;br&gt;Eurydice is surprised by the fact that Artemis, even though she is a goddess, sees the nymphs as equals.\nTitans.\nSelene.\n&lt;a href=\"Selene\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt;: Moon Incarnate.&lt;br&gt;They both are part of the Silver Sisters, and Artemis says she can always count on Selene's light to guide her in her nocturnal hunts. \nChronos.\n&lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;: Artemis's paternal grandfather.&lt;br&gt;Despite being her own grandfather, Artemis feels no connection to him and simply wants him gone."}
{"id": "442", "revid": "17777", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=442", "title": "Artifacts", "text": "Artifacts are rewards for winning Underworld &lt;a href=\"Chambers%20and%20Encounters\"&gt;Encounters&lt;/a&gt; which either benefit &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus's&lt;/a&gt; current escape attempt or can be spent to obtain permanent benefits on future attempts.\nCurrency Artifacts.\nThese can be spent on permanent upgrades and are obtained from standard Encounters. These resources persist after a run (i.e., they are not lost whether or not Zagreus succeeded in escaping) and can be used back in the House of Hades.\nBounty Artifacts.\nThese can be spent on permanent upgrades and are obtained by completing &lt;a href=\"Bounties\"&gt;Bounties&lt;/a&gt;.\nOther Artifacts.\nThese artifacts improve Zagreus's power in his current escape attempt. The benefits these grant will be lost after a run ends. With the exception of the Loyalty Card, Red Onion, and Anvil of Fates, all of these Artifacts are rewards for normal Encounters."}
{"id": "3179", "revid": "55184635", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3179", "title": "Ashes", "text": "Ashes are a common reagent currency used primarily to unlock &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Cards\"&gt;Arcana Cards&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads/Training%20Grounds%23The_Altar_of_Ashes\"&gt;Altar of Ashes&lt;/a&gt;. It is also used in various &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Cauldron&lt;/a&gt; incantations, as well as to unlock and upgrade &lt;a href=\"Gathering%20Tools\"&gt;Gathering Tools&lt;/a&gt; and certain aspects of the &lt;a href=\"Nocturnal%20Arms\"&gt;Nocturnal Arms&lt;/a&gt;.\nUsing Ashes.\nAshes are used for:"}
