{"id": "386", "revid": "40239097", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=386", "title": "Centaur Heart", "text": "Centaur Hearts are &lt;a href=\"Artifacts\"&gt;Artifacts&lt;/a&gt; found within the underworld which increase &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus's&lt;/a&gt; current and maximum &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt; by 25 for the current run. \nObtaining Centaur Hearts.\nCentaur Hearts can be found:\nA Centaur Heart found in an &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Erebus&lt;/a&gt; encounter or Mini-boss room will always grant 50 instead of 25.\nLife Affirmation.\nThe effect of Centaur Hearts can be increased with the &lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;'s boon \"Life Affirmation\". This effect does not apply to Centaur Hearts gained from Thanatos or other ways of increasing max &lt;a href=\"health\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "391", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=391", "title": "Cerberus", "text": "Cerberus is a massive three-headed dog charged with guarding the gates of the Underworld to prevent the dead from escaping. He is a magnificent beast, companion of &lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen Zagreus left the House for the first time, Cerberus threw a tantrum that wrecked the House's lounge area.\nOnce Zagreus reaches the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Styx\"&gt;Temple of Styx&lt;/a&gt;, Cerberus guards its exit. Zagreus must find a &lt;a href=\"Satyr%20Sack\"&gt;Satyr Sack&lt;/a&gt;, Cerberus's favorite snack, as a bribe to leave the area.\nCerberus returns in &lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;, having been cast out of the &lt;a href=\"Underworld\"&gt;Underworld&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt; he now guards the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Mourning\"&gt;Fields of Mourning&lt;/a&gt; but has been transformed into Infernal Cerberus which serves as the boss encounter of the Fields of Mourning.\nOnce he has been defeated, he'll run off to be with &lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Tartarus\"&gt;Tartarus&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nCerberus is the guardian of the Underworld and the faithful companion of &lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;master Hades&lt;/a&gt;. Despite his intimidating reputation, he now serves more as a pet than anything else in the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;. \nCerberus is a gentle, helpful, and playful dog. He has offered his companionship and protection to &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; when wore only diapers, swearing him eternal loyalty. Cerberus enjoys typical dog play, such as fetching, which can cause quite a bit of massive destruction. He loves Zagreus so much that he destroyed the lounge when Zagreus attempted to leave the Underworld for the first time.\nHades rewards Cerberus for his faithful work by allowing him to stay at home, but it is Cerberus who rewards Hades after a long day of work. He is reliable and cannot disobey his master's orders, but he can sometimes be persuaded with a simple bone.\nCerberus patrols the shores of the Styx to prevent strangers from entering or residents from leaving. It is possible to pet Cerberus (although only one of his heads enjoys pets) and indeed necessary to unlock certain improvements from the House Contractor. He can be needy, and when he becomes anxious, he may carelessly destroy the lounge, making it unavailable for immediate use. But overall, he is a great companion and is well-loved by all members of his family.\nPhysical description.\nCerberus is a formidable, three-headed guard dog depicted as a large and imposing creature, towering over many tall characters, including &lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;. He possesses bright red fur, and each of his heads features a distinct green nose and a salivating tongue with an orange-to-yellow gradient. This unique coloration may suggest the presence of acid or lava, further emphasizing of docile Cerberus's intimidating nature. \nHades.\nUpon taking notice of &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;' absence within the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;, Cerberus became agitated and upset, frustratingly destroying the Lounge. \nWhen Zagreus reaches the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Styx\"&gt;Temple of Styx&lt;/a&gt; he encounters Cerberus guarding the gate to the surface. Zagreus ultimately can't bring himself to fight Cerberus and opts to bribe him with a &lt;a href=\"Satyr%20Sack\"&gt;sack&lt;/a&gt; filled with an unknown content that Cerberus loves which allows him to leave the Underworld without fighting his canine friend.\nHades II.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt; took control of the Underworld, he cast out Cerberus as he had no need for him to the Fields of Mourning. There Cerberus was corrupted by its energies, warping him into the Infernal Beast.\nAs the Infernal Beast, he is the final encounter of the Fields of Mourning. After Melino\u00eb defeats him, he returns to his original form and leaves to find &lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt; and can be found along with Hades in Tartarus. Due to not having bonded with Melino\u00eb, Cerberus will refuse to let her pet him. \nIf Melino\u00eb defeats or fails to reach Chronos in Tartarus then Cerberus will be thrown out again to the Fields of Mourning reverting him back into his Infernal form which must be defeated again.\nAffinity.\nIf given &lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;, Cerberus gives Zagreus the &lt;a href=\"Old%20Spiked%20Collar\"&gt;Old Spiked Collar&lt;/a&gt;.\nZagreus can pet him at any time in the House.\nCerberus' affinity gauge maxes out at 9 hearts.\nIf affinity is maxed out with Cerberus, there will be unique text above his keepsake. this text states: \"from Cerberus; you share a ferocious bond\" as well as \"the hound of hell has entrusted all his loyalty in his master, and his master's son\".\nFavor.\nTo complete Cerberus' favor, he must be pet at least 20 times. (Pets given before the final favor lock was added to the game are not counted, so fortunately you must pet him another 20 times)\nPetting him 10 times earns the Three-Headed Boy &lt;a href=\"Achievements\"&gt;achievement&lt;/a&gt;, which is an indicator that you're at least halfway there.\nGallery.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nConcept=\nIllustration=\nMerchandise=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
