{"id": "2499", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2499", "title": "Cerberus/Relationships", "text": "Family.\nHades.\n&lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;: Cerberus's Owner.&lt;br&gt;Cerberus appears to be Hades' only genuine companion and reprieve from his endless work.\nZagreus.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;: Cerberus's Owner.&lt;br&gt;Cerberus is Zagreus's beloved pet and best friend. He is affectionate towards Zagreus, and is quite mournful when he leaves. Zagreus also refuses to fight Cerberus and dislikes his father using him as a way to guilt him into staying, implying emotional harm and potential physical harm (since the two would eventually have to fight should Zagreus continue his escape attempts) on the pet as a result of his son leaving.\nPersephone.\n&lt;a href=\"Persephone\"&gt;Persephone&lt;/a&gt;: Cerberus's Owner.&lt;br&gt;Cerberus wags his tail at Persephone when she returns. She greets him before even Hades, her own husband, saying that she missed him very much.\nHouse of Hades.\nMegaera and Thanatos.\n&lt;a href=\"Megaera\"&gt;Megaera&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thanatos\"&gt;Thanatos&lt;/a&gt;: Cerberus's friends.&lt;br&gt;He used to take care of Megaera and Thanatos when they were very young. They still play with Zagreus from time to time.\nSkelly.\n&lt;a href=\"Skelly\"&gt;Skelly&lt;/a&gt;: Training Dummy.&lt;br&gt;Cerberus always confuses Skelly with an bone and chews on him. It is still unclear whether Skelly likes it or not."}
