rts don't you Charon mate. Most of the dead are here in Asphodel correct?\"\nCharon: \"nnnnrrhhhh\u2026.\"\nZagreus: \"Hey Charon, I'm in Asphodel now, aren't I? I'd always heard this was some sort of flower-covered meadow type place, not such a\u2026terrifying hellscape.\"\nCharon: \"hhhaaaaaahhh\u2026.\"\nZagreus: \"Hi Charon! I finally met Hermes, god of swiftness, travel, bringing souls of the departed to your boat. Calls you his professional associate. You and he, you've been working together for a while, haven't you?\"\nCharon: \"Hrrrrnnghhhhhhhhh\u2026.:\nZagreus: \"You don't say.\"\nZagreus: \"Tell Hermes hey for me.\"\n- \"Upon leaving shop, no response.\"\nZagreus: \"Charon, I always thought Olympians never consorted with Chtonic gods such as yourself. But it sounds like Hermes is a close colleague of yours. You wouldn't\u2026happen to know why he's helping me, would you?\"\nCharon: \"Grrhhoooaaahhhhhh..!\"\nZagreus: \"I'm sorry mate i meant you no offense.\"\nZagreus: \"Charon, Hermes told me that the other Olympians are unaware he's been lending his support to me. I'm curious to know what's going on. I'm thinking of asking Nyx. Figured I'd check with you first. \"\nCharon: \"Mmnnnrraaauuugggghhh!!\"\nZagreus: \"I'll\u2026keep it to myself from now on, thanks!\"\nZagreus: \"Well, look at you Charon mate, you're looking well! Something's different about you, can't quite put my finger on it. Have you done something with your hair?\"\nCharon: \"Urrraaaaauuhgggghhh\"\nCharon: \"Hhhrrhhhh\u2026 hhrrnn\u2026. Hrrrrhhhhh...\"\nZagreus: \"I'm pleased to have you as a friend as well, Charon. The pleasure's mine.\"\nGifting Nectar.\nNectar 1.\nZagreus: \"Charon, you've been such a reassuring sight I thought I'd offer you a token of my gratitude.\"\nCharon: \"Hrrrhhroooohh, hnnnn\u2026.\"\nZagreus: \"Wait you don\u2019t have to give me something in return, it was a gift! Though, you're insisting aren't you.\"\nNectar 2.\nCharon: \"Hohhh\u2026..\"\nZagreus: \"Glad you like it mate. Thank you for helping me out with your supply. Even if you fleece me with those prices.\"\nNectar 3.\nCharon: \"Hrrnnn\u2026?\"\nZagreus: \"You enjoy that mate! And, when it comes time to reconsider your price structure, hope you think of me!\"\nNectar 4.\nCharon: \"Hrrn, hhmmmmmm hmmmmmm\u2026.\"\nZagreus: \"Enjoy it, Charon mate! Don't go thinking I'm just being kind to get you to lower your prices for me, that would be unconscionable!\"\nNectar 5.\nCharon: \"Hrroooooooohhhh\u2026\"\nZagreus: \"You know, I thought you'd say that Charon mate, but I insist you take it and enjoy it all right?\"\nNectar 6.\nZagreus: \"Charon, mate? As a long time customer, I just wanted to take a moment to thank you again for your invaluable service as a part of my repeated attempts at getting out of here. What would I have done without your wares all these many times? Besides dying a lot faster.\"\nCharon: \"Hrrnngghh, grhhh, grhaaaaaaahhhh...\"\nNectar 7 (Final).\nZagreus: \"Charon, I realize you have a very busy schedule and certainly needn't keep going out of your way for me like this, so here. Just a small token of my appreciation for you. If you ever want to talk, know that I'm here.\"\nCharon: \"Hrrrnnnnnn\u2026! Thhhrrrrrrrnnnn...kkrrrrrhhhh...!\"\nConversations about Charon.\nZagreus: \u201cMother, one thing I was wondering about was, how did you summon Charon to your surface residence? Especially without, you know, being dead.\u201d\nPersephone: \u201cOh, why\u2026 he gave me his calling card after he graciously helped get me out of here the first time. No doubt at Nyx\u2019s request, but still. Never thought I\u2019d use it, but\u2026 I still kept it. Just in case.\u201d\nZagreus: \u201cNo idea what a calling card is, but, OK!\u201d&lt;br&gt;"}
