s of Nyx within our ranks. Granted, one's always fast asleep...\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Huunnnnnggghhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Forgive me, I must not have understood. Hypnos is of greater use this way...?\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Hmm, hmm...\"\n&lt;a href=\"Olympians\"&gt;Olympians&lt;/a&gt;.\n Charon : \n\"\"Hrrmmmm, nnnrrraaauggghhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Yes, my lord, I met Apollo, Grandmother, Uncle Poseidon... I've known Artemis and Hermes for so long, I'm impressed they kept my secret from the others all this time.\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Grrrnhhh...\"\n&lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01 (Hermes' Mission).\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"No sign of Hermes yet, my lord...? Forgive my impatience, I know infiltrating our enemy's ranks and discovering the details of his plans to conquer Olympus is sensitive work...\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Hrrmmmnnngggggghhhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Of course. He'll be back any evening now I'm sure.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Charon : \n\"\"Hrrrmmmmmm...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I'm certain he's all right, my lord. This is Hermes we're talking about! It's not like anyone could catch him, even if he were in peril.\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Nrrgghhh...\"\nDialogue 03.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I heard from Hermes at last, my lord! He didn't get into the details of what he discovered, though perhaps you know more.\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Auugggghhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I understand. It's not my wish to pry.\"\nDialogue 04.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Hermes wanted me to tell you \"hey\", my lord. A message he'd surely deliver himself if he could. Though he seems well enough.\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Hhhrrrrrmmmm...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Of course, my lord.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You're not particularly close with your brothers or sisters, are you? When you chance to visit us, Nemesis all but ignores you...\"\n Charon : \n\"Nrrrmmm, \"hhaaaaahhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I know, it's just...\"\nDialogue 02.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I know that you've seen Nemesis about. She's supposed to be at her post, but... I think you probably can understand. Whatever it takes for the family and the realm, right?\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Rrrrauuggh, heehhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Then may she go unseen.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You can sense it, can't you, my lord? The mark of Primordial Chaos. It seems I have another patron from the ranks of the chthonic gods.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Eris\"&gt;Eris&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Eris returned to the Crossroads, my lord. Forgive me for speaking ill of one of your siblings, but... I always fear the worst when she's around. Could she be working against us?\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Mnngghghhhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"If only she was more like you.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Your mother Nyx, my lord... I saw her lately in a nightmare or a dream. She was very beautiful... and she was unharmed, I think.\"\n Charon : \n\"Mrmmm, \"nrruuunnngghhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"We're going to find her. I swear it.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Fates\"&gt;The Fates&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You know already, don't you, my lord? About the Three Fates. That Chronos has your sisters in his thrall. Lord Moros is safe with us, at least.\"\n Charon : \n\"Kkhhh, \"kkhhrrrraaauugggghhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Do you truly think so...?\"\n&lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It's reassuring to know Artemis has been keeping track of things around here lately, my lord. She seems unusually well-supplied, as well.\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Hhrrraaauuggghhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Oh, I won't tell a soul.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Arachne\"&gt;Arachne&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Do you think Arachne's going to be all right in all of this, my lord? The surface was no longer welcoming, or safe, for her. And now, I fear that Erebus is not much better off...\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Mmrrrnnnggghhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You're right. She's twice as resourceful as just about anybody. \"Four \"times! Just... look out for her, would you?\"\nWith Other Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;.\nBold\n Charon : \n\"\"Mmnnnggghhhhhh...\"\n\"Hecate\"\n\"These shipments shall be very valuable to us. We remain as ever in your debt, Charon. May swift Hermes hasten your voyages across the realms, wherever he may be. And until we meet again, shadows conceal you.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Thank you for the supplies, my lord...!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Moros : \n\"...Nevertheless, I feel as though I ought have been there, Brother. Perhaps I could have protected them as was my charge. To think the Fates themselves may have denied me the attempt. It's discomforting that I may never know.\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Keeehhhh, hraaauuggghhh...!\"\n Moros : \n\"You have every reason to be angry. I'm angry, too. Nonetheless, I'm grateful that our paths have intertwined again. Be safe, Charon.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Moros : \n\"Charon... you, Nemesis, even Hypnos. Who else, Eris? It seems I was one of the last to know of these Crossroads among the children of Nyx. Perhaps I ought have stayed in better contact.\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Mrrnngggghhh, hnnnn...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Come, Lord Charon, your brother is our guest. And even if you did all drift apart, you're here together now. Moving forward.\"\n Moros : \n\"Wait, how did you...? No matter.\"\nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Would you indulge me for a moment, Boatman? If we're to restore the old order around here, I was thinking why not start like this?\"\n Charon : \n\"\"Hhhhrrrrnnnngggghhh...?\"\n\"Charon gives &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Purse\"&gt;Gold Purse&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Wait, are you certain there's no charge for this?\"\n2nd Time.\n Charon : \n\"\"Oooohhhhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Indeed, Lord Charon. May we soon restore the old customs between our families, and bring about a new aeon of prosperity.\"\n3rd Time.\n Charon : \n\"\"Auuggggghhhhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I know you require only Gold, my lord. Nevertheless, I wanted to give you something more! I've always found your commitment to the realm and to your discipline inspiring.\"\n4th Time.\n Charon : \n\"\"Nrrrghhhhh, hauuuugghhhh...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Perseverance is what got us to this point, my lord. May your resolve never waver! Whenever mine does, I take comfort knowing I have such dependable allies.\""}
{"id": "2514", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2514", "title": "Charon/Relationships", "text": " \nFamily.\nNyx.\n&lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's mother&lt;br&gt;Nyx and her son seem to have a positive relationship. He is always there, carrying out various tasks for Nyx, including his regular duties of rowing and ferrying tormented souls across the River Styx, or even engaging in combat against wrongdoers when necessary.\nNyx was surprised when Charon broke his work commitment to help &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Persephone\"&gt;Persephone&lt;/a&gt;, even though such behavior isn't typical of Charon, he was still approved by her. Nyx commends Charon for his unwavering dedication to his responsibilities, considering him a reliable and helpful member of the House. She also understands her son, the enigmatic figure whom few can decipher what he's thinking, although this is not unusual for a mother.\nThanatos.\n&lt;a href=\"Thanatos\"&gt;Thanatos&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's younger brother&lt;br&gt;Thanatos fears and admires his brother for his good work. He tells Zagreus that Charon was already present in the Underworld before Hades, and admits that despite his role of simply being the ferryman, the entire Underworld would stop functioning without him. They don't seem to understand each other, but when using &lt;a href=\"Companion%20Mort\"&gt;Companion Mort&lt;/a&gt; against Charon will illicit an enthusiastic \"Hail, Brother!\" from Thanatos. Thanatos will occasionally imitate Charon's \"Hraaaagh!\" in battle, suggesting the two have more in common than either one lets on. Further supporting this is the fact both have wielded &lt;a href=\"Moonstone%20Axe\"&gt;Zorephet&lt;/a&gt;, possibly passed down from Charon to Thanatos.\nHypnos.\n&lt;a href=\"Hypnos\"&gt;Hypnos&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's younger brother&lt;br&gt;One of Charon's little brothers, Hypnos respects and admires his brother. Unlike many of their other siblings who refer to him in a mostly professional manner with little mention of their familial relationship, Hypnos uses more affectionate terms, and Charon doesn't seem to mind, so he must like it. Charon doesn't seem to pay much attention to Hypnos, but Hypnos knows that Charon always takes care of them despite being busy with his constant responsibilities.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;' takeover of the underworld, Charon remarks to &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; that he is of more use asleep than awake, seemingly urging her not to pursue awaking him any time soon. It's unclear if this refers to some unknown effort against Chronos that Hypnos is able to put in only when asleep, or if Charon is joking at his brother's expense.\nNemesis.\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's younger sister\nCharon and his younger sister are not close, though Nemesis respects Charon's dislike of talking and will provide him with gold in exchange for wares.\nMoros.\n&lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's younger brother&lt;br&gt;Moros expresses surprise upon discovering Melino\u00eb can understand Charon perfectly, pointing out it isn't easy to understand him, even among their family.\nEris.\n&lt;a href=\"Eris\"&gt;Eris&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's younger sister.&lt;br&gt;\nThe Fates.\n&lt;a href=\"Fates\"&gt;The Fates&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's sisters.&lt;br&gt;\nChaos.\n&lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's grandparent.&lt;br&gt;\nHouse of Hades.\nZagreus.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's colleague.&lt;br&gt;Initially, Charon will prevent Zagreus from leaving and may even engage in a physical fight to stop him. He won't like it if Zagreus tries to trick him. He later helps Zagreus in exchange for Obol, and is involved in his escape attempts much more heavily than most other characters in the story.\nMelino\u00eb.\n&lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;: Princess of the Underworld.&lt;br&gt;Charon was a key figure in her childhood, to the point where she came to fully understand him, a task pointed out to be difficult. He aids her in her task, pulling shops on her way and sending cargo to &lt;a href=\"the%20Crossroads\"&gt;the Crossroads&lt;/a&gt;.\nHades.\n&lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's boss.&lt;br&gt;Charon is one of the most loyal employees of the House. Charon has been present in the underworld long before Hades arrived, faithfully carrying out his duties. His role is of paramount importance, and the underworld would be in chaos without him. Both Charon and Hades acknowledge this fact. While Zagreus recognizes Charon's strength and his potential to challenge his father, Charon remains unwaveringly loyal to Hades in this role. Consequently, Hades doesn't take Charon lightly and knows how to show him the respect he deserves. Charon's role as a shopkeeper and collector ensures that he continues to earn money, so Charon maintains good terms with his employer, as Hades wants to keep him and wouldn't dare to confront or dismiss him.\nMegaera.\n&lt;a href=\"Megaera\"&gt;Megaera&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's colleague.&lt;br&gt;Although she doesn't even want to get close to him, Charon was seen taking Megaera, Thanatos, and Zagreus on a casual boat ride for fishing, which was very nice of him.\nSkelly.\n&lt;a href=\"Skelly\"&gt;Skelly&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's colleague.&lt;br&gt;Charon is Skelly's employer, Skelly is very eager to work for him.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;, he instructs Melino\u00eb to behave when Charon visits the Crossroads, demonstrating he heavily respects him and doesn't want to get on his bad side.\nDusa.\n&lt;a href=\"Dusa\"&gt;Dusa&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's colleague.&lt;br&gt;Although she finds Charon scary, they come up with a plan to reunite a certain mother and son.\nPersephone.\n&lt;a href=\"Persephone\"&gt;Persephone&lt;/a&gt;: Charon's queen.&lt;br&gt;A kinder side of Charon can be seen when he secretly helps Persephone herself to enter and exit the Underworld, crossing the River Styx. Previously, he also recruited Skelly and Hermes to help Zagreus and Persephone reunite in secret.\nOlympian Gods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Olympians\"&gt;Olympians&lt;/a&gt; don't like Charon, not even &lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt; who speaks so highly of other &lt;a href=\"Chthonic%20Deities\"&gt;Chthonic gods&lt;/a&gt;. Whenever Zagreus purchases a boon of them from Charon's shop, they'll often speak their opinion of him and it's never a positive one. Hermes is the only exception to this behaviour.\nIn Hades II, some have changed their views on him, but most still remain skeptical in having to resort to him.\nHermes.\n&lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;: Fellow psychopomp and bestie.&lt;br&gt;Pals Psychopomp and longtime friends, Charon and Hermes possess a remarkable bond despite their contrasting personalities. Charon exudes an aura of chill and reserve, even among the denizens of the underworld, while Hermes, responsible for guiding souls to the River Styx, stands as a stark contrast with his lively and talkative nature.\nDespite their differences, Charon seems to genuinely enjoy Hermes's company, displaying an unexpected warmth in their interactions. While Charon typically remains reticent, Hermes's animated chatter doesn't seem to faze him, in stark contrast to other characters. Their camaraderie is further accentuated by Hermes's admiration for Charon, as he speaks highly of him to others.\nTheir bond is strengthened by their roles: Hermes, the god of merchants and traders, naturally gravitates towards Charon, the game's primary merchant. This alignment reinforces their connection, as Charon's pivotal role in the underworld's economy aligns perfectly with Hermes's domain.\nDuring the second game, their relationship has deepen, as many characters spend the beginning assuring Charon that Hermes is alright and will return from his mission. Upon Hermes' return, he mentions the first thing he did was go to Charon. Melino\u00eb is also tasked with sending a quick \"Hey\" in their stead to each other every now and then.\nFuthermore, they operate in similar ways, controlling the &lt;a href=\"Well%20of%20Charon\"&gt;Wells of Charon&lt;/a&gt; and Shrines of Hermes, similar by nature. Hermes may also drop an Olympian boon to Melino\u00eb if she pays for it as if it were a package, which is similar to Charon's visit to the Crossroads.\nAphrodite.\n&lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;: Admirer.&lt;br&gt;Aphrodite has a secret crush on him, which unfortunately appears to be one-sided. She mentions how she finds that Ferryman; he's such a solitary soul. Robust... tall... with a powerful build. Hmm. As Melino\u00eb truly understands Charon, she asks Melino\u00eb to send messages to him, which probably won't be reciprocated. When Melino\u00eb questions Aphrodite, she says that everyone has fantasies."}
