{"id": "2884", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2884", "title": "Chellen", "text": "Chellen is &lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;'s tortoise companion. She can be spotted inside his satchel most times, but also watches over the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20Hermes\"&gt;Shrines of Hermes&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; can come across while on the surface.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nNot much is known about Chellen since she's a tortoise and Hermes barely speaks of her. However, she could barely be spotted inside Hermes's satchel in &lt;a href=\"Hades%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;, either because of how packed it was or because she's shy. During &lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;, she's more visible, having the bag all for herself, and she appears happy.\nShe can be spotted under Hermes's scarf when he is met personally, and she also watches over the Shrines of Hermes on the surface, demonstrating trust in her caretaker and as much a sense of duty as him.\nHermes believes it's wise to have an animal companion by your side! He has a soft spot for quiet, self-sufficient types. According to Hermes, she feels at home wherever they go.\nPhysical Description.\nChellen is a green tortoise with a shiny shell. When standing, she stops just about Hermes's kneecaps. When found at a shrine, she's hidden in her shell save for her head.\nFrom one game to another, she appears to have grown."}
{"id": "3113", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3113", "title": "Children of Nyx", "text": "The Children of Nyx are the sons and daughters of the &lt;a href=\"Primordials\"&gt;Primordial&lt;/a&gt; Goddess of the Night, &lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;. Like their mother, they embody an abstract concept as their domains like Death, Sleep, Retribution, etc. and are described as being primordial forces of which the world itself could barely even be imagined without."}
