{"id": "2783", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2783", "title": "Circe", "text": "Circe is an enchantress and daughter of &lt;a href=\"Helios\"&gt;Helios&lt;/a&gt; renowned for her vast knowledge of potions, herbs and for transforming her enemies, or those who offend her, into animals. During &lt;a href=\"Odysseus\"&gt;Odysseus&lt;/a&gt;' journey, he encountered Circe on her island of Aeaea where Circe transformed his crew into swine. Odysseus was able to convice her to change his crew back into men and lived with her for a year. The two ended up having a brief affair during Odysseus' stay that ended when he left to continue on his journey back home.\nCirce appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\" and offers her Changes &amp; Fortunes to &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; in her fight against &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;. She can be encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Rift%20of%20Thessaly\"&gt;Rift of Thessaly&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nCirce acts as a sort of a godmother to Melino\u00eb, while imparting her knowledge of ancient magic as an additional aid in battles. She behaves like an aunt, being talkative and displaying great familiarity, despite Melino\u00eb not having seen her since infancy, affectionately referring to her as Molly. She mentions that Hecate was akin to a mother to her and seems to regard her as a model witch, thus she diligently watches over Melino\u00eb.\nShe consistently maintains a cheerful demeanor and can often be observed happily reciting the ingredients for her next dubious transfiguration potion. Furthermore, she exhibits considerable hypocrisy, particularly concerning her niece Medea, fearing the possibility of her adopting bad habits, despite not being the best influence herself. Nonetheless, she genuinely cares for her.\nPhysical description.\nCirce is depicted as a voluptuous woman. Her eyes gleam with a bright golden hue, similar to her &lt;a href=\"Titan\"&gt;Titan&lt;/a&gt; aunt &lt;a href=\"Selene\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt; and her father Helios. She has full, reddish-tinged hair adorned with cat ears and a garland.\nShe wears a sand-colored dress decorated with moons and its topped by cheetah skin, held in place with a golden belt. Her armbands are also made of cheetah skin. The front depicts silk below decorated with a similar symbol as the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Sisters\"&gt;Silver Sisters&lt;/a&gt;', but in gold instead of silver on top of it. She wears other golden jewelry, like her choker, bracelets and earrings. She's seen with crystals, feathers and other items on her belt. Her wand is in her right hand and she uses it to levitate some crystals. She also has a tail, or some fur to give that effect, behind her.\nHades II.\nCirce is encountered by Melino\u00eb in the Rift of Thessaly on her island of Aeaea. She explains that she was sent by &lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt; to monitor the situation near &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Olympus\"&gt;Mount Olympus&lt;/a&gt;. Circe will then provide her Fortunes to Melino\u00eb whenever she visits Aeaea.\nAffinity.\nIf given &lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;, Circe will give you the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Figurine\"&gt;Crystal Figurine&lt;/a&gt;.\nGallery.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nConcept=\nIllustration=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;&lt;noinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "4251", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4251", "title": "Circe/Fortunes of Circe", "text": ""}
{"id": "2785", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2785", "title": "Circe/Quotes", "text": "The following are quotes from &lt;a href=\"Circe\"&gt;Circe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nFirst Meeting.\n Circe : \"\"Oh\", well, isn't this marvelous! How you've \"grown\", little miss! Do you remember Circe the Enchantress still? \"Ah? \"Oh, no matter, \"hahaha. \"Not the circumstances for small talk! Show me your palms.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \"Of course I remember you, Madame Circe! So this is your famous island! Such a relief to be here rather than another drowned ship. I take it we're not meeting by chance?\"\n Circe : \"Wise to our ways as ever! Our Lady Hecate and I decided I had best relocate for a while, and survey events as near the mountain of the gods as possible. Then tonight within my crystals, I saw \"you! \"Now, how may we make you better?\"\nBasic Narrative Dialogue.\nChanting (Beginnings).\n\"\"Fang and feather, tuft of wool, &lt;br&gt; \"Dusky wing and horn of bull,\" \n\"\"Little seeds and bigger fronds, &lt;br&gt; \"Stones from rivers, moss from ponds,\"\n\"\"Bubble, tea leaves, ocean breeze, &lt;br&gt; \"Briar thorns, and wax of bees,\"\n\"\"Gust of wind, and spray of sea, &lt;br&gt; \"Clump of soil, branch of tree,\"\n\"\"Apple pieces, olives, figs, &lt;br&gt; \"Ginger roots and cypress twigs,\"\n\"\"Lichen, garlic, bark of pine, &lt;br&gt; \"Dash of oil, drop of wine,\"\n\"\"Cap of mushroom, skin of snake, &lt;br&gt; \"Lemon juice and sand of lake,\"\n\"\"Coiled vine and peat of fens, &lt;br&gt; \"Sugar beets and egg of hens,\"\n\"\"Onyx crystal, Python scale, &lt;br&gt; \"Morning dew, and fingernail,\"\n\"\"Silk of spider, tooth of shark, &lt;br&gt; \"Ray of light, and mote of dark,\"\n\"\"Heap of soil, chip of stone, &lt;br&gt; \"Harpy feather, knuckle bone,\"\n\"\"Cotton-plant and shard of flint, &lt;br&gt; \"Cherry pit and sprig of mint,\"\nChanting (Ends).\n\"\"Bit of toadstool, claw of cat, &lt;br&gt; \"Heat it, stir it, that is that!\"\n\"\"Hoof of pig, and fur of hound, &lt;br&gt; \"Brew a potion, safe and sound!\"\n\"\"Moly petals, I've a lot! &lt;br&gt; \"Boil, simmer, in my pot!\"*\n\"\"Bask in Moonlight, all of you, &lt;br&gt; \"Till you be this witch's brew!\"\nKeepsake Dialogue (&lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Figurine\"&gt;Crystal Figurine&lt;/a&gt;).\nTBA\nReactions.\nTBA\nAbouth the Scenery.\nCirce's Hut.\n\"Welcome, poppet! Though forgive me that I've not invited you \"inside \"my little hut. Such hospitality I don't extend to anyone, \"hmhm! \"And I make no exceptions, not even for you!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Madame Circe, that is perfectly all right, and there's no need to explain. We all live in seclusion in our own way. What other way is there? With privacy comes peace of mind.\" \n Circe : \n\"I'm grateful that you understand. Of late, I share my simple home with beasts but that is all! This Isle of Aiaia is not mine of course; rather, it's my dear companion, and can be \"yours. \"So please, help yourself to anything you need whilst here.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Rift%20of%20Thessaly\"&gt;Rift of Thessaly&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"\"Fie \"on that never-ending fleet of ghastly sailing-ships, all headed for the mountain of the gods, \"hah! \"My little isle sometimes gets \"right \"in the way! No hospitality awaits their boorish crews, \"ahaha! \"Whilst \"I \"replenish my supply of firewood.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You must long for the days when your island was more secluded, and had much less unwanted company. I hope I'm not disturbing your peace, Madame!\"\n Circe : \n\"\"Oh\", heavens \"no! \"In actuality, it could be rather all too quiet with only the rustle of the vegetation, and the snuffle of my piggies, and the like. I more than welcome your returns!\"\nMiscellaneous Conversations.\nAbout Backstory.\n Circe : \n\"You and I are much alike in that our Lady Hecate discovered us when most we needed someone such as her, poppet. Perchance, her similar affinity for beasts made her take some pity on me then... a witch, amongst the polecats and the pigs!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Take pity on you, how? That doesn't sound like the Headmistress I know. She has always thought highly of you, and depends on you to be our eyes here at this key juncture.\"\n Circe : \n\"I owe her this, and more. When I was a young outcast, practicing an art oft thought to be profane, it was our Lady who discovered me and showed me that my path led not to ruin, but to harmony. It veritably is a long and winding path, but one I shall not stray from anymore.\"\nAbout Miracles.\n Circe : \n\"I foresaw within the facets of my crystals that you were headed here again... or \"through \"here, I should say. Is there a salve, potion, or poultice that might ease your passage?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Most certainly, and thank you, Madame Circe. I don't suppose you have anything that renders me invulnerable, or lets me find vast quantities of rare reagents on my way?\"\n Circe : \n\"Heavens \"no\", poppet, \"hah! \"The greater the effect, the greater the unintended consequence, that much we know is true. \"Erm\", there is a \"balance \"to creating miracles! Shall one of these suffice?\"\nAbout Studies.\n Circe : \n\"How you were \"always \"at your studies, little miss! That you are here suggests how much you have achieved. I always wanted you to visit me; you used to say it was \"impossible!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It turns out even prophecies of the Three Fates are circumventable. Though, I still have much to learn... or so I keep reminding myself night after night. How about you? You must have perfect mastery over our craft by now!\"\n Circe : \n\"Now it's \"my \"turn to say something \"is \"impossible! I've been practicing enchantment for three quarters of my life, and have yet to ever change the essence of a thing! Only the \"form. \"But the pursuit I find is fascinating without end!\"\nAbout &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Cards\"&gt;Arcana&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"Our Lady Hecate would sometimes tell me of your progress, and let on that you attuned to the Altar of Ashes at long last, \"hoho! \"How marvelous... for the Arcana have so much to offer us.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I couldn't agree more. Through grasping the Arcana, I've discovered strength I never realized I had. To think I used to use our Altar merely to collect my thoughts.\"\n Circe : \n\"Collecting one's thoughts is valuable enough! Mine own at least are prone to scattering. As for your innate strength and magickal acuity, perchance we shall discover even more.\"\nAbout Family.\n Circe : \n\"I oft forget, we share some kinship, do we not? My father is the shining Sun itself, the Titan Helios. Distant accomplice to the gods! Not close with anyone. But he is... brother to the Lady Demeter, my aunt, who is your grandmother, correct...?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Oh Madame Circe, right you are! That makes us cousins once removed, I think. I don't know how any of us can keep all this genealogy straight! In any case, the bond matters more than the blood, does it not?\"\n Circe : \n\"Quite veritably so! Though, you'll forgive me that I've shied from all of it. Amongst family, I was expected to act differently with each and every one. I scarcely understood how to be \"me! \"Things are much simpler on this isle here.\"\nAbout &lt;a href=\"Moly\"&gt;Moly&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"Something felt \"different\", just as you arrived. It's \"Moly\", isn't it? And quite a \"lot\", as I perceive! You need no such protection in this place. A miracle it does not interfere with your own craft!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I have been gathering what Moly I can find in Erebus. It has its uses to be sure, though in my purse it doesn't bother me, and remains fresh. You have an aversion to it? And here I thought that every plant and herb had earned your love.\"\n Circe : \n\"Some earn my caution sooner than my love! Moly has a \"stifling \"effect I care for not at all! So much so, that I have learned to negate it. As you have no need of its powers here, it shall do neither of us any harm! Though, do be careful, little miss.\"\nAbout Crystals.\n Circe : \n\"\"Ah-ha\", I knew you would arrive just now, poppet, \"haha! \"No innate gift of foresight required, merely intuition and my crystals hereabouts. Have you incorporated any into \"your \"routine?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Well... I've learned to see into our &lt;a href=\"https%3A//hades.fandom.com/wiki/The_Crossroads/Training_Grounds%23The_Pitch-Black_Stone%3A~%3Atext%3Dbetween%2520the%2520gateways.-%2CThe%2520Pitch%252DBlack%2520Stone%2C-The%2520Pitch%252DBlack\"&gt;Pitch-Black Stone&lt;/a&gt;! I used to think that it was there to help make us unseen, but it has other potent uses, too. Crystals! So full of potential.\"\n Circe : \n\"Mother Gaia's multicolored bounty, \"oh! \"I sometimes envy that you live beneath the Earth where crystals and gemstones grow in abundance! Each has its special properties suggested by a single touch, \"oh-hohoh! \"How brilliant they all are!\"\nAbout the &lt;a href=\"Witch%27s%20Staff\"&gt;Aspect of Circe&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"How fares my \"marvelous \"Descura, little miss? I knew that you were next in line for her, though I still feel a bit emotional to see my favored staff again, \"hohoho. \"Our Lady Hecate had to do more than a \"bit \"of prodding to make me give her up, \"hehehoho!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I've done my best to wield Descura with respect; to live up to those who possessed the Witch's Staff before me. And it... or rather she has served me well. My presence here is evidence to that. Do you... wish to hold her again?\"\n Circe : \n\"Oh, no, I mustn't! We had our time. Long had she grown heavy in my hands before I passed her on, besides. May she protect you just as fiercely as I know she can!\"\nAbout Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"How lately is the temperament of our Lady Hecate? Long has it been since last I basked in her wisdom; for I have wisdom of my own, she says! You must have needed her attention more than I...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Madame Circe, I... I did not mean to deny you her attention. Although Headmistress has been preoccupied not just with my training, but with leading the Unseen, warding the Crossroads against any harm, readying our plans to take back what's ours. She's counting on us... on you.\"\n Circe : \n\"I know, I know... and I apologize that I insinuated any feelings of resentment on my part; for none exist towards you, let alone her! You have my \"word\", poppet. It's just... she was like a mother to me! \"Oh\", how she hated when I told her so, \"haha!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Selene\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"You've one of great Selene's precious blessings on this eve, that I can tell, poppet! Even from afar, the Moon has always kept me company. Her light can be so \"utterly \"transformative!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"And may Selene's light ever shine for us, Madame. I'd likely not have found my way to you if not for her. As for her magick... sometimes I wonder if it isn't transforming me, so much as revealing who I really am.\"\n Circe : \n\"That may well be so! Who is to say where our true nature lies? A spell of transformation is a spell of revelation; when we change, we become more like \"ourselves\". Not less!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Medea\"&gt;Medea&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"I have seen neither hide nor hair of that Medea as of late! Her charge was far less pleasant than my own, having to watch over that ghastly town. I worry she's developing bad habits, practicing in such a place!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I've seen Lady Medea recently. She seems rather comfortable in Ephyra, in spite of what's happened there. Though, has she always had such a singular interest in curses and the necromantic arts?\"\n Circe : \n\"Since she was old enough to think for herself, yes, \"heh\". To \"fend \"for herself, I should say. She may be my niece yet she was always \"far \"more interested in our blood's \"other \"properties. At least she hasn't put a curse on \"me, haha. Ah! \"As far as I can tell!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Odysseus\"&gt;Odysseus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"I wonder, does our Lady Hecate as yet consort with that Tactician Shade of hers, \"heh? \"Swarthy in his mortal days, not of surpassing stature, prone to talk. \"Oh\", what was his name again?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You mean Odysseus? He remains indispensable to our cause. What knowledge I possess of this route and the dangers along it are thanks largely to him. Why do you ask?\"\n Circe : \n\"\"Oh! \"No reason at all! It's merely that he was a flighty sort as I recall, quite prone to wandering about! So his continued service is a bit of a surprise. A pleasant one, mind you!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Did you use to know him? I don't recall you interacting at the Crossroads. Not that I was paying much heed to anything besides my studies then. I was so little last you visited!\"\n Circe : \n\"Once I relocated this isle, the journey to the Crossroads became \"much \"more arduous. As for Odysseus, yes, him I have met before. Him and his pig-headed crew. A different age, poppet! Perchance he's learned a bit since then.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Scylla\"&gt;Scylla&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"All of this sea-water must feel very disconcerting, little miss. For me, though, it feels rather much like home! Even the depths of Oceanus bring a sense of comfort, more than fear!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I'm getting used to it. My path into the Underworld requires me to skirt the edge of Oceanus. The water's beautiful, though I could do without the sea-monsters. Particularly Scylla and her Siren friends... perhaps you know of them?\"\n Circe : \n\"Oh, \"yes! \"I do indeed. I grew up underneath the sea, and Scylla I remember from my youth. Always yelping about \"this \"or \"that! \"Was \"deafening! \"Perchance why I prefer the silence now.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;.\n Circe : \n\"What has the world come to, little miss? \"Uh! \"Living on my little isle, I must have been the last to learn calamity had spread all from the heavens to beneath the earth!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"And Chronos is responsible for all of it. \"Time \"apparently wishes to ruin everything eventually, though we are not about to let him have his way. We'll drive his forces from Olympus and unseat him from my father's throne.\"\n Circe : \n\"\"Oh\", we immortals and our warring ways! What example do we set for \"mortalkind? \"But I know certain battles must be fought; and I remain committed to our Lady Hecate, and you.\"\nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Madame Circe, I'm grateful that we had a chance to meet again after all this time. Your kindness to me always meant a lot, and I wanted to give you this small token in return.\"\n Circe : \n\"\"Nectar! Ohh, thank you\", little miss! I've made attempts to brew my own but never get it right! Though why don't you take \"this \"in kind? Think of it as a little island souvenir!\"\n\"Circe gives &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Crystal%20Figurine\"&gt;Crystal Figurine&lt;/a&gt;.'\n Melino\u00eb : \"It's beautiful, and quite adorable! Thank you!\"\n2nd Time.\n Circe : \n\"Good heavens! More, for \"me? \"I'm unaccustomed to receiving gifts here on my little isle. Though I'm pleased to try and get more used to it, \"ahaha! \"If you must so \"insist!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"Insist \"is a strong word, Madame, but I would like for you to have this, yes. Perhaps it will help you perfect your own recipe... or while away a pleasant night, should one arise.\""}
{"id": "2788", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2788", "title": "Circe/Relationships", "text": "Family.\nSelene.\n&lt;a href=\"Selene\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt;: Circe's aunt.&lt;br&gt;Circe comments that even if the Moon's light is far away, it always keeps her company.\nMedea.\n&lt;a href=\"Medea\"&gt;Medea&lt;/a&gt;: Circe's niece.&lt;br&gt;Despite being blood-related and fellow witches, Circe and her niece Medea are not on the best of terms. Circe worries that Medea's stay in the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Ephyra\"&gt;City of Ephyra&lt;/a&gt; has caused her to develop bad habits, such as an unhealthy interest in their family blood's \"other\" properties.\nThe Unseen.\nHecate.\n&lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;: Witch of the Crossroads.&lt;br&gt;It was Hecate that taught Circe witchcraft, taken the then young witch under her wing. Circe says their relationship is almost akin to that of a mother and child. Now, Circe watches over the &lt;a href=\"Rift%20of%20Thessaly\"&gt;Rift of Thessaly&lt;/a&gt; as per Hecate's orders, though she may occasionally visit the Crossroads still.\nMelino\u00eb.\n&lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;: Princess of the Underworld.&lt;br&gt;Circe was present in Melino\u00eb's childhood, and notes how the princess was constantly studying. Even to this day, Melino\u00eb greatly admires Circe's powers, and gladly receives one of her spells when they meet during a night. She affectionately calls the princess \"poppet\".\nOdysseus.\n&lt;a href=\"Odysseus\"&gt;Odysseus&lt;/a&gt;: Veteran Tactician.&lt;br&gt;Circe and Odysseus have a past together, as she was one of the women he crossed paths with during his journey back home, and also with whom he cheated on &lt;a href=\"Penelope\"&gt;his wife&lt;/a&gt;. They've since grown apart, with Odysseus wanting nothing more to do with Circe, going as far as not read her reports and instead sending them directly to Hecate. Circe does not seem to miss him in the slightest; in fact, she hopes he has changed since the last time they were together, back when he was alive.\nOthers.\nScylla.\n&lt;a href=\"Scylla\"&gt;Scylla&lt;/a&gt;: Scourge of the Seas.&lt;br&gt;Scylla was a figure of Circe's youth, though they didn't have the best of relationships, as Circe comments Scylla would always be yapping about and it's why the witch much prefers the silence now. It's also implied that it was Circe that transformed Scylla in the sea-monster she is today."}
{"id": "2856", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2856", "title": "City of Ephyra", "text": "The City of Ephyra is a surface biome, capital of Thesprotia that worshiped &lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Persephone\"&gt;Persephone&lt;/a&gt;. The City was attacked by the armies of &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt; and most of the inhabitants were killed. The City of Ephyra is the first surface biome &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; must fight through to reach &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Olympus\"&gt;Mount Olympus&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe following biome is the &lt;a href=\"Rift%20of%20Thessaly\"&gt;Rift of Thessaly&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nRather than being a gauntlet of rooms with optional diverging paths, The City of Ephyra is instead a central hub with many rooms to chose from. At the center lies a fountain that will restore HP once, and an exit guarded by a barrier kept by six Pylons powered by Shades trapped within the several \"rooms\" of Ephyra. \nAround the fountain several doorways are available, inside there will be a single room with a Pylon corresponding to the ones guarding the exit for Melino\u00eb to break and free the shades, further weakening the barrier. Some rooms will offer extra, optional rooms to get more resources. \nOnce all Pylons protecting the exit are broken, any unvisited path will be permanently closed. Past the exit lies one of Charon's shops and the path to the boss fight with &lt;a href=\"Polyphemus\"&gt;Polyphemus&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll-Seeing Bats.\nThrough the &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Cauldron&lt;/a&gt;, Melino\u00eb can unlock cages with bats spread across Ephyra to give her a \"bird's eye\" view of the city, marking all the rooms she can enter and what rewards they offer.\nEnemy Encounters.\nThese are all the enemies that can be encountered in any other City of Ephyra chamber. These enemies can also appear as Elites, giving them armor and upgraded attacks."}
