{"id": "1042", "revid": "55184635", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1042", "title": "Crawler", "text": "Crawlers are small vermin which inhabit the chambers beneath the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Styx\"&gt;Temple of Styx&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen one spots &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;, a crawler will move very quickly towards him, and upon reaching him, will instantly attack with a close ranged melee hit.\nCrawlers have a fast attack animation, meaning while they inflict small amounts of damage, they can attack in quick succession, dealing high damage if left unchecked.\nAdditionally, Crawlers spawn in very large packs, and Zagreus can be attacked by multiple Crawlers at the same time."}
{"id": "4370", "revid": "54583845", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4370", "title": "Crawler/Hades II", "text": "Crawlers are small vermin minions summoned by &lt;a href=\"Satyr%20Vierophant\"&gt;Satyr Vierophants&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Verminancer\"&gt;The Verminancer&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Tartarus/Hades%20II\"&gt;Tartarus&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt; overthrew &lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Lord Hades&lt;/a&gt;, the Satyrs moved from the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Styx\"&gt;Temple of Styx&lt;/a&gt; to the deepest regions of the Underworld to serve the Titan of Time. They brought the rat infestation with them, and these Crawlers now nest in large numbers inside the robes of their Satyr masters.\nCrawlers will dart around at high speeds; look for the sunburst indicators (these appear around their hitbox) to determine where they are. They are fragile and deal only a small amount of damage, but can become a hassle if several groups are allowed to spawn at once.\nA red summoning circle will appear at the feet of &lt;a href=\"Satyr%20Vierophant\"&gt;Satyr Vierophants&lt;/a&gt; shortly before 2-3 Crawlers appear. Their summoning can be interrupted if the Satyr channeling the spell is staggered or defeated quickly enough."}
{"id": "3858", "revid": "45030189", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3858", "title": "Crescent Pick", "text": "The Crescent Pick is one of four &lt;a href=\"Gathering%20Tools\"&gt;Gathering Tools&lt;/a&gt; Melino\u00eb can access from the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//hades.fandom.com/wiki/The_Crossroads/Training_Grounds%23The_Silver_Pool%3A~%3Atext%3DThe-%2CSilver%2520Pool%2C-is%2520an%2520area\"&gt;Silver Pool&lt;/a&gt;. It is used to mine Outcroppings both in the Underworld and on the Surface. \nAs with all &lt;a href=\"Gathering%20Tools\"&gt;Gathering Tools&lt;/a&gt;, the Crescent Pick becomes available after completing the Night's Craftwork incantation at Hecate's &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Cauldron&lt;/a&gt;. As of Early Access, the Pick can be upgraded once, to Rank II.\nMaterials gathered with the Crescent Pick are most commonly used to unlock and upgrade the &lt;a href=\"Nocturnal%20Arms\"&gt;Nocturnal Arms&lt;/a&gt;, but have uses for certain &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Incantations&lt;/a&gt; and some &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Cards\"&gt;Arcana Cards&lt;/a&gt; as well.\nGatherable Items.\nThe Crescent Pick can gather the following materials:\nEach node will produce 3 of its material before it is exhausted."}
