{"id": "1672", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1672", "title": "Dionysus/Quotes (Hades)", "text": "\"The following are quotes from &lt;a href=\"Dionysus\"&gt;Dionysus&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Hades%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;\".\nFirst Meeting.\n Zagreus: \n\"That was... revelry? People having a good time? Well, sure, then! In the name of Hades! Olympus, I'll accept this message.\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Heeey, there, Zag, man, how's it going? Look, you have got to get here with the rest of us already, we've been saving you a spot! Let me see what I can do, make life a little sweeter for you in the meantime!\" \nKeepsake Dialogue (&lt;a href=\"Overflowing%20Cup\"&gt;Overflowing Cup&lt;/a&gt;).\nKeepsake Equipped.\n Dionysus: \n\"Say, isn't that the Overflowing Cup I handed down to you, I'm glad you like it, man! I guess it's overflowing still, because I figure otherwise I couldn't tell at all!\" \nReactions.\nSeeing &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; at Low Health.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Whoaa Zag, man, you look positively knackered, you be sure and take it easy if you can out there, all right? Here, maybe this'll help!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Oof\", Zag, look, I know you're not in a good spot right now, you must be really out of sorts! Though maybe \"this \"might numb the pain a bit!\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Eugh\", you're a proper mess right now, got to be candid with you, man, you're bleeding everywhere, get it together, yeah?\" \nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"Now what's the matter, down there, Zag, it's like you've been up feasting day and night, you're barely standing, everything OK?\" \nDialogue 05.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Ooh\", you're in no shape to be going off, what happened to you, there? Well, here, you know what? Let me see if we can get you back into it, man!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; (First Choice).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey cheers man!\"\nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"What, for me, Zag, wow...!\"\nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey now that is something, yeah!\"\nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"I can't say no to that!\"\nDialogue 05.\n Dionysus: \n\"I owe you one man!\"\nDialogue 06.\n Dionysus: \n\"Cheers, I'll take it man!\"\nDialogue 07.\n Dionysus: \n\"Oh yeah I dig it man!\"\nDialogue 08.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hahaha, don't you know it, man!\"\nDialogue 09.\n Dionysus: \n\"Oh we are going to have a feast tonight!\"\nDialogue 10.\n Dionysus: \n\"Ooh you're in a real heap of trouble, Zag!\"\nDialogue 11.\n Dionysus: \n\"Yeaaah, man, you know what it's all about!\"\nDialogue 12.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hah, cheers to you, then, man!\"\nDialogue 13.\n Dionysus: \n\"That definitely was a good decision, man!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; (Rejection).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Oh, come \"on\", Zag, and here I thought that we were cool. You hurt my pride, there, man. I guess I'm going to have to hurt yours...\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Ohhh man, that was definitely not a thing to do, I mean, are we best mates, or not...? You think on that, while I do \"this\".\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"Look Zag, I'm not going to lie, you hurt my feelings here, I thought we had a thing! A close familial bond! I'm really \"mad \"now that I think on it!\"\nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"What, you wouldn't hang with me given the choice? I thought I had you sorted, man, but maybe you just don't appreciate the finer things!\" \nDialogue 05.\n Dionysus: \n\"Ah, come on, Zag, now that was not the choice I would have made, you messing with me, man? All right! I'll mess with \"you\".\" \nDialogue 06.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Ohh\", we all make mistakes from time to time, man, and you ought to know! You made one there just now!\" \nDialogue 07.\n Dionysus: \n\"Why do it to me like that, Zag, man, I thought we were close as grapes upon the vine, but I was wrong?\" \nDialogue 08.\n Dionysus: \n\"Did I do something to deserve this, man, because I thought that we were getting on just fine, better than fine, but this?\" \nDialogue 09.\n Dionysus: \n\"It's not that I'm upset or anything, here, Zag, you know I'm not, but truthfully I am a bit annoyed, a little bit, and so, I got to send the message, man.\" \nDialogue 10.\n Dionysus: \n\"Really, man? After everything we've been through together, \"this \"is the gratitude I get?\" \nDialogue 11.\n Dionysus: \n\"Well, way to spoil the feast, there, Zag, I mean come on, I thought I was your mate? Was I mistaken, man?\" \nDialogue 12.\n Dionysus: \n\"Zag, I can take a jest, ask anybody, but when it comes to competition here, it's not a laughing matter! Do you understand me, man?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; (Making Up).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"All right, all right, all right, we're cool, we're cool, no need to get all hot and bothered any longer, here!\"\nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"OK, let's say we're settled up now, Zag, and go on being best mates just like before, yeah?\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"You know, Zag, you are not so bad, just had a little lapse in judgment, happens to me all the time, now let's get on with it!\" \nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, now, that was quite a sight, I got to hand it to you, man, and you \"deserve \"this, here!\" \nDialogue 05.\n Dionysus: \n\"Know what, man, I'm not even angry after that. What was I even going off about, do you recall...?\"\nDialogue 06.\n Dionysus: \n\"OK, all right, it's fine already, Zag, you win this time and I am good as grapes.\" \nDialogue 07.\n Dionysus: \n\"Appreciate your understanding, there, man, so let's just avoid this type of little shake-up next time, yeah?\" \nDialogue 08.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Hahahahahah\", OK, thanks for a good laugh, there, Zag, what was it I was going on about, before...?\" \nDialogue 09.\n Dionysus: \n\"Oh I just can't stay mad about you, Zag, and to be honest, why, I wasn't that mad to begin with, I just thought I'd shake your branches up a bit!\" \nDialogue 10.\n Dionysus: \n\"You're all right, man, you're all right, don't even worry about the rough patch we just crossed back there, we're stronger than all that!\" \nDialogue 11.\n Dionysus: \n\"I figured this time I'd stay mad at you for sure, man, but you know what, I just couldn't! No matter how hard I tried.\" \nDialogue 12.\n Dionysus: \n\"Know what, man, just forget about what happened, yeah? 'Cause I already did, I mean, it happens, right?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20the%20Gods\"&gt;Trial of the Gods&lt;/a&gt; (Killing &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"What can I say, man, it's a shame all right.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"I'm absolutely gutted man.\"\nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"Now that's a crying shame.\"\nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"Didn't have to be like this, man! We were having such a good time!\"\nDialogue 05.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hate to sour the occasion like this, Zag. What was I supposed to do?\"\nDialogue 06.\n Dionysus: \n\"Eugh, I feel bad all of a sudden, man, I mean, what happened, there?\"\nGeneric Greetings.\nLong Lines.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Looks like this feast is getting started still, am I not right about that, Zag? Come on, let's show everybody a good time.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Just getting warmed up down there, yeah, Zag? Here, I've a fine selection of my blessings, just for you!\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Whooaa\", Zag, I bet you could use a little pick-me-up right about now, and I am here to offer you whichever one you please!\" \nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey Zag, how is life, you hanging in there, yeah? I reckoned maybe we could raise a glass here, to your health, but then I thought, No, wait! I can do a little more than that! So, here we go!\"\nDialogue 05.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, how you living life down there right now, all right I take it, yeah? No, wait, though, I have just the thing!\" \nDialogue 06.\n Dionysus: \n\"Why, hello, Zag! Fancy running into you, though there's no need to work yourself so hard, you hear me, yeah? I reckon this should take the edge right off!\" \nDialogue 07.\n Dionysus: \n\"How goes it this time, man, everything fine? Though hold that thought, I wager we can make things finer yet!\" \nDialogue 08.\n Dionysus: \n\"That Underworld of yours, place is a real pit, isn't it Zag, a shame you're stuck down there. But we are going to get you out of there, together, you and I!\" \nDialogue 09.\n Dionysus: \n\"Soon as you get up to Olympus, man... it's going to be a feast like you have \"never \"seen, you mark my words! Now take this, and good luck!\" \nDialogue 10.\n Dionysus: \n\"You give those musty shades and corpses a fair fighting chance down there, you hear me, Zag? Though just in case you need a hand...\" \nDialogue 11.\n Dionysus: \n\"You got this, man! I \"so \"believe in you, it's almost like the Greeks believe in me! And they believe in me an awful lot, you know!\" \nDialogue 12.\n Dionysus: \n\"Time for another go at getting out of there, eh, Zag? Well not to worry, we'll make something happen, let's hop to it then!\" \nDialogue 13.\n Dionysus: \n\"Now listen up here, Zag, 'cause this time I have got something for you that's going to put some extra fire in your step, you ready, man?\" \nDialogue 14.\n Dionysus: \n\"You wait for just a moment, Zag, 'cause I got just the thing for this occasion, you are going to love it, get a load of this!\" \nDialogue 15.\n Dionysus: \n\"Now, Zagreus, I'm certain everything is going fine for you right now, but just in case, but \"just in case\"! I got a little something, just for you!\" \nDialogue 16.\n Dionysus: \n\"It's me, Zag, hey, I know you haven't got a lot of time to listen to me prattle on like this, and so, I'm cutting to the chase here, look!\" \nDialogue 17.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey again as ever Zag, now you keep at it like you have been and I bet we'll all be hanging out up here in no time flat! I'm with you \"all \"the way!\" \nDialogue 18.\n Dionysus: \n\"Oh, hey, let's see, man, I am thinking that \"this \"time around this smattering of my concoctions ought to do you right!\" \nImproved Relationship Lines.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Now how's my favorite Underworld god surviving, Zag, you holding up or what? Right better momentarily, I bet!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Man oh man, Zag, someday you will be the guest of honor at the \"biggest \"feast that you have \"ever \"seen! Though I know you have got your hands full for the time, so, first things first!\" \nAbout Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Megaera\"&gt;Megaera&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Erm\", hey, man, you been having some bad run-ins with that Fury, Megaera, is that her name? Now isn't she a real firebrand! Maybe this'll help you out next time you meet!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Whoa, Zag, heard you're hanging with the Fury Megaera of late, well cheers to that, man, bet she's something else, but you just watch for that whip of hers, OK?\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey man, I'm hearing up here that you got in good with Megaera, the Fury, is that right, I mean, I hope it is, because, \"hahaha, yeow\", know what I mean? They say she's something else!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Thanatos\"&gt;Thanatos&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, you're in good with Thanatos, isn't that right? A real broody sort, sometimes I think maybe I ought to just invite him to a feast, but then, what if he cools the whole thing down, makes everybody kind of \"ehhhhh\", you know?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Theseus\"&gt;Theseus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"Heard that you took care of Theseus down in Elysium of late, there, Zag! Nice work, never liked that one, between us. There's this nice lass helped him out one time, and he just dumped her rotten, I don't like that, man!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Orpheus\"&gt;Orpheus&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey Zag, ever see a fellow by the name of Orpheus down there, you ever heard of him? I bet you have, and I have had a funny thought, a little jest that maybe we could try, if you'd be up to have a little harmless fun?\" \n Zagreus: \n\"Harmless fun at the expense of Orpheus? You have my full and complete attention, Dionysus mate.\" \n Dionysus: \n\"...That chap comes up with the most smashing songs, so I was thinking, maybe we could spin him a tall tale, something like how maybe you and I, like, we're connected or something? He'll buy it, tell him, tell him for me, yeah?!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Hahaha\", Zag! I heard you got to Orpheus, he's got this whole entire ballad now, about how you are really me, or maybe it's the other way around, I've no idea, \"hahahaha\"! Here!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"So Zag, you met my dad by now, your uncle Zeus? He's cool and loves a feasting, just... be sure to keep him in your thoughts. OK?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, Zag, got to tell you, I cannot believe that little Artemis is hanging out with you! She doesn't hang with anybody, man! But I digress, take this!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey man, I heard Athena had a word with you already yeah? She's cool, though, once you get to know her. Here! I got something that ought to suit her style.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"You hanging out with Ares, are you, Zag? He's quite the chap, I'll give him that, I'll give him that, and now, I'll give you \"this\"!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Whoa\", hey, you must have had a run-in with the lovely Aphrodite, am I right, or am I right, there Zag? But I have \"just \"the thing to go with her!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Hoh-ho\", no way Zag, looking like you got yourself a gift from old Poseidon there? He's quite the catch, but here, hope you saved some room for more!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dionysus: \n\"Felt a shiver in the air just now, and that can only mean that chilly Demeter decided to give you a little help, there, huh? Or maybe it's just cold, I mean, this is a mountaintop!\" \nWith Other Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey Zag, my Dad, he's here and wants to have a word, be cool man, go along with what he says, OK?\" \n Zeus: \n\"That Dionysus, always much too kind with introductions, though at least he shows me suitable respect. Perhaps someday he can instruct you in the customs of Olympus here.\" \n&lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, Zag, when you arrive, it's going to be a real scene, I'll tell you now! Even Athena here will cut loose for a bit, let down her hair, you know, put on something more comfy, yeah, it's going to be \"great\"!\" \n Athena: \n\"Perhaps Lord Dionysus here is the true god of strategy, as it appears he is uncannily aware of my next move, Cousin. Although, be that as it may, I shall attempt to remain focused on your situation. Not his feast.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Athena: \n\"Some members of our family do not yet fully understand just how precarious your situation is, Cousin. My Lord Dionysus here, he goes about as though this is a festive matter of some sort!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Oh, come on, Athena girl, you really mean to tell me that discovering a long-lost relative isn't a cause for celebrating right away, I mean, you can't be telling me a thing like \"that\"? Because if Zag isn't a cause for feasting, I don't know what is!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Uh\", Zag, \"erm\"... your uncle's passing through. Not Dad, \"erm\", the other one I mean, and he just wanted to check in, see how you're doing, so...\" \n Poseidon: \n\"\"Ah-hah\", there you are, my little nephew! Dionysus showing you the ropes, or what? You want a real feast, though, you just stick with \"me\"! Now take my blessing, \"go\"!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"\"Oh\", anyway we're here, man, waiting up for you! We know you're going to make it, I would say eventually?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"You know, Zag, maybe once you get here, you could get old Ares to just lighten up a little, you know, man? Always dragging down the mood, with talk of blood, and nastiness, all sorts of stuff like that!\" \n Ares: \n\"Why, my Lord Dionysus! I fail to see why such discussion is perceived as unbecoming of a feast. A successfully conducted war is certainly a cause for celebration, is it not?\" \nDialogue 02.\n Ares: \n\"Ah, my kin! I was just inquiring with Lord Dionysus here, under which circumstances are the greatest mortal feasts of all prepared? Because I have a certain hunch, regarding that...\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Yeah, yeah, Ares, I will hand it to you, man. There's nothing like a feast after a war, all right! Provided you're on the surviving side, that is! Otherwise I guess they'll be feasting with \"you \"down there, Zag!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey Zag, got a favor here I mean to ask, could you maybe persuade the Lady Demeter to ease up on the whole \"'not let anything grow' \"thing she's been going on about?\" \n Demeter: \n\"I daresay, my Lord Dionysus, that partaking of less wine for some amount of time might do you good. Regardless, you'll not coax a better crop from me.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Demeter: \n\"The crops shall wither and decay so long as I may please, young Zagreus. Although we do have those upon Olympus who take issue with my reasoning...\" \n Dionysus: \n\"\"Erm\", yeah, milady, I take issue here! I mean how are the grapes supposed to grow and wine supposed to flow when you are so uptight, now, just ease up a little there, let's see what we can do!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Look, Zag, you should know by now that when it comes to feasting, it's Yours Truly here who puts on the best performance. But I do have Lady Aphrodite's help!\" \n Aphrodite: \n\"Wine does have a rather special way of making everybody look even more beautiful than ever, Dionysus dear! And from such beauty, why, long-lasting love is born! And also shorter-lasting love, much of the time.\" \nDialogue 02.\n Aphrodite: \n\"My powers, dearest, oft go hand-in-hand with those of Dionysus, with his power to persuade the mind to find such beauty where it isn't, really!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"\"Ah, haha\", no need to flatter me like that, there, Lady Aphrodite! Beauty's almost entirely within the mind, I'm sure! And in the muscles and the jawline and the winning smile and, well, who am I to tell you, yeah?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt; (Duo Boon).\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Zag, man, I was just attempting here to get our good friend Artemis to finally make an appearance at one of my feasts, it's just... wouldn't you know, she's all preoccupied, something about a hunt?\" \n Artemis: \n\"That's right, Lord Dionysus, a \"hunt\"! Which requires lots and lots of \"total quiet\", and clear-minded focus. So, if you'll excuse me?\" \nDialogue 02.\n Artemis: \n\"Oh, great, it's you, Zagreus! Here, let me offer you some fine new Boons, as well as Lord Dionysus here, who I am sure would love to talk your ear off just as much as mine!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"\"Eh\", tells me I'm being awful loud, and to back off, all sorts of nasty stuff like that, what can you do, though, right?\" \nBeing Invited to the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt; (Pre-Epilogue).\n Zagreus: \n\"Hope this lives up to your expectations, mate. In the name of Hades! Olympus? This is an official message! Should be a good time, Lord Dionysus!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Whoa, hold just for a moment, Zag, now, I can recognize an invite when I see one, man! And this is definitely almost certainly some sort of invite, one for me, and... one for everybody else, it looks like, here? Hoh, I'm excited, that is something really special, I can tell!\" \nPost-Epilogue Dialogue.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, back when we had that feast, there, man, I, I hope I didn't, you know, make for any inconveniences or anything down there, did I...?\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Zag, I cannot believe your mom's Persephone, that's something else, I got to tell you, man! I never took her for the sort to be all into Underworld stuff!\" \nMiscellaneous Conversations.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; Progressing in a Run.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"I got to hand it to you, Zag, you don't back down, you don't ever back down, what is this, like the twentieth time that you've attempted to escape?\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"You're getting somewhere, getting somewhere, man, I understand you made it up to Asphodel before, now that is progress, keep it up, you keep on going, yeah?\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"Heard you wrestled with some Satyrs near the surface, Zag! Nice work making it that far, and I just want to let you know that they are definitely not my crew, man! Satyrs I know aren't like that at all!\" \n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; Clearing a Run.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Ah, Zag, what \"happened \"last time, man? It seemed like you were rather close, but then, we couldn't see you anymore from here, and now you're back? Well, give another go!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Want you to know something, here, man. It's been a bit of a long haul, but you are getting closer to the surface, and you'll get there someday, and we're with you, however long it takes, OK?\" \nBuying Boon at &lt;a href=\"Charon\"&gt;Charon&lt;/a&gt;'s Shop.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Heeey, what's, uh, with that Charon, man, he's sort of, \"I-don't-know\", though I am glad he's been of service!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Ah-hah\", you found me holing up in Charon's nasty stash there did you man, well good, good, here!\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"Looks like you are stocked for one hell of a night down there, man! I knew Charon would hook you up with what you need!\" \nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, cheers for picking up the tab, there, Zag, now, I cannot exactly pay you back, though I could give you \"this\"!\" \nDialogue 05.\n Dionysus: \n\"I bet that Charon has to be the life of every feast you have down there, with such a personality, am I not right about that, man?\"\nHigh Affinity Dialogue.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"The key to any halfway decent feast is lots and lots of preparation, man. Or maybe just having to improvise, you know?\" \nAbout Backstory.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Sometimes I have to wonder, man, what's going through your head, I mean, I know you hear me and the others but it's so damn dark down there I can't hear you at all!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Let me tell you something, Zag, I know your dad he's got to be a real handful, I relate to that, you understand me, mate? So you get out of there, and you'll be more than welcome here, with us!\" \nAbout Legendary Boon.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Oh-hoh\", Zag, have I got something special here for you, I mean \"this \"here is top-notch stuff, \"even \"among the top-notch stuff I have to give, just look at this!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Look, man, I am feeling generous right now, know what I mean? And so, here's something \"extra \"potent for you, ought to keep you going for a while longer than you're used to, there!\" \nAbout &lt;a href=\"Yarn%20of%20Ariadne\"&gt;Yarn of Ariadne&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Why, you've a Yarn of Ariadne, right there, Zag, I know the lass for whom that yarn is named! She was a right attractive one, we had our little time, long story, though, will save it till you get here!\" \nAbout Reuniting &lt;a href=\"Orpheus\"&gt;Orpheus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Eurydice\"&gt;Eurydice&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Zag, I heard that Orpheus, he found his missing bride, why, isn't that the sweetest thing, isn't it, man? I'll drink to that, and I think so should you!\" \nAbout Gifting.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"You are the talk of the mountain, you know that, man? Good on you, getting on just about everybody's good side up here, I mean, that is a feat, all right!\" \nAbout &lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"You, man, must be mates with just about \"everybody \"down there, by now, yeah? Doling out Nectars left and right, just livening the place right up!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Say, let me just point out you've got a lot of Nectar on you, man! Oh, I can tell, I like the stuff a lot, myself, but even I don't pack \"that \"much, and I mean, \"wow\"!\" \nAbout &lt;a href=\"Ambrosia\"&gt;Ambrosia&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Say, man, if I'm not mistaken, I think you got yourself a bottle of Ambrosia, there? I'd no idea you could get that stuff downstairs! Do me a solid, though, hang on to any more you find, or better yet, give it away! I'd hate to think even a drop has gone to waste!\" \nDialogue 02.\n Dionysus: \n\"Well, would you just look at yourself, Zag! You are like a walking stockpile of Ambrosia, aren't you? Taking the best care of it, at that. I knew I could count on you, but... \"&lt;Sniff&gt; \"I didn't know I could be just so proud of you, you know, man?\" \nDialogue 03.\n Dionysus: \n\"Zag, turns out I am quite the judge of character, and you, man, have an \"awful \"lot of it, I mean, you've given out how much Ambrosia now? To \"all \"your mates, and \"more\"?!\" \nDialogue 04.\n Dionysus: \n\"You got to let me in on something, Zag, how did you gather up so much Ambrosia, there? I mean, sometimes I think the stuff is plentiful up here, but you are positively swimming in it, man!\" \nAbout Hades' &lt;a href=\"Sigil%20of%20the%20Dead\"&gt;Keepsake&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, Zag, uh... I may just be losing it or something here, but isn't that your dad's own blessing that you've got? That's something, man, I didn't know that he was helping you!\" \nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"Lord Dionysus, it's been great getting to know you, so, please accept this humble offering.\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Now that is something, a right princely gift, there, Zag, and just so happens I got something here I have been meaning to give you!\" \n\"Dionysus gives &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Overflowing%20Cup\"&gt;Overflowing Cup&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n Zagreus: \n\"Thank you, Dionysus mate.\"\n2nd Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"A toast in your honor, Lord Dionysus mate. Have I mentioned how pleased I am to have made your acquaintance?\" \n Dionysus: \n\"\"Hoh-oh\", what, is that for me, \"really\", I mean, cheers man, that is awful generous of you, I'm much obliged!\" \n3rd Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"Lord Dionysus mate, you have made the mood down here materially less miserable, and I am much obliged.\" \n Dionysus: \n\"What, is that for me, why Zag, I mean you really shouldn't have, you know I can't get enough of this stuff, right?\" \n4th Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"Lord Dionysus mate, you must have no shortage of supreme vintage at your disposal, but this one's from me.\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Why Zag, how positively thoughtful, man, I mean I love it, positively love this stuff, and I am very moved that you would think of me for it!\" \n5th Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"Hey, on no occasion whatsoever, cheers to you again, Lord Dionysus mate! This place is so much less dreary under your influence!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Ah, this is the greatest, Zag! This feast I'm headed to? I was getting a little concerned I wasn't going to have quite enough to go around for everyone. Well, you just saved my evening, man! Too bad you couldn't be there, yeah?\" \n6th Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"Dionysus mate, sometimes things weigh heavily on me, but then I hear from you, and it's like I don't have a care in the world! To your health!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Oh, you're really too much for me sometimes, you know that, man? Got to tell you, I don't think I ever felt so close to somebody so damn far away. But through the gift of drink? It's like we're with each other in spirit, all the time, you know?\" \n&lt;a href=\"Ambrosia\"&gt;Ambrosia&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Zagreus: \n\"What does one offer to the god of wine? The very best, is what, and down here, this is it, mate! I'm grateful I've got some of your spirit in me. To have such a connection, with you despite all the distance between us...!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Zag, I cannot believe what you are offering to me! Ambrosia, man, for \"me\"? And talk about a bottle that has seen some wild days and nights, I mean if it got all the way to you down there, only to come back up! Know what? I'm saving it, till we can share it, here!\" "}
{"id": "5239", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5239", "title": "Dionysus/Quotes (Hades II)", "text": "\"The following are quotes from &lt;a href=\"Dionysus\"&gt;Dionysus&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nFirst Meeting.\n Dionysus: \n\"Now who is \"this\", what sort of Nymph do we have here? Not from the waters nor the woods, but wait wait \"wait!\" Those \"eyes!\" Zag, man, is that \"you?!\" You've \"changed!\" I like it!\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"Lord Dionysus, I presume? I'm Melino\u00eb, sister to Zagreus. I've come to the mountain's aid at the family's behest! But, what is the meaning of this festivity? Aren't you at war?\"\n Dionysus: \n\"\"Ohhh, Mel,\" right, the others mentioned you. \"Erm,\" listen baby, I'm into \"lots\" of different things, but war just isn't one of them. What's the use, we gods can't die! But we can \"live!\"\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"Your mountain is under seige. Chronos took my side of the family, and soon he may take yours!\"\n Dionysus: \n\"All the more reason to raise a cup while we still can, yeah? \"Heh.\" Though I get it! Not your thing. But why not have a little pick-me-up for the road ahead?\"\nKeepsake Dialogue (&lt;a href=\"Keepsakes/Hades%20II\"&gt;Fig Leaf&lt;/a&gt;).\nKeepsake Equipped.\n Dionysus: \n\"That Fig Leaf that you're carrying ... it's from my \"private wardrobe!\" So how come you have it and not me? What, did I just hand it over as a gift?\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"You did exactly that, yes. I offered you a bottle of Nectar, and you gave me this Leaf in exchange. Don't you recall?\"\n Dionysus: \n\"Don't I recall ... \"erm\", sometimes! But not always, not so much of late! Well if past-me thought he should give you such a thing, he must have had a real good feeling for you, yeah?\"\nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"I ... don't wish to be just some ungrateful guest. I know you have your customs here, and I have studied them. So, please! For all your cheer and generosity!\" \n Dionysus: \n\"Whoa, this is Nectar, it's the real thing, we could use every drop that we can get! Then here is something for my most distinguished guests, of which I have decided \"you are one!\"\n\"Dionysus gives &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Keepsakes/Hades%20II\"&gt;Fig Leaf&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"I'm most grateful ... and wish I could stay for the festivities.\"\n2nd Time.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, \"nice\", more Nectar always good to have around in case the wine runs out, not that it ever does or ever will! Now, what exactly do we toast to next?\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"To emerging from peril unscathed? Or whatever you decide. I know maintaining high morale is paramount, especially with the mountain under siege.\"\n3rd Time.\n Dionysus: \n\"Hey, sure, I'll take that Nectar off your hands! As this here's \"just\" the place to put it to its proper use. But don't you get all sad and sappy with me, you're at a \"feast\", not at a wake!\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"I must admit, I'm unable to cast aside my fears and worries quite like you, Dionysus. It's little wonder mortals make so many offerings in your name ... as now do I.\"\n4th Time.\n Dionysus: \n\"Now that's the spirit, giving back to the community, I \"like\" it, yeah? After all, you know I can't make cheer and revelry for everyone all by myself, don't you? Though between us, I still can make an \"awful\" lot.\" \n Melino\u00eb: \n\"Such cheer and revelry that you've created, seemingly out of thin air ... and during such a time. Well, if this truly is to be a never-ending feast, then you'll need plenty of supplies!\""}
{"id": "2511", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2511", "title": "Dionysus/Relationships", "text": "Family.\nZeus.\n&lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' father.&lt;br&gt;They seemingly maintain a positive father-son relationship, even though Dionysus is not considered as reliable as some of Zeus' other children. Dionysus is aware that his father, Zeus, generally perceives him as someone irresponsible who rarely takes things seriously and underestimates him. However, he possesses the talent to please his father, who is notably indulgent with him.\nZeus held such great paternal affection for Dionysus that he elevated him to the status of a full god and invited him to reside on Mount Olympus. \nDionysus is sociable and excels in social gatherings. Zeus observes that Dionysus is polite in his interactions and always shows the due respect, finding him decent company for Zagreus.\nAthena.\n&lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' half-sister.&lt;br&gt;She indirectly criticizes him, suggesting that some of his relatives are participating only because they consider all of this a festival. However, it can be suggested that, unlike Athena, who may be acting, he genuinely thinks discovering a long-lost relative is cause for celebration.\nAres.\n&lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' half-brother.&lt;br&gt;Dionysus finds Ares too tempestuous. He thinks Zagreus can help him feel lighter. Ares seems to enjoy the parties his youngest half-brother throws, but dislikes his general passivity.\nAphrodite.\n&lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;: The Goddess of Love and Beauty.&lt;br&gt;She seems to have a good relationship with Dionysus, considering him to be sociable to the fullest and referring to him as a common brother. She participates in his revelries, telling Dionysus how amazing it is to have the power to persuade minds through wine, which flatters Dionysus.\nArtemis.\n&lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' half-sister.&lt;br&gt;He regards Artemis as a kind of hermit. Dionysus has tried more than once to include her in his usual feasts and revelries, but she cannot stand the noise. She disapproves of Dionysus' inconsequential lifestyle. In her dialogues with Zagreus, she warns him not to get involved with her partying half-brother.\nApollo.\n&lt;a href=\"Apollo\"&gt;Apollo&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' half-brother.&lt;br&gt;Their relationship is currently unknown. \nHermes.\n&lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' half-brother.&lt;br&gt;Hermes is Dionysus's older half-brother, and both of them are playful. Hermes tells Zagreus that Dionysus never feels like life is moving too fast. He also comments on Dionysus' ability to throw a great feast, hinting that he's probably attended many such parties with his brother.\nDemeter.\n&lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' foster aunt.&lt;br&gt;Dionysus finds Demeter very uptight and disagrees that the plants must die in winter, which he considers it a great exaggeration. He thinks his aunt should relax and enjoy some good wine with him. She warns him that drinking less wine for a while might do him good.\nPoseidon.\n&lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' uncle.&lt;br&gt;Poseidon seems to get along well with his nephew Dionysus, considering him similar, as they are both very relaxed, receptive and enjoy a good time and consider joining a feast with Zagreus as well.\nNonetheless, it seems Dionysus fears his uncle to a degree, similarly to his father, likely due to his authority and how he's from an older generation.\nChthonic Gods.\nThe Gods of the Underworld.\nHades.\n&lt;a href=\"Hades\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' uncle.&lt;br&gt; As someone who values work, Hades isn't too fond of Dionysus's life style of constant partying. He's even afraid the feast won't be good enough because of Dionysus's insane drinking habit.\nZagreus.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' cousin.&lt;br&gt; Initially, he helps Zagreus because he doesn't have anything else interesting to do, and it's been a long time since anything \"bombastic\" has happened. Dionysus shares a relaxed and genuine relationship with Zagreus and like the other Olympians, offers his aid to his cousin. He refers to him as \"Zag\", \"guy' or \"Prince Z\". At one point, the two collaborate together in pranking Orpheus, leading the musician to believe that the two are the same person. Dionysus plans to have an epic feast and party with Zagreus once Zagreus reaches Olympus.\nMelino\u00eb.\n&lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;: Dionysus' cousin.\nUnderworld Residents.\nTheseus.\n&lt;a href=\"Theseus\"&gt;Theseus&lt;/a&gt;: Hero of Athens.&lt;br&gt;Dionysus admits that he doesn't like Theseus for abandoning Ariadne shortly after defeating Asterius. Nonetheless, he'll grant him his help if called upon.\nOrpheus.\n&lt;a href=\"Orpheus\"&gt;Orpheus&lt;/a&gt;: Court Musician.&lt;br&gt;He proposes to Zagreus to have some \"harmless fun\" with Orpheus by tricking him into believing in an epic narrative where he and Zagreus are one and the same. When Zagreus does it, Dionysus has a good laugh. Orpheus later composes a song about it called the \"&lt;a href=\"Hymn%20to%20Zagreus\"&gt;Hymn to Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOthers.\nAriadne.\nAriadne: Dionysus's lover.\nIt was Dionysus that rescued Ariadne after she was abandoned by Theseus on the Island of Naxos. He'll tell Zagreus she's a nice lass and very attractive, and that they'll talk once Zagreus reaches Olympus.\nChaos.\n&lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;: The ancestor of Dionysus.&lt;br&gt;Chaos finds entertainment in Dionysus's unpredictability, much like Zagreus."}
