{"id": "1324", "revid": "18653", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1324", "title": "Doomstone", "text": "The Doomstone is a mini-boss found in a unique chamber in &lt;a href=\"Tartarus\"&gt;Tartarus&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt fires an 8-line radial pattern of beams from itself, beginning with two beams and sequentially firing more, though only 6 can be active at a time.\nEach time it takes damage, the Doomstone releases a Fragment that can form barriers of beams when near each other or the main Doomstone, similar to the Linker trait from the &lt;a href=\"Pact%20of%20Punishment%23Conditions\"&gt;Benefits Package Pact&lt;/a&gt; condition. The Fragments each have 20 Health and 20 Armor, and their beams deal 1 Damage per tick."}
{"id": "2290", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2290", "title": "Dora", "text": "Dora is a shade that inhabits &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads\"&gt;The Crossroads&lt;/a&gt; and is &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;'s roomate.\nShe appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\" and can be found in Melino\u00eb's tent where she can be interacted with.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nDora is a cunning amnesiac &lt;a href=\"Shade\"&gt;Shade&lt;/a&gt;, a posthumous soul of someone who passed away so long ago that she can't recall the details of her past life. Her mood swings are constant, oscillating between friendliness and menace. Yet, once people get to know her, they realize she's not as she appears; everyone understands she's harmless to her peers.\nHer personality is primarily mischievous, relaxed, sarcastic, and somewhat lethargic, though she maintains a friendly and even casual relationship with &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;. She often speaks of her endeavors in 'haunting,' to which the protagonist provides guidance and encouragement.\nDora can also alter her appearance to exude a more menacing aura, often speaking in macabre and theatrical terms when doing so. Additionally, her ghostly form allows her to enact 'minor possessions,' which presumably allows her to inhabit objects (like Melino\u00eb's mushroom bottle, as per her jests) to some degree.\nA few characters, such as &lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;, mention that there are rumors about Dora being a wicked, vengeful, and untrustworthy spirit, and that Melino\u00eb should stay away. However, in their interactions, Dora is only friendly and not at all apathetic towards Melino\u00eb, indicating that even its official title \"listless shade\" is mere speculation.\nRegarding the events of Hades II, particularly the renewed siege on Olympus by &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;, she primarily expresses a lack of familiarity with them. She sees &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Olympus\"&gt;Olympus&lt;/a&gt; as the domain of Melino\u00eb's less agreeable relatives, and views Chronos as a malevolent figure, albeit one who has never personally wronged her.\nPhysical description.\nIn her casual form, Dora is a smugly smiling shade with long hair and bangs that almost cover her eyes, as well as large hands that resemble the paws of a cat. By contrast, her 'haunting' form is lengthened, and has sharper features; it is further shrouded in shadow, marked by piercing yellow eyes with no irises, and a silhouetted, sharp mouth.\nDecorations.\nAs of the Olympic Update, Dora can be interacted with to add decorations to &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads\"&gt;The Crossroads&lt;/a&gt;. This costs a mixture of a new resource &lt;a href=\"Prestige\"&gt;Prestige&lt;/a&gt; and occasionally additional harvested resources. She will also become present in additional areas aside from &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;'s Tent, with each area having its own unique set of available decorations:\nGallery.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nIllustration=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "2721", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2721", "title": "Dora/Quotes", "text": "The following are quotes from &lt;a href=\"Dora\"&gt;Dora&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nFirst Meeting.\n Dora : \n\"\"Who dares disturb my eternal rest? You trifle with powers far beyond your comprehension, witch. Speak!\"\n Dora : \n\" \"...That was pretty decent, right, Mel? Maybe pushing it. OK if I call you \"witch \"like that?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"Witch \"worked for me in context, and a solid haunting all in all, Dora. But, I'd better run. Something I have to do.\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Then begone!\"\nKeepsake Dialogue (&lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Onion\"&gt;Ghost Onion&lt;/a&gt;).\nTBA\nAbout the Scenery.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//hades.fandom.com/wiki/The_Crossroads%23Melino%25C3%25AB%27s_Tent%3A~%3Atext%3DSub%252DLocations-%2CMelino%25C3%25AB%2527s%2520Tent%2C-%25E2%2580%259C\"&gt;Melino\u00eb's Tent&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Dora, couldn't help but notice that my jar collection wasn't sorted properly. I would never store fungus with herbs. Are you trying to subtly drive me mad?\"\n Dora : \n\"No... Although, now that you put it that way, maybe in the future, \"yes\". I was working on minor possessions and your mushroom bottle kind of slipped. So I put it back!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You put it \"incorrectly \"back. I... \"augh\". Just tell me of such things next time, would you?\"\n Dora : \n\"Maybe I will, maybe I won't.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Dora : \n\"You know, Mel, you can be a bit uptight sometimes. Where'd you even get that from? Even the head witch is more relaxed than you.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Look I'm under a lot of pressure right now, all right? Everybody's counting on me to literally \"kill Time... \"so I would like this tent to be an orderly place! Seeing as I'm having to return so often...\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Eh\", so what? Killing time's my specialty, don't see \"me \"gettin' all worked up.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"Ungh...\"\nDialogue 03.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Dora, I was thinking... if I promise not to be so \"uptight\", as you call it... would you promise not to move my belongings about when I'm away?\"\n Dora : \n\"\"How dare you make demands of me, you insignificant fleck? Mmm\", nope, no deal. Want to be uptight, go ahead. Don't stop on my account.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You just want to keep messing with my stuff!\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Mmm\", that's right.\"\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads\"&gt;The Crossroads&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It's been nice to see you out and about a little more often lately, not just cooped up in here. How are you managing? \"\n Dora : \n\"\"Eh\", I'm managing. Those other Shades don't know the first thing about haunting, and it turns out they've got the dirt on \"everybody \"here... including \"you.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Comforting to know the brunt of our resistance is enjoying themselves a good bit of gossip.\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Ohh \"yeah.\"\nOceanus.\n Dora : \n\"Hey, you're up. You were out a while. See anything good down there that time?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I fought past Erebus, down into Oceanus. It was so strange, being underneath the sea. Do you remember the sea, Dora?\"\n Dora : \n\"The sea... the sea, the sea, the sea, \"that's \"the thing with all the \"water \"in it, \"right? \"Heard it's nice \"sometimes! \"Also \"kills \"a bunch of people, death by drowning, so... \"Huh\", I've been getting mixed messages, I guess.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It's a big place...\"\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Surface\"&gt;The Surface&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You must remember something of life on the surface, right, Dora? Anything at all? I wonder what it must have been like.\"\n Dora : \n\"I \"don't \"remember, and I \"don't \"wonder! Who cares? \"This \"is the life, right here.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"&lt;Sigh&gt;\"\n&lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Mourning\"&gt;Fields of Mourning&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dora : \n\"\"Oof\", you look rough, if we're being honest, Mel. Want to talk about it, or at least tell me the juicy bits because I'm bored?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Last night I visited the Mourning Fields, and... being surrounded by that much despair... I think I must have brought some of it home.\"\n Dora : \n\"Well why don't I just \"scare it out of you, you wretched worm?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Hey that worked.\"\n Dora : \n\"I know, right?\"\n&lt;a href=\"Rift%20of%20Thessaly\"&gt;Rift of Thessaly&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dora : \n\"Hey where've you been? You \"smell! \"Not in a bad way necessarily, and I don't know how I \"can \"smell, or remember any smell, so... that is weird.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I was up top. Must be the sea air and the salt, distinct from Oceanus down below. I sailed across the waters, toward Olympus, on a ship! \"\n Dora : \n\"Exciting! I was right here the whole time.\"\nMiscellaneous Conversations.\nAbout &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; Returning to the Tent.\nDialogue 01.\n Dora : \n\"Mel! Thought I finally had the place to myself, then next I know, you're back. Damn near scared me to life. Rough night again?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Rough night, Dora. Fear not, you'll have the tent to yourself yet! See you.\"\n Dora : \n\"Yeah, you too.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Dora : \n\"You know, it's kind of spooky how you never come in through the front flap anymore. Ever think of taking up haunting, yourself?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Oh, yes! I figure if none of this works out, the lot of us can wander the earth, striking fear into the hearts of any mortals who dare look upon us.\"\n Dora : \n\"\"&lt;Gasp&gt; \"Now we're talking...\"\nDialogue 03.\n Dora : \n\"\"Whew! \"Thought you'd never snap out of it. You OK?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Yes, thank you, Dora. I hope I didn't cause you any concern. Have you been by my side here all this time?\"\n Dora : \n\"What, me? No. Just out for a breather.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"But you don't even breathe...\"\n Dora : \n\"Cut it out...!\