re, back when I died...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Oh I doubt it. You'd remember having met someone like that. And he'd remember you as well! Though, you have been dead a while...\"\n Dora : \n\"Yeah. Maybe I was one of his first jobs. Just an innocent young woman, doomed to a cruel inevitable future she never deserved...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"OK, Dora.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Heracles\"&gt;Heracles&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Do you remember the name \"Heracles? \"The greatest half-god hero of the surface, slayer of the Nemean Lion, and so on?\"\n Dora : \n\"Nah, not really. But I hear the other Shades go \"on \"and \"on \"about him every now and then. Why do you ask?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I encountered him. He's as big as they say, that much is sure. He has such a storied past, I thought maybe you'd recall one of the tales.\"\n Dora : \n\"Well, you thought wrong, my friend.\"\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//hades.fandom.com/wiki/Characters/Hades_II%23The_Unseen%3A~%3Atext%3DBook%2520of%2520Shadows-%2CThe%2520Unseen%2C-Melino%25C3%25AB\"&gt;The Unseen as a Whole&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Have you ever even spoken with Commander Schelemeus, Dora? Or Odysseus? We have these great masters on our side, who know so much of history. So much they can teach us.\"\n Dora : \n\"History? That what they call it nowadays? Well, I don't have big plans to go to war with the rest of you anytime soon, though if I change my mind, I'll probably check in with those guys.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"They're good people!\"\nWith other Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Dora : \n\"...And so I say, \"begone accursed witch! I have occupied this grove for aeons, long before your pitiable tent came to rest upon it! \"Oh hey Mel.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I see the two of you have met! Lord Moros, Dora speaks the truth as always. She's been here longer than I have, if you can believe it!\"\n Moros : \n\"I can, indeed. For I know an old soul when I see one. It's a pleasure to meet you, Dora. Do let me know if I can be of service in some way.\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Haha. \"Count on it, Horns! Now then, \"I bid your leave. Farewell!\"\n Moros : \n\"Farewell!\"\nDialogue 02.\n Dora : \n\"...His own \"brother? Eugh, \"no way, that is twisted! Your sisters are sick!\"\n Moros : \n\"Well... they have many mortal lives to untangle, so to speak. The work can grow repetitive, lose its spark. So they liven things up from time to time.\"\n Dora : \n\"Oh totally I, I would completely do the same if I were them. I wonder what they did to \"me... \"Could you, like, look me up, or something...?\"\n Moros : \n\"\"Heh! \"I fear I'm not at liberty to do such things.\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Ah\", come on...\"\nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Wanted you to have this, Dora. To the best haunter in all the Crossroads!\"\n Dora : \n\"See, I \"knew \"you were going to pull this gift-custom thing on me sooner or later, so I have come prepared. Catch!\"\n\"Dora gives &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Onion\"&gt;Ghost Onion&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"For me? Thank you, Dora!\"\n2nd Time.\n Dora : \n\"Oh, you don't need to get this kind of stuff for me! I can just take whatever stuff of yours I want when you're out!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Well you can't take \"this \"while I'm out! I keep it on me at all times, for just such an occasion.\"\n3rd Time.\n Dora : \n\"\"Fool! I am not susceptible to mere baubles such as this! Ah\", just kidding. \"Totally \"susceptible. Gimme!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"At last, I have discovered a vulnerable point in your defenses!\"\n4th Time.\n Dora : \n\"Starting to get the feeling maybe I liked this stuff back when I had eyeballs and so on.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Doesn't matter whether you liked it then, what matters is you like it now.\"\n5th Time.\n Dora : \n\"\"Ungh\", on the one hand, I really don't know what I did to deserve this. But on the other hand, I really don't care! It's mine now.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It most certainly is! And there's more in it for you if you keep on haunting this tent!\"\n6th Time.\n Dora : \n\"\"Such pitiable offerings as this are hardly worth my notice, witch! \"No, but, seriously, thanks. Nobody ever gets me anything! Besides you, I mean. It's nice, you know?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It's nice for me as well! Having you here as company means a lot, so it really is the least I could do.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Bath%20Salts\"&gt;Bath Salts&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Say Dora? Would you mind accompanying me over to the baths? I'd hate to think they aren't haunted.\"\n Dora : \n\"Do I want to float aimlessly in some near-boiling water? Do I ever! What are we waiting for?\"\n Dora : \n\"Wonder if I was ever shy about this kind of stuff...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You still can sense something of the waters' warmth, can't you, Dora?\"\n Dora : \n\"Well, I can see all the steam rising, which I associate with warmth, so... I guess it kind of tricks me into thinking warm thoughts.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"That doesn't sound so bad. Though, you do remember what warmth was like, then? From your mortal days?\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Ohh\", not really, no. I, I guess I've just heard so much about it, it's like I've experienced it myself.\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Whew! \"That was basically like floating around in your tent, though I appreciate it nonetheless!\"\n2nd Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Hey I've got these bath salts here that are more than enough for me, if you're not busy at the moment...?\"\n Dora : \n\"Mel, you know I like doing nothing. Sitting in the bathhouse with you? Well that's got to be the next best thing so, shall we?\"\n Dora : \n\"Like being cooked in a cauldron, isn't it?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Don't you ever wonder how you used to be, Dora? When you were flesh and blood? I bet you were very beautiful.\"\n Dora : \n\"\"Hah! Whaaat\", seriously? Is it because of my voice or because of my curves? Nah, you're just messing with me.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I am not! It's because of your confidence, I suppose. You're very self-assured! Some Shades cower before me, but you and I always got on.\"\n Dora : \n\"Well, some Shades are total buffoons. Anyway, it doesn't really matter to me how I used to be. If I was happy about it, I figure I'd remember.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You think you've deliberately forgotten your past?\"\n Dora : \n\"Yeah. Why else would I have forgotten everything? Probably took a couple swigs from the River Lethe, and that was that! Clean slate.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"The River of Forgetfulness... you think you were down in Elysium?\"\n Dora : \n\"You know, if I'm not mistaken I think I had a good time with you back there. Thanks, Mel!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Twin%20Lures\"&gt;Twin Lures&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Hey, if you're not busy, up for a little visit with me to the riverside? I've got a twin lure we could use right here.\"\n Dora : \n\"Don't know that I'll be doing you much good, between my inability to use a rod of fishing and my inability to keep quiet, but hey! You asked for it.\"\n Dora : \n\"Well, that definitely was a thing that happened. Thanks!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Bye.\""}
