{"id": "974", "revid": "34508", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=974", "title": "Duo Boons", "text": "Duo Boons are a type of &lt;a href=\"Boons\"&gt;Boon&lt;/a&gt; which combines the powers of two different gods for a unique effect. Duo Boons can only be obtained when you have the prerequisite boons and, like all boons, are lost when &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; dies and returns to the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;\" there are 28 Duo Boons, shared between 8 different gods: &lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ares\"&gt;Ares&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dionysus\"&gt;Dionysus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt;. Neither &lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt; nor &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt; will offer Duo Boons. Every god that may have Duo boons shares one with each other god.\nThe chances for Duo Boons can be increased with specific gods' &lt;a href=\"Keepsakes\"&gt;Keepsakes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Eurydice\"&gt;Eurydice&lt;/a&gt;'s Refreshing Nectar, &lt;a href=\"Well%20of%20Charon\"&gt;Well of Charon&lt;/a&gt; item Yarn of Ariadne, and the &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20of%20Night\"&gt;Mirror of Night&lt;/a&gt; talent Gods' Legacy.\nAcquiring all Duo Boons awards 15 from the &lt;a href=\"Fated%20List%20of%20Minor%20Prophecies\"&gt;Fated List of Minor Prophecies&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4241", "revid": "4008728", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4241", "title": "Duo Boons/Hades II", "text": "Duo Boons are a type of &lt;a href=\"Boons/Hades%20II\"&gt;Boon&lt;/a&gt; which combines the powers of two different gods for a unique effect. Duo Boons can only be obtained when you have the prerequisite boons and, like all boons, are lost when &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; dies and returns to &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads\"&gt;The Crossroads&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\" there are 29 Duo Boons, shared between 8 different gods: &lt;a href=\"Aphrodite\"&gt;Aphrodite&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Apollo\"&gt;Apollo&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Demeter\"&gt;Demeter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hephaestus\"&gt;Hephaestus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hera\"&gt;Hera&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hestia\"&gt;Hestia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Poseidon\"&gt;Poseidon&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Artemis\"&gt;Artemis&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dionysus\"&gt;Dionysus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Selene\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt; will not offer Duo Boons. Every god that may have Duo boons shares one with each other god.\nAll Duo Boons count for the &lt;a href=\"Aether\"&gt;Aether&lt;/a&gt; element.\nThe chance for a Duo Boon is 12%, increased only by a Miniboss Encounter in Tartarus to 20%."}
{"id": "432", "revid": "49442578", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=432", "title": "Dusa", "text": "Dusa is a shade in the form of a floating, disembodied 's head. She works as a maid in the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt; under &lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;, constantly floating around and cleaning, and after a time is promoted to the House's Head Custodian. \nCharacteristics and Personality.\nDusa is the severed head of a Gorgon who works as a suffering maid for the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;. She appears very optimistic, cheerful, extremely hardworking and is one of the best people &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; could ever meet, but always seems doomed to do everything on her own.\nDusa is friendly, shy, playful, a great company and likes to share gossip in their free time. She has a painfully obvious crush on Zagreus (you can even hear some sighs), but she is never able to express her feelings due to her strong social anxiety and, more importantly, her never-ending cleaning tasks.\nHowever, Dusa doesn't like pity eyes, as she is seen as the \"Cinderella.\" Sometimes the residents of the House sympathize with her and offer their help, but she shows her fangs and refuses any assistance, insisting on doing everything on her own. She is a victim of her workload, especially under &lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;'s supervision, and gets skittish with anyone she wants to avoid.\nDusa is not good at hiding things and can speak without filters. In a conversation with Zagreus, she confesses that she has fantasized about Zagreus and &lt;a href=\"Thanatos\"&gt;Thanatos&lt;/a&gt; in her mind when they are alone, which makes her run away in embarrassment.\nIn the end of her romance arc she rejects him, when Zagreus invites her to go out, she realizes that she loves him and admits that he is one of the coolest people in the House of Hades, but she simply doesn't feel attracted him in a romantic way. She asks to remain friends for eternity.\nPhysical description.\nDusa is a small Gorgon, and her body remains unknown. She has light green skin with freckles and large yellow eyes, giving her a positive expression. One of her serpentine locks always holds a duster, and she ties the emblem of the House of Hades around her forehead.\nHistory.\nBefore Hades.\nLittle is known about Dusa's past, as she doesn't talk much about it. \nHowever, the codex entry on gorgons says that when Medusa was killed, her blood soaked into the underworld and spawned a brood of vengeful offspring. In a conversation between Zagreus and Dusa where Zagreus asks about Asphodels's gorgons, Dusa says to imagine having mindless siblings made from your own blood. It can then be assumed that when the hero Perseus decapitated Medusa, her blood soaked into Asphodel and created the gorgons, the Megagorgon, and Dusa. Dusa does specifically say your blood when talking about the gorgons which might mean that Dusa is the soul of Medusa, or perhaps some of Medusa's memory given physical from. She does mention that she thought anyone could turn others into stone by just looking, like she did.\nHer cause of death was decapitation, the preferable method to kill gorgons.\nHades.\nDusa is a maid in the House of Hades. She's tasked with feeding Cerberus and cleaning the House, occasionally checking on other workers as well. She constantly overworks herself, which often worry those around her. Even if they try to help, she'll just hiss at them and deny their offer.\nAs Zagreus starts to talk more frequently to her and building a friendship, Nyx grows weary of this, and in what she sees as an act of compassion for the gorgon, fires her. Zagreus doesn't take the news well, and neither does Megaera, so after a little convincing from him, Nyx re-hires Dusa, warning her to not overwork herself so much, and promotes her to Head Custodian.\nEpilogue.\nShe keeps on working for House, now taking better care of herself.\nBefore Hades II.\nDusa was trapped in time like all of the House of Hades by &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt; after the Titan escaped his imprisonment.\nAffinity.\nIf given &lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;, Dusa will give you the &lt;a href=\"Harpy%20Feather%20Duster\"&gt;Harpy Feather Duster&lt;/a&gt;. \nAfter being given 6 bottles of Nectar, further gifts will be locked until her favor is completed. \nCompleting the favor and gifting her a bottle of &lt;a href=\"Ambrosia\"&gt;Ambrosia&lt;/a&gt; will have her give you &lt;a href=\"Companion%20Fidi\"&gt;Companion Fidi&lt;/a&gt; in return.\nDusa's affinity gauge is maxed out at 10 hearts, requiring the gifting of 6 Nectar and 10 Ambrosia, differing from other romanceable characters. Further information detailed in &lt;a href=\"%23Romance\"&gt;Romance&lt;/a&gt;.\nFavor.\nDusa's favor involves the lounge renovations, which she has fallen behind on doing. Zagreus must help her bring the lounge up to Nyx's standards by using the &lt;a href=\"House%20Contractor\"&gt;House Contractor&lt;/a&gt; to complete a minimum of 12 Lounge-focused renovations, which \"must\" include at least one rug for the area as well as cleaning up &lt;a href=\"Cerberus\"&gt;Cerberus's&lt;/a&gt; fur and the scratches he left in the floor. After doing this, talking to Dusa will complete the A Place of Revelry &lt;a href=\"Fated%20List%20of%20Minor%20Prophecies\"&gt;prophecy&lt;/a&gt; and unlock the ability to give &lt;a href=\"Ambrosia\"&gt;Ambrosia&lt;/a&gt; to her.\nRomance?\nDusa's romance differs from the other options in that each successive gift of Ambrosia requires an increased number of bottles; while her first only requires 1, subsequent gifts require 2, then 3, until her final gift is given as 4 bottles.\nAfter giving Dusa the tenth gift, she and Zagreus will have a conversation where Dusa explains that she has come to realise she isn't looking for an intimate relationship, and isn't attracted to him in that way. They agree to remain \"friends for all eternity\" instead, though as Zagreus points out, that in itself can be its own form of love.\nSome time after the final romance conversation, Dusa will offer to return all the Ambrosia she has been given; Zagreus may take them back or persuade her to keep them as the gift they were intended as, with no negative repercussions for either choice.\nDusa can be romanced at the same time as &lt;a href=\"Megaera\"&gt;Megaera&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"Thanatos\"&gt;Thanatos&lt;/a&gt; with no drawbacks.\nGallery.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nConcept=\nIllustration=\nMerchandise=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "1906", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1906", "title": "Dusa/Quotes", "text": "Dusa Quotes.\nThis details the dialogue and quotes of the maid, Dusa. Be aware this page will contain SPOILERS.\n&lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;.\nDusa will often talk independent of conversation.\nApproaching.\n\"Hah, haha!\"&lt;br&gt;\n\"H, hi!\"&lt;br&gt;\n\"&lt;Gasp&gt;\"\nConversations with &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Dusa: \"Oh, \"um\", so, hi Prince! So, is there anything I can get you, or maybe tidy up some more, or... I just thought maybe you'd like something to drink? Sometime?\"\n Zagreus: \"\"Oh\"! A drink sometime sounds wonderful, Dusa, maybe tomorrow assuming I'm not getting out of here by then...?\"\n Dusa: \"\"Whaa\", I mean, it's no big deal, I mean, forget I asked, or anything, I'm sorry, bye!\"\n &lt;Dusa proceeds to fly away.&gt;\n Zagreus: \"Dusa...?\"\n Dusa: \"\"Ohh\", oh, oh, oh my, Your Highness, are you... are you really sure you want me to have \"this\"?\"\n Zagreus: \"I really am, Dusa. I hope you enjoy it.\"\n - After the third gift of &lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;\n Dusa: \"Uh, \"um\", I just, wanted to apologize, because, I think maybe I didn't act very appropriately last time you spoke to me? BUt I just really, really like this job, and promise I will \n always do my very best, so, I just hope I'll have another chance?\"\n Zagreus: \"Dusa, please, there's no need to apologize! You've been doing a wonderful job, really!\"\n Dusa: \"I... \"what\"? You really mean it, Prince, I... thank you, thanks so much!!\"\n &lt;Dusa proceeds to fly away.&gt;\n Zagreus: \"\"Erm\", Ms. Dusa, I wanted to, \"uh\", cordially invite you to an outing in the lounge? Remember when you asked me about a drink?\"\n Dusa: \"\"Aaah\"! Oh, oh, oh, really, what you mean, right now, you're... I... I guess I'm overdue to take a break...\"\n &lt;They travel to the lounge and time passes&gt;\n Dusa: \"...And, well, since I don't exactly fit the mold of your traditional gorgon, I mean, I have no body for example, I had trouble finding work! That is until Lord Hades took me in, and then I \n met you, and, well, I just love this job!!\"\n Zagreus: \"\"Oh\"! I can definitely relate at least to some of that.\"\n Dusa: \"&lt;\"Sigh\"&gt; I, I, I, thanks, Your Highness. Prince. Prince Zagreus!\"\n Zagreus: \"Bye for now.\"\n &lt;Dusa proceeds to fly away.&gt;"}
{"id": "2498", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2498", "title": "Dusa/Relationships", "text": " \nHouse of Hades.\nZagreus.\n&lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;: Dusa's colleague&lt;br&gt;Zagreus extends genuine warmth and respect towards Dusa, regardless of their differing positions. Despite their contrasting statuses, he treats her as an equal, never condescending or looking down on her. Whenever they interact, Dusa often finds herself flustered, her demeanor betraying the depth of her feelings towards Zagreus, though she may not readily admit them.\nInitially, Nyx holds reservations about their friendship, concerned about Dusa's tendency to overwork herself and the potential implications of her closeness to Zagreus. This unease reaches a breaking point when Nyx abruptly dismisses Dusa from her duties. However, Zagreus intervenes, advocating for Dusa's reinstatement, emphasizing her value to the household, albeit with certain conditions to ensure her well-being.\nWhile Zagreus and Dusa share a deep bond and mutual respect, there's a subtle undercurrent of romantic tension between them. Zagreus may entertain the idea of pursuing a romantic relationship with Dusa, but she ultimately turns down his advances. Despite her admiration for him, Dusa realizes that her feelings for Zagreus are rooted more in their friendship and camaraderie, prioritizing their platonic connection above any romantic entanglement.\nMegaera.\n&lt;a href=\"Megaera\"&gt;Megaera&lt;/a&gt;: Dusa's colleague.&lt;br&gt;Megaera maintains friendly relations with Dusa and acknowledges that Megaera has always treated her kindly. The two often invite each other out when they have time off, and they always take the day for girls, drinking and gossiping on days off.\nDespite Dusa's reluctance to accept help from others and even telling Megaera that she's fine and not to worry about her, Megaera was the first to oppose Nyx and the main force behind getting Dusa back to work and taking a break.\nBefore accepting the proposal to date Zagreus, Megaera will talk to Dusa about it. Dusa is happy that she's the first to know the news. Despite having a crush on Zagreus, she believes it feels so right, and she supports her and Zagreus being together. She insists that Megaera shouldn't deny her feelings, sacrificing in favor of their friendship. Dusa acknowledges Megaera's care and concern for her, and this time, she is willing to make the sacrifice for the sake of their friendship.\nNyx.\n&lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;: Dusa's boss.&lt;br&gt;Nyx is very fond of Dusa but disapproves of her tendency to overwork herself and associating with Zagreus. She eventually removes Dusa from her job without warning. It is when Zagreus intervenes that Nyx is persuaded to allow Dusa to work in the House again, although not without \"certain stipulations\". Dusa is eventually promoted to head guardian of the house by her, when Nyx provided that she may have been unfair.\nThanatos.\n&lt;a href=\"Thanatos\"&gt;Thanatos&lt;/a&gt;: Dusa's colleague.&lt;br&gt;When dating Thanatos, Dusa lets slip to having thoughts about Zagreus and Thanatos, imagining lately \"the things they do together,\" blushing in panic before going into further detail. At least Thanatos must acknowledge that Dusa works better than her brother.\nHypnos.\n&lt;a href=\"Hypnos\"&gt;Hypnos&lt;/a&gt;: Dusa's colleague.&lt;br&gt;She is efficient and he is lazy, but they seem to have a friendly disposition. As Hypnos becomes more productive, he is praised by his brother and also by Dusa for his good service, but she still puts in more effort.\nSkelly and Charon.\n&lt;a href=\"Skelly\"&gt;Skelly&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charon\"&gt;Charon&lt;/a&gt;: Dusa's colleagues.&lt;br&gt;Dusa's colleagues. Skelly and she seem to have a positive relationship. Even though she finds Charon intimidating, they devise a plan to reunite a certain mother and son.\nPersephone.\n&lt;a href=\"Persephone\"&gt;Persephone&lt;/a&gt;: Dusa's queen.&lt;br&gt;Their relationship wasn't fully explored, but employee comments suggest that Persephone treated everyone well in the underworld. It's highly likely that they all still miss her. Additionally, the devotion of Dusa and Skelly were evident as they wanted her back home.\nAchilles.\n&lt;a href=\"Achilles\"&gt;Achilles&lt;/a&gt;: Forgotten Hero.&lt;br&gt;Even though they don't talk much to each other, he noticed that she hates it when residents feel sorry for her. Once, Achilles sympathized with the suffering of the maiden Dusa and offered to help her clean, but she just bared her teeth and refused.\nOlympian Gods.\nAthena.\n&lt;a href=\"Athena\"&gt;Athena&lt;/a&gt;: Goddess of Wisdom.&lt;br&gt;Although the nature of her relationship with Athena remains undisclosed, it is noteworthy that whenever Athena makes an appearance on screen, she noticeably displays terror and seeks to conceal herself in order to avoid being seen by the goddess.\nHermes.\n&lt;a href=\"Hermes\"&gt;Hermes&lt;/a&gt;: God of Swiftness.&lt;br&gt;Dusa and Hermes were part of a team, along with Charon and Skelly, joining forces to bring Zagreus and Persephone together."}
