{"id": "3974", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3974", "title": "Earth", "text": ""}
{"id": "2824", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2824", "title": "Echo", "text": "Echo is an Oread nymph who was cursed to repeat the last words spoken to her by &lt;a href=\"Hera\"&gt;Hera&lt;/a&gt; after Echo had covered for &lt;a href=\"Zeus\"&gt;Zeus&lt;/a&gt;. Echo would later fall in love with &lt;a href=\"Narcissus\"&gt;Narcissus&lt;/a&gt; but like all his other suitors she was rejected by him which caused her to die with a broken heart. Her treatment by Narcissus caught the eye of &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;, who cursed Narcissus to only fall in love with himself.\nEcho appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt; \" and offers her Plaintive Echoes to &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; in her fight against &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;. She can be encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Mourning\"&gt;Fields of Mourning&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nHaving been cursed to speak only what has been said last by others, she is merely an echo of what once was.\nDespite seeming static and her expressions not conveying much, she's a good-natured nymph. As Melino\u00eb can deduce from their interactions, Echo genuinely cares for the princess, even though they didn't initially knew each other well, and she helps her out of fear for her safety.\nEcho is also a hapless romantic, as she had a crush on Narcissus who unfortunately didn't reciprocate her feelings for him. This led Echo to become heartbroken even in death which led her to inhabit the Fields of Mourning.\nAlthough repetitive in nature, Echo possesses the ability to distort and manipulate what she hears. She presents herself with an air of propriety, capable of twisting Mel's words to her advantage as she wishes.\nPhysical description.\nBeing an Oread nymph, she's of the mountains and her skin and hair reflect as such. Her body is hourglass shaped with various carvings and moss adoring her, along with gold jewelry accents. Her hair is mostly held above her head and looks liked carved stones stacked atop each other, with two 'rock buns' lower down. Echo's ears are pointed and her eyes are a light shade of purple.\nHades II.\nEcho is encountered by Melino\u00eb while traversing the Fields of Mourning and gives her Plaintive Echoes to Melino\u00eb whenever she visits her. During one of the conversations with Echo, Melino\u00eb mentions Narcissus which makes Echo repeat his name in a rather sad tone which caught Melino\u00eb's attention and makes her realize that Echo is in the Fields because of him.\nGallery.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nConcept=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "5213", "revid": "55148434", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5213", "title": "Echo/Plaintive Echoes", "text": "Echo's \"Plaintive echoes\" are focused around \"echoing\" your abilities and skills, either by giving diminishing bonuses to survivability, copying rewards or mirroring pre-aquired bonuses. Echo will offer &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; a \"Plaintive echo\" upon entering her chamber in the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Mourning\"&gt;Fields of Mourning&lt;/a&gt;."}
