ields? But you don't have to be afraid of her.\"\n Echo : \n\"...afraid of her... don't have to be afraid of her... \"don't be afraid of her...\"\nWith Other Characters.\n&lt;a href=\"Narcissus\"&gt;Narcissus&lt;/a&gt; (While in &lt;a href=\"Oceanus\"&gt;Oceanus&lt;/a&gt; Wearing The &lt;a href=\"Concave%20Stone\"&gt;Concave Stone&lt;/a&gt;).\n Narcissus : \n\"Be seeing you, Laurel!\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"It's Melino\u00eb! Forget it...\"\n Echo : \n\"Melino\u00eb, forget it... forget it... \"forget it...\"\nGifts.\n&lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"Even in a place of sorrow such as this, there's beauty... gentleness. I know not how to ease your burden yet, though perhaps this will help.\"\n Echo : \n\"Perhaps this will help... this will help... \"this will help...\"\n\"Echo gives &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Concave%20Stone\"&gt;Concave Stone&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"You're giving this to me? It's an honor.\"\n Echo : \n\"An honor... an honor... \"an honor...\"\n2nd Time.\n Melino\u00eb: \n\"It means a lot to see your friendly face. May this Nectar sweeten your time here! Look how vast these Fields are. Plenty of room for more than just sorrow!\"\n Echo : \n\"More than just sorrow... just sorrow... \"just sorrow...\"\n3rd Time.\n\"I have more Nectar for you, Echo, if you please! Where I am from, it's a small gift we offer those we care about. I don't know about you, but even just handing over this stuff, I feel a bit better.\"\n Echo : \n\"I feel a bit better... bit better... \"bit better...\""}
{"id": "4407", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4407", "title": "Echo/Relationships", "text": "The Unseen.\nMelino\u00eb.\n&lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;: Princess of the Underworld.\nMelino\u00eb can come across Echo in the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Mourning\"&gt;Fields of Mourning&lt;/a&gt;. At first, communication will be difficult, until Melino\u00eb understands Echo can only repeat what she says, and thus will change her way of speech to allow Echo to greet her as well, instead of it being one-sided. Eventually, Melino\u00eb discovers Echo is a former admirer of Narcissus and works to have them see each other again, in an attempt to lift Echo's spirits.\nNemesis.\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;: Retribution Incarnate.\nEcho is terrified of Nemesis and tends to go and hide somewhere to avoid her.\nUnderworld Residents.\nNarcissus.\n&lt;a href=\"Narcissus\"&gt;Narcissus&lt;/a&gt;: Echo's crush.\nIn life, Echo was enamored to him, but he didn't reciprocate her feelings and she died from heartbreak. She still loves and thinks about him, and apparently Narcissus hasn't forgotten her, though he finds her to be too self-centered, unaware of her curse. Nonetheless, when the water of his glade becomes murky, to pass the time, Narcissus travels from &lt;a href=\"Oceanus\"&gt;Oceanus&lt;/a&gt; to the Fields of Mourning to see and talk with her again and, later, back in Oceanus, says he didn't like the place much, but might go back."}
{"id": "4378", "revid": "54583845", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4378", "title": "Eidolon", "text": "Eidolons are one-eyed monstrosities roaming the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Ephyra\"&gt;City of Ephyra&lt;/a&gt;.\nFloating and oozing blood, Eidolons strike at Melino\u00eb by hurling disembodied eyeballs at her. These eyes deal a small amount of damage on impact and then take on a life of their own, pursuing Melino\u00eb and detonating at close range if not killed quickly. Upon death, the Eidolon will leave behind a single eye.\n&lt;a href=\"Gameplay_mechanics/Hades_II%23Armor\"&gt;Armored&lt;/a&gt; Eidolons spawn additional (Armored) eyes."}
