t like it, and brought me in here hoping a nice hot bath was all it'd take for me to change, well then... I hate to disappoint.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Looks like the waters haven't rid you of your tensions yet...! Sometimes a hot spring is just a hot spring, Eris. Not everything is an assault on your ideals.\"\n Eris : \n\"With all of you, I never can be sure. Though, this is nicer than the last time, and the heat isn't so bad right now, I guess...\"\n Eris : \n\"\"Eugh\"... think I drank \"way \"too much bath water back there. Is this what being purified feels like? \"Whew!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"See you, Eris...\"\nGift Decline.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Hey... what would you say about a visit to the hot springs, to cleanse yourself of all your foul deeds? And me of mine?\"\n Eris : \n\"Oh, \"haha\", well... you know, I'd feel way too self-conscious there with anybody else. Sorry!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Twin%20Lures\"&gt;Twin Lures&lt;/a&gt;.\nGift Decline.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"The fishing pier's wide open as you can see... any impulse to make use of it a while?\"\n Eris : \n\"\"Mmm\", a trip to the fishing-hole involves a lot more being still and quiet than I think I can handle right now, thanks.\"\n\"NPC_Eris_01.MissingDistanceTrigger.VoiceLines\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Eris is gone...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"What's Eris up to now...\"\nPre-Fight Conversations.\nFirst Meeting.\n Eris : \n\"Heya, sailor! What a coincidence, running into you like this \"so \"far away from home. Where you headed? Maybe I could give you a lift.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You know perfectly well where I'm headed. And I can get there on my own, thanks.\"\n Eris : \n\"You sure about that? Because it looks like you've been having a \"pretty \"rough night so far. And it's only going to get worse.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I don't care for your insinuations here, Eris. Speak plain, or get out of my way.\"\n Eris : \n\"Oh I'll speak plain: You're boring. I don't \"like \"you. And you don't get to order me around...!\"\nMiscellaneous Conversations.\nAbout The Obstacles.\n Eris : \n\"Come on, \"really? \"I thought I made myself real clear with you before, but here you are like nothing happened, and it's just another night!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"This \"is \"just another night to me, Eris. So you stand with Chronos against the gods, so what? You're just another obstacle on my path.\"\n Eris : \n\"Hate to break it to you, Trouble: Obstacles are things you're supposed to \"avoid. \"But in \"this \"channel, you're going to run into me \"every time.\"\nAbout Mistakes.\n Eris : \n\"Another go? Can't always tell if you're stubborn, or just plain... \"you \"know. Not that it matters either way.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You're standing between me and my objective, Eris... or, floating. The point is, sooner or later, you'll come to understand that's a mistake.\"\n Eris : \n\"\"Aw\", but we all make mistakes, right? Neither one of us would be here otherwise. So you ready now, or what? Let's have some \"fun.\"\nAbout Relaxation.\n Eris : \n\"Isn't this \"great\", Trouble? Now before I shoot you all to hell, I just want us both to take a moment to \"breathe, relax... really \"just appreciate all that we have.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"These senseless fights with you... I cannot rightly say I appreciate them at all. Though, at least the Moon is beautiful tonight?\"\n Eris : \n\"\"That's \"the spirit! Now how 'bout we stain that pale glow of hers in blood and ichor, huh? And we'll let the sea drink its fill, for good measure!\"\nAbout Consequences.\n Eris : \n\"You're tougher than you look, I'll give you that, Trouble. And I'll give you something \"else \"for what you did to me last time.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"The outcome of our prior meeting was the direct result of your provocation and hostility. Tonight may go even worse.\"\n Eris : \n\"Wait, you're telling me our choices have \"c-c-consequences...? C'mon\", don't be so gullible. Anyway! I'm gonna open fire now.\"\nAbout &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Apple\"&gt;Golden Apples&lt;/a&gt;.\n Eris : \n\"Give back the Golden Apple that you took from me last time, and I might just let you walk this once. What do you say?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You mean the Golden Apple that you very likely \"stole? \"Supposedly they grow but in a single garden, and I highly doubt that such a place would let \"you \"in.\"\n Eris : \n\"Life starts to get a \"lot \"more interesting once you accept that you \"don't \"always need an invitation to show up. Fine! Keep the Apple, then. I've got a whole lot more...\""}
{"id": "2766", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2766", "title": "Eris/Relationships", "text": "Family.\nNyx.\n&lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' mother&lt;br&gt;Eris has a strained relationship with her mother, disliking her controlling nature which is why she is not interested in saving her from Chronos.\nAccordingly Eris blames her mother for all of her behavior, claiming that she was raised and made to be the embodiment of conflict, refusing to take any responsibility for her actions because she's just doing what she was created to do, no matter how much she tries not to.\nFates.\n&lt;a href=\"Fates\"&gt;Fates&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' older sisters&lt;br&gt;Eris has no respect for her older sisters.\nCharon.\n&lt;a href=\"Charon\"&gt;Charon&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' older brother&lt;br&gt;Eris has a strained relationship with her brother.\nMoros.\n&lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' older brother&lt;br&gt;Moros is one of the many siblings whom Eris mentions she feels maybe consider themselves superior to her. Eris has a strained relationship with her brother. Her lack of direction and petulant behavior make her quite unpopular among her siblings; both Moros and Nemesis mention clashes with her on several occasions. Eris teases him by suggesting the Fates intended to set him up with Melino\u00eb.\nEris will notice when spending more time with her siblings at the crossroads. She comments on Moros being different, stranger than usual. She notices the way he looks at Melino\u00eb, which makes her feel nauseous. It's possible that Eris is jealous of her older brother, even if she doesn't admit it.\nNemesis.\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' older sister&lt;br&gt;Eris has a strained relationship with her older sister, during a conversation at the Crossroads, Eris dismisses Nemesis' attempts at ordering her. In the past, Eris would often pester her into fights, which resulted in Nemesis beating her up. Nemesis threatened to beat Eris up if she interfered with the task to defeat Chronos.\nUnlike Nemesis, who shares a healthy bond with her mother, Nyx, Nemesis often lashes out at Eris with hurtful remarks, not just to her face. This stems from Eris feeling she doesn't fit into Nemesis's mold of a star disciple, unlike Nemesis does for Nyx. Eris had to move on; after all, she doesn't need anyone like that in her life.\nEris's hurt by Nemesis is palpable; Nemesis claims she promised Nyx she would take care of Eris but ended up abandoning her. It's clear that Eris still nurses a grudge. Once close, Eris used to admire Nemesis, making her slightly envious seeing Nemesis with Melino\u00eb.\nShe tells Melino\u00eb she only wants to spend time with her \"big sister,\" which might not have been entirely sarcastic. Eris enjoys purposefully riling up her sister to witness Nemesis's wild side.\nThanatos.\n&lt;a href=\"Thanatos\"&gt;Thanatos&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' older brother&lt;br&gt;Eris has a strained relationship with her brother who she considers to be a stuck up and has no interest in saving him from Chronos.\nHypnos.\n&lt;a href=\"Hypnos\"&gt;Hypnos&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' older brother&lt;br&gt;Eris enjoys vandalizing Hypnos during his nap, probably scribbling on his face with a pen. The relationship between Eris and Hypnos doesn't seem to be as tense as with her other siblings, as she doesn't mention him feeling superior to her like the more efficient siblings do, since both can be seen as failing in their roles. However, when she's bored, she doesn't hesitate to see Hypnos as an easy target for mischief.\nThe Crossroads.\nHecate.\n&lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' guardian&lt;br&gt; According to the pact between Hecate and Nyx, all of Nyx's children are welcome at the Crossroads. Eris loathes staying still and has the freedom to come and go from there as she pleases. However, she also goes out of her way to make life as irritating as possible for everyone else, using Hecate's cauldron to prepare explosives.\nMelino\u00eb.\n&lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;: Eris' favorite target&lt;br&gt; Melino\u00eb has become Eris's favorite target for mischief and pranks at the moment. Eris calls her 'Babe,' not that she's allied with Chronos or anything like that. Despite Eris's pestering, Melino\u00eb is drawn towards Eris as though she were \"a moth to a flame.\" Eris often sends mixed messages towards Melino\u00eb, claiming she is boring on one occasion, then asserting that she \"likes her face\" and is willing to fight her night after night, and said fights are \"thrilling.\"\nTheir exchanges with Melino\u00eb, although initially humiliating and immature, gradually ease as they converse. This shift may be attributed to Mel's attempts to treat her normally rather than as a bother, prompting a more positive response from her. She pledges to make an effort to change, though not excessively\u2014just a bit. Eris makes strides to try to \"loosen\" Melino\u00eb up, usually involving fighting her at the banks of the Rift of Thessaly and is pleased when Melino\u00eb is angry or shows her displeasure at her."}
