{"id": "2421", "revid": "51676213", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2421", "title": "Fates", "text": "The Fates, better known as the Three Fates, are a trio of goddesses responsible for weaving the threads of fate that govern the world of \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;\". \nThe three fates are Atropos, Lachesis and Clotho.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nThe Fates are seen as cold, inflexible, unfair and even cruel by mortals and gods alike but as described by their brother &lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;, each is their own goddess with their own qualities. Clotho is described as being the talkative and decisive one, Lachesis as being more agreeable, and Atropos as just being focused on cutting the threads of fate. Also, weaving is their passion according to Moros.\nHistory.\nHades.\nThe Fates do not appear in person in \"Hades\". However, they can interact with &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; through the &lt;a href=\"Fated%20List%20of%20Minor%20Prophecies\"&gt;Fated List of Minor Prophecies&lt;/a&gt; and are frequently mentioned by other characters, particularly by their mother &lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt; or by other characters lamenting their cruelty or indifference.\nHades II.\nOnce again, the Fated List appears in Hades II after they are invoked during a ritual. They still do not make a physical appearance and are only mentioned by other characters, mostly &lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;, their brother and emissary. During the events of the game, they have been captured by &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt; and seek the aid of &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; through the Fated List of Minor Prophecies, their rescue has yet to be implemented in the current early access build, however.\nGallery.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\nConcept=\nIllustration=\nMerchandise=\n&lt;/tabber&gt;"}
{"id": "4708", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4708", "title": "Fates/Relationships", "text": "Family.\nNyx.\n&lt;a href=\"Nyx\"&gt;Nyx&lt;/a&gt;: the Fates' mother.\nMoros.\n&lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;: The Fates' brother, guardian and emissary.\nNemesis.\nNemesis: The Fates' sister."}
{"id": "4956", "revid": "55148434", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4956", "title": "Fear", "text": "Fear represents the level of self-imposed restriction &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; will have to contend with during her attempts to vanquish &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt; or reach &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Olympus\"&gt;Mount Olympus&lt;/a&gt;. The level of Fear can be raised or lowered at the &lt;a href=\"Oath%20of%20the%20Unseen\"&gt;Oath of the unseen&lt;/a&gt; before starting a run. Beating certain &lt;a href=\"Guardians\"&gt;Guardians&lt;/a&gt; at a high enough Fear level will also reward one &lt;a href=\"Nightmare\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt; in addition to their standard rewards."}
{"id": "2857", "revid": "55184635", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2857", "title": "Fields of Mourning", "text": "The Fields of Mourning is the third biome of the Underworld. The area is home to many Shades who have decided to stay, despite the infestion of &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;' forces.\nThe following biome is &lt;a href=\"Tartarus/Hades%20II\"&gt;Tartarus&lt;/a&gt;.\nEnemy Encounters.\nThese are all the enemies that can be encountered in any other Fields of Mourning chamber. These enemies can also appear as Elites, giving them armor and upgraded attacks."}
