{"id": "1199", "revid": "55184635", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1199", "title": "Fishing", "text": "Fishing is a minigame available throughout the underworld in various places available after purchasing the &lt;a href=\"House%20Contractor%23Work_Orders\"&gt;Rod of Fishing&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"House%20Contractor\"&gt;House Contractor&lt;/a&gt;. Fishing rewards the player with various &lt;a href=\"Artifacts\"&gt;Artifacts&lt;/a&gt;, once exchanged to the &lt;a href=\"Head%20Chef\"&gt;Head Chef&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpawning of Fishing Spot.\nA fishing spot can only spawn when all of the following conditions are met:\nThe game will notify the player that a fishing spot spawns with a \"ding\" sound when:\nHow to Fish.\nZagreus cannot start fishing until the encounter is cleared of enemies.\nStand near the fishing spot and press the Interact button to start fishing. The bobber may fake bob up to 3 times. When a fish bites the hook, the bobber will submerge completely in the water. Also, there will be a flash of light on top of the rod. At this moment, the player should press the Interact button as soon as possible to catch the fish.\nThe sooner the Interact button is pressed, the higher rarity the fish will be. The time window of fishing is:\nWhen Zagreus is fishing, the in-game run timer and the timer of &lt;a href=\"Pact%20of%20Punishment\"&gt;Tight Deadline&lt;/a&gt; will be paused.\nPerfect catch always gives you at least a Rare fish. \nIn theory, the game data sets the weighted chance for each type of fish, with 1/21 (\u2248 4.76%) chance to catch a Legendary fish on Perfect catch, and 1/21 of catching a Rare on Good catch (see FishingData.lua - default weight is 1, and those have 0.05). \nIn practice, there's a trivial bug in FishingScripts.lua , line 69 codice_1, due to using codice_2 instead of codice_3. As a result, all the weights are set to 1, giving 50% for each type of possible fish, as stated in the bullet points above. \nSupergiant devs confirmed that, while this is in fact a bug, they embraced it as a feature, and that the chances will stay the way they are (i.e. 50/50 for both categories). \nRewards.\nAfter returning to the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;, Zagreus can turn in all the fish to the &lt;a href=\"Head%20Chef\"&gt;Head Chef&lt;/a&gt; to exchange for rewards. Caught fish will also be logged in their &lt;a href=\"Codex\"&gt;Codex&lt;/a&gt; section titled \"River Denizens,\" unlocking more notes for each fish with each subsequent catch."}
{"id": "4356", "revid": "4008728", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4356", "title": "Fishing/Hades II", "text": "Fishing is a minigame that becomes available throughout the Underworld and on the Surface after Melino\u00eb has obtained the &lt;a href=\"Rod%20of%20Fishing\"&gt;Rod of Fishing&lt;/a&gt;. The Rod (alongside all other &lt;a href=\"Gathering%20Tools\"&gt;Gathering Tools&lt;/a&gt;) will become unlockable after completing the &lt;a href=\"Cauldron%23Incantations\"&gt;Incantation&lt;/a&gt; Night's Craftwork, which itself requires only 1.\nMelino\u00eb can purchase and equip the Rod of Fishing at the &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads/Training%20Grounds%23The_Silver_Pool\"&gt;Silver Pool&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads/Training%20Grounds\"&gt;Training Grounds&lt;/a&gt;. As of Early Access, the Rod can be upgraded once, to Rank II. Upgrading to Rank II grants a 50% chance for Melino\u00eb to receive 1 while gathering, once per night.\nBecause Bronze can only be found on the Surface and must be mined, Melino\u00eb must complete the Permeation of Witching-Wards incantation and obtain the &lt;a href=\"Crescent%20Pick\"&gt;Crescent Pick&lt;/a&gt; to acquire the materials for the Rod.\nCaught fish can be exchanged for Bones from the &lt;a href=\"Wretched%20Broker/Hades%20II\"&gt;Wretched Broker&lt;/a&gt; (see \"Possible Catches\" table below). \nHow to Fish.\nMelino\u00eb cannot start fishing until the encounter is cleared of enemies.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Fishing\"&gt;Hades I&lt;/a&gt;, standing near the Fishing Point and pressing the Interact button will begin a fishing attempt. When the minigame starts, a set of orbs will appear below the screen to signify the number of fishing attempts you have before the fish gets away from your bait. The goal is to wait for the bobber to align with the sparkle in the water before attempting to reel in the catch. You have a limited amount of time and chances to succeed before the fish gets away.\nIf Melino\u00eb is accompanied by her Animal Familiar &lt;a href=\"Toula\"&gt;Toula&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Toula\"&gt;Toula&lt;/a&gt; will fish for her and the minigame will automatically be skipped.\nThe best way to find places you can fish is by doing the &lt;a href=\"Cauldron%23Incantations\"&gt;Incantation&lt;/a&gt; \"Reagent Sensing\", which alerts you to resources nearby on your current map, including Fishing Points. Reagent Sensing requires 1 to activate.\nFishing with Others.\nAfter completing the \"Rite of River-Fording\" &lt;a href=\"Cauldron%23Incantations\"&gt;Incantation&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads%23The%20Fishing%20Pier\"&gt;Fishing Pier&lt;/a&gt; will be added to the the northwest corner of the Crossroads and Melino\u00eb will be awarded &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Lures\"&gt;Twin Lures&lt;/a&gt; . Upon offering to certain characters, they may accompany her to the Pier. This will improve Melino\u00eb's affinity/bond with them, similar to offering &lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe characters that you can offer the Twin Lures to are &lt;a href=\"Dora\"&gt;Dora&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Odysseus\"&gt;Odysseus&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce triggering this bonding event, in-game time is fast-forwarded to the equivalent of traversing 16 .\nAdditional can be purchased from the &lt;a href=\"Wretched%20Broker/Hades%20II\"&gt;Wretched Broker&lt;/a&gt; for 100 each.\nAnimal Familiar.\nAfter recruiting &lt;a href=\"Toula\"&gt;Toula&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Familiars\"&gt;Familiar&lt;/a&gt;, you can access her Soul Bond ability. Toula's presence increases the chances of Fishing Points to appear during a run, and she will catch fish for Melino\u00eb, bypassing the minigame."}
