{"id": "2733", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2733", "title": "Frinos", "text": "Frinos is a green toad companion and a potential &lt;a href=\"Animal%20Familiar\"&gt;Animal Familiar&lt;/a&gt; that settles outside &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;'s tent in &lt;a href=\"the%20Crossroads\"&gt;the Crossroads&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nFrinos is a light-green toad adorned with a teal, moon-shaped tassel pendant on his back. He has orange lips and yellow eyes with ovoid black pupils. In the crossroads, he can be found sitting on a stone at the respawn location, where &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; has the option to \"confide\" in him, typically about how she last died.\nHe is very tranquil, as he shows little reaction to being struck by projectiles. According to his codex entry, he enjoys eating any kind of insect that comes near Melino\u00eb's tent.\nHistory.\nBefore Hades II.\nFrinos is a regular toad that would one day by chance hop into Melino\u00eb's tent, &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; herself quickly growing attached to the amphibian who became one of her closest confidants, close enough with his owner for her to talk about the things that bothered her.\nHades II.\nFrinos is perched on a rock where he tends to witness Melino\u00eb return from her runs, who in turns tends to greet him in multiple ways. Melino\u00eb eventually makes him her official familiar, allowing him to join on her runs.\nAffinity.\nAfter using the Faith of the Familiar Spirits &lt;a href=\"Incantations\"&gt;Incantation&lt;/a&gt;, Melino\u00eb can offer Frinos a &lt;a href=\"Witch%27s%20Delight\"&gt;Witch's Delight&lt;/a&gt;, allowing him to be used as a familiar. When Frinos is equipped, he leaps randomly about the encounter arena and absorbs projectiles, ostensibly serving as portable cover. He cannot be stunned or take damage, though he is typically knocked back when he takes a hit. Some types of projectiles, most notably wave-shaped ones, can pass through him, however.\nHe also has the &lt;a href=\"Gathering%20Tools\"&gt;tool&lt;/a&gt; function of the &lt;a href=\"Tablet%20of%20Peace\"&gt;Tablet of Peace&lt;/a&gt;; he increases the chances of Lost Shades to appear during a run and can turn them directly into Psyche, skipping the minigame.\nBonds.\nAfter the initial &lt;a href=\"Witch%27s%20Delight\"&gt;Witch's Delight&lt;/a&gt; used to unlock him as a companion, further offerings can be used to strengthen bonds which make both of you stronger while together."}
