{"id": "4329", "revid": "54583845", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4329", "title": "Goldwraith", "text": "Goldwraiths are animated sacks of gold that are common throughout &lt;a href=\"Tartarus/Hades%20II\"&gt;Tartarus&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGoldwraiths will wander briefly after spawning, then stop and fire a single beam that crosses the entire length of the chamber. The beam will appear red as the Goldwraith begins channeling, but it will only deal damage once it begins pulsating black and white (this occurs after a short delay). These beams will then rotate towards Melino\u00eb, and deal small but rapid amounts of damage if she gets caught in their path.\nGoldwraiths become dangerous in large groups due to the multiple crisscrossing beams limiting both movement and safe spots for Melino\u00eb.\nThe mini-boss version of the Goldwraith is known as a &lt;a href=\"Goldwrath\"&gt;Goldwrath&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4335", "revid": "54583845", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4335", "title": "Goldwrath", "text": "The Goldwrath is a larger, stronger version of the Goldwraith. It is one of two mini-bosses of &lt;a href=\"Tartarus/Hades%20II\"&gt;Tartarus&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "1030", "revid": "55184635", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1030", "title": "Good Riddance", "text": "Good Riddance is one of the vocal tracks in &lt;a href=\"Hades%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hades&lt;/a&gt;. It is performed by &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.imdb.com/name/nm6501214/\"&gt;Ashley Barrett&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game, it is sung by &lt;a href=\"Eurydice\"&gt;Eurydice&lt;/a&gt; as the background track of her dedicated chamber in &lt;a href=\"Asphodel\"&gt;Asphodel&lt;/a&gt;. Its lyrics exemplify Eurydice's carefree attitude towards her time in the afterlife, which she sees not as eternal punishment but instead as a truly free existence unbothered by the perils and worries of mortal life.\nThis song can also be heard by &lt;a href=\"Orpheus\"&gt;Orpheus&lt;/a&gt; occasionally. Orpheus is sung by Darren Korb. To have Orpheus sing Good Riddance, the player must have purchased the Music Stand from the &lt;a href=\"House%20Contractor\"&gt;House Contractor&lt;/a&gt;, encountered &lt;a href=\"Eurydice\"&gt;Eurydice&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Asphodel\"&gt;Asphodel&lt;/a&gt;, and progressed through her storyline enough to obtain sheet music from her. Following these steps, the song can be unlocked by purchasing it from the Contractor.\nEventually, when the Musician and Muse &lt;a href=\"Fated%20List%20of%20Minor%20Prophecies\"&gt;prophecy&lt;/a&gt; is completed, and Orpheus and Eurydice are reunited, both Orpheus and Eurydice will be singing the song if &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; reaches Eurydice's chamber and Orpheus is visiting.\nLyrics.\n\"Farewell\" \n\"To all the earthly remains\"\n\"No burdens\" \n\"No further debts to be paid\" \n\"Atlas\" \n\"Can rest his weary bones\" \n\"The weight of the world\" \n\"All falls away\" \n\"In time\" \n\"Goodbye\" \n\"To all the plans that we made\" \n\"No contracts\" \n\"I\u2019m free to do as I may\" \n\"No hunger\" \n\"No sleep except to dream\" \n\"Mild and warm\" \n\"Safe from all harm\" \n\"Calm\" \n\"Good riddance\" \n\"To all the thieves\" \n\"To all the fools that stifled me\" \n\"They\u2019ve come and gone\" \n\"And passed me by\" \n\"Good riddance\" \n\"To all\" \n\"Farewell\" \n\"To all the earthly remains\" \n\"No burdens\" \n\"No further debts to be paid\" \n\"Atlas\" \n\"Can rest his weary bones\" \n\"The weight of the world\" \n\"All falls away\" \n\"In time\" "}
