{"id": "4379", "revid": "54583845", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4379", "title": "Harpy Talon", "text": "Harpy Talons are harpies who have taken the opportunity to join &lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;'s assault on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Olympus\"&gt;Mount Olympus&lt;/a&gt;. \nHarpy Talons will dive down onto the ghost ships to attack Melino\u00eb. Between rapid, short-range dashes they will swoop feet-first, slashing a path in front of them with their talons and striking multiple times. \nMost dangerous, however, are the cutting winds Harpy Talons cast with their wings: A spinning circle will track across the ship, dealing constant damage along its path. These circles linger for a time, potentially leaving Melino\u00eb very little room to maneuver. &lt;a href=\"Gameplay_mechanics/Hades_II%23Armor\"&gt;Armored&lt;/a&gt; Harpy Talons will throw out three of these spinning circles at once."}
{"id": "1740", "revid": "54583845", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1740", "title": "Head Chef", "text": "The Head Chef is a shade employed to provide food for the various shades within the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;. He resides in the kitchen within the lounge, perpetually cutting onions, sometimes throwing a pair of onions into the air and gracefully slashing them into clean slices. Occasionally, the Head Chef will be the Featured Houseservant.\nInteractions.\nThe Head Chef accepts any &lt;a href=\"River%20Denizens\"&gt;River Denizens&lt;/a&gt; caught by &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; during his escape attempts, exchanging &lt;a href=\"Gemstone\"&gt;Gemstones&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nectar\"&gt;Nectar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chthonic%20Key\"&gt;Chthonic Keys&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Darkness\"&gt;Darkness&lt;/a&gt; based on the regions each fish originated and the amount on rarity; a &lt;a href=\"Diamond\"&gt;Diamond&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ambrosia\"&gt;Ambrosia&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Titan%20Blood\"&gt;Titan Blood&lt;/a&gt; can also be exchanged for certain fish caught.\nHead Chef emotes when kitchen purchases from the Lounge tab of &lt;a href=\"House%20Contractor\"&gt;House Contractor&lt;/a&gt; are made."}
{"id": "2712", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2712", "title": "Headmistress Hecate", "text": ""}
{"id": "482", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=482", "title": "Health", "text": "Health is Zagreus's Life Total. By default, he has 50 . If it reaches 0, he will die and revive in the &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20Hades\"&gt;House of Hades&lt;/a&gt;. You start each run with full health, and it is reduced by being hit by enemy attacks or traps, triggering relevant Chaos curses, entering a &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Gate\"&gt;Chaos Gate&lt;/a&gt; without the &lt;a href=\"Cosmic%20Egg\"&gt;Cosmic Egg&lt;/a&gt; equipped, running out of time with the Tight Deadline &lt;a href=\"Pact%20of%20Punishment\"&gt;Pact of Punishment&lt;/a&gt; modifier on, or inflicting self-damage with the &lt;a href=\"Adamant%20Rail\"&gt;Adamant Rail&lt;/a&gt;'s \"Hazard Bomb\" upgrade.\nWhen unlocked from the &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20of%20Night\"&gt;Mirror of Night&lt;/a&gt;, Zagreus can get &lt;a href=\"Death%20Defiance\"&gt;Death Defiances&lt;/a&gt;. Instead of dying after receiving lethal damage which reduces his health to 0, &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt; instead loses one Death Defiance charge, briefly becomes invulnerable, and restores 50% for a second chance. Alternatively, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Defiance%23Stubborn_Defiance\"&gt;Stubborn Defiance&lt;/a&gt; will restore 30% and work once per chamber."}
{"id": "4269", "revid": "48934972", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4269", "title": "Health/Hades II", "text": " Health is Melino\u00eb's Life Total. By default, she has 30 health. If it reaches 0, she will leave and return to &lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads\"&gt;The Crossroads&lt;/a&gt;. You start each night with full health, and it is reduced by being hit by enemy attacks or traps, triggering relevant Chaos curses, entering a &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Gate\"&gt;Chaos Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen unlocking the Eternity arcana card from the &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Cards\"&gt;Altar of Ashes&lt;/a&gt;, Melino\u00eb can get &lt;a href=\"Death%20Defiance/Hades%20II\"&gt;Death Defiances&lt;/a&gt;. Instead of dying after receiving lethal damage which reduces her health to 0, &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt; instead loses one Death Defiance charge, briefly becomes invulnerable, and restores 40% for a second chance."}
{"id": "424", "revid": "4008728", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=424", "title": "Heart-Seeking Bow", "text": "Coronacht, the Heart-Seeking Bow is an &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Arms\"&gt;Infernal Arm&lt;/a&gt; that can be unlocked for 1 &lt;a href=\"Chthonic%20Key\"&gt;Chthonic Key&lt;/a&gt;.\nFighting style.\nThe bow delivers ranged attacks that hit enemies at a distance. The main attack can be charged to increase distance and damage, releasing at the right moment for additional 10 damage. The special sprays arrows in a cone in front of you, dealing 10 damage each. \nAspects.\nThe Heart-Seeking Bow has 4 Aspects: &lt;a href=\"Zagreus\"&gt;Zagreus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chiron\"&gt;Chiron&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hera\"&gt;Hera&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Rama\"&gt;Rama&lt;/a&gt;. Like all other weapons, each Aspect has 5 levels that can be unlocked by spending &lt;a href=\"Titan%20Blood\"&gt;Titan Blood&lt;/a&gt;. The higher the level of the Aspect, the more effective its improvement is. Reaching the highest level in all Aspects requires 51 &lt;a href=\"Titan%20Blood\"&gt;Titan Blood&lt;/a&gt;. An Aspect will not only change the appearance of the Heart-Seeking Bow, but will also improve its attacks. The Aspect of Rama has a unique move-set which changes the fighting style of the Heart-Seeking Bow.\nRevealing the Aspect of Rama.\nReveal the Aspect of Rama by meeting the following requirements:"}
