{"id": "2669", "revid": "56005706", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2669", "title": "Hecate/Quotes", "text": "These voicelines are listed in order of priority, not necessarily in narrative order. \nHecate has two states of interacting, first as an NPC in the Crossroads and also as a Guardian of Erebus. Hecate's Crossroads conversations differ based on things you did or places you went in your last run; if you perform multiple events in a run, you receive the highest priority voiceline first and the rest are saved for the next night to be selected from again.\n\"The following are quotes from &lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Hades%20II\"&gt;Hades II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nFirst Meeting.\nDialogue 01.\n Hecate : \n\"Time forced our hand, Melino\u00eb. Nary a soul expected you to slay our enemy last night, on a new moon, no less! But, you accomplished something of great import.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I lack such forgiveness for my failure, Headmistress Hecate. The Titan yet lives, and Olympus yet burns, while I'm back where I started! What is it I accomplished?\"\n Hecate : \n\"You're here to speak of it! Recovered in body, if not in spirit. You've not failed; merely begun. Thus may you learn, grow stronger, and complete your task. \"Death to Chronos.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Death to Chronos.\"\nContinuation 01.\n Hecate : \n\"This cauldron's filthy still, alas. But there's something at our Altar you may use, and I've unsealed the Silver Pool as well.\"\nContinuation 02.\n Hecate : \n\"We shall await your safe return. May moonlight guide you.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"'Twas a worthwhile first attempt, Melino\u00eb. I trust you'd have gone farther still had I not obstructed your path. Quite unsuccessfully, I concede.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You needed to ensure I was prepared, Headmistress Hecate. And I know there is much left to prove.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Just so. Trust well your instincts and your craft, and continue the task. \"Death to Chronos.\"\nBasic Narrative Dialogue.\nChanting.\nChanting 01.\n\"\"Upon this cauldron, by the will of Night,\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Hear me, Shades of the Dead, and listen well,\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Your strength is needed now to join our fight,\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Upon Olympus and in depths of hell.\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Within these Crossroads you are safe with us,\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Yet we would ask your service to our cause.\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Your will is yours, your choice is given thus:\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Together, let us rise above our flaws.\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"So mote it be.\"\nChanting 02.\n\"\"By light of Moon, in darkest Erebus,\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Look well upon the wards about this place,\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Which keep us hidden within Night's embrace.\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"Ensure that each is whole, its strength secure,\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"As we hold out against our common foe;\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"To achieve victory we must endure\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"\"The ravages on us Time would bestow.\" &lt;br&gt;\n\"So mote it be.\"\nAbouth the Scenery.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Crossroads\"&gt;The Crossroads&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"Grow not attached to such a place as this; you belong within the luxury of your great father's House.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"As you say, Headmistress...\"\n&lt;a href=\"Oceanus\"&gt;Oceanus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"'Tis fortunate your father's realm is vast indeed, that you may circumnavigate it at the edge of Oceanus, where our enemy is relatively weak.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"If we cannot pass directly through Elysium, then we shall make what way we can. Though the fiends that lurk the border of the sea care not for my presence.\"\n Hecate : \n\"God-hating monsters with salt in their veins; the seas covering the world's surface just were not enough for them. The sunken chambers they occupy have not yet fallen to Chronos, at least.\"\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Surface\"&gt;The Surface&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Headmistress, if I may? What is it that you and Master Odysseus are planning? He's always with his charts and diagrams.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Odysseus considers our plan of attack. \"Yours\", more specifically. He plots a course from the nearest Underworld entrance to Olympus.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"The \"surface...? \"I am to attack \"Olympus? \"When? How?\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"Attack, defend... \"'tis all the same. Patience, Melino\u00eb. As you observed, we are still... working through some of the details.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"But... \"mm.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Headmistress, if Olympus is besieged, then why am I not permitted on the surface? If I could aid the gods, then they could aid us even more!\"\n Hecate : \n\"Melino\u00eb, however you complete the task is up to you; I have not barred you from the surface. But I caution, if you go, your strength shall fail you. Your birthright is to blame; no fault of yours.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Born in the Underworld and here I'll stay, thank the Fates. I don't intend to live up there, I just... Do you know how long I'd even have?\"\n Hecate : \n\"I know your brother and father had a day at best ere they could not stand it any longer. Perhaps you're different, but don't count on it.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"A day at best...?\"\nDialogue 03.\n Hecate : \n\"You visited the surface. I can't imagine \"that \"played out particularly well. At least you made it back at all.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It was draining... even at night, something about being under the stars, I... didn't know there were so many. It was more than I could take. You were right.\"\n Hecate : \n\"A lesson learned, and an experience gained. The Fates themselves do not want you up there. What shall you do?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I have an incantation to complete. I don't need to stay forever on the surface... I just need to hold on long enough to make it to Olympus...\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"Ah\", then you seek to improve this aspect of yourself, without rejecting it outright. I see how that may work...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It has to...\"\n&lt;a href=\"Rift%20of%20Thessaly\"&gt;Rift of Thessaly&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"How fares the ever-sinking fleet of ships within the Rift of Thessaly? 'Tis a wonder Chronos gathered as many followers as he has, using such shoddily built craft.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"The fleet shows no real sign of slowing down. Fortunately, the same sorcery that seems to be holding those ships together lets me transfer quickly from one to the next. Are all surface ships so odd-looking?\"\n Hecate : \n\"I certainly think not. \"These \"are merely emblematic of the Titan's false promises of a new age. They assault not just Olympus but our sensibilities as well.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"We'll fight them off.\"\nMiscellaneous Conversations.\nAbout Backstory.\n Hecate : \n\"Such a mess made of our best-laid plans. Leave it to swiftest Hermes to show up one evening with bad news, then scurry off! Nary a message from him since, whilst \"you \"are forced now to attempt the task we'd no intention to initiate till many moons hence...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Hermes must still be trying to figure out what Chronos is up to... the attacks on Olympus grown so much bolder all of a sudden. We just couldn't afford to wait any longer for details, could we...?\"\n Hecate : \n\"No, Hermes was quite insistent about that. Persuaded Artemis to do her part, and now it seems your other \"mountain relatives \"are finally aware of you. They have been quick to be of benefit, at least?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Most certainly.\"\nAbout Mission.\nDialogue 01.\n Hecate : \n\"What troubles you, Melino\u00eb? Your brow is furrowed not with fierceness but with doubt... the one emotion we cannot afford.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"Ungh\", Headmistress, it's just... I'm struggling to muster the rage I should feel. I'm tasked with slaying a Titan I do not even know, to avenge a family I cannot remember...\"\n Hecate : \n\"Your feelings never lie to you; 'tis their origins that may deceive. You feel no rage? Then \"you \"are in control. Tell me, do you question the need to complete our task?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"No, Headmistress. Treachery against the House of Hades cannot go unpunished.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Just so. Center yourself on that.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"How fares the task thus far, Melino\u00eb? Our enemy yet remains indisposed with more pressing matters. The time to strike at him is now.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"There is much left to do, Headmistress. You must know that. How much time do I have?\"\n Hecate : \n\"Who can say? Our enemy is Time itself. Time's passage seems to bear little meaning anymore. Do not rush needlessly. The task shall only take longer that way.\"\nAbout Pressure.\n Hecate : \n\"Much is expected of you. The pressure that you feel; you never speak of it, and yet full well I know it's there. Your constant companion.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I can hardly distinguish between pressure and faith anymore. My entire life has led to this, and all of you are counting on me. Are you truly so certain in my inevitable success, Headmistress?\"\n Hecate : \n\"Pressure and faith are intertwined, 'tis true. Ever in conflict. Should the pressure utterly prevail, out comes despair. Only then do we truly falter.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You didn't answer my question. The combined might of the gods was not enough to stop Chronos before. And you know the Fates are unpredictable. My success is not a certainty...\"\n Hecate : \n\"My faith is not in outcomes, 'tis in you! And I've enough of it to last. Should you find yours lacking, I shall always spare you some of mine.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"...Thank you for believing in me.\"\n Hecate : \n\"No need.\"\nAbout Quest Log.\nDialogue 01.\n Hecate : \n\"At least our cauldron's finally purified, praise the Fates! Speaking of which, are you as yet considering an invocation to them? I have my doubts that they would listen, even now...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"If there's any chance the Three Fates shall aid us, I'll take it. Thank you for preparing things for me. Though, I'm well short of freshly picked reagents still.\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"Mm. \"I'd offer such reagents if I could but, as you venture past this glade look carefully along your path and you shall find them. Fates willing...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Yes, Headmistress.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"The Fates indulged you after all. That is their scroll beside your tent; it followed you out of the shadows. Perhaps it can provide some answers.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Would that it does. The Fated List has tasked me with ensuring certain minor prophecies are fulfilled, though says little else as yet.\"\n Hecate : \n\"May it reward your efforts, at least. But do not expect the Fates to always favor you; the bane of our enemy is not necessarily our friend.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"We'll have to take our chances...\"\nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Trials\"&gt;Chaos Trials&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"Those paths and possibilities are real, like as not; as are the splendors that await, should you indulge our primordial benefactor. There always is uncertainty where Chaos is concerned... yet I trust that Nyx's parent is an ally, not a threat.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I trust so too.\"\nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Book%20of%20Shadows\"&gt;Book of Shadows&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"Have you had opportunity to glean much from the Book of Shadows yet, Melino\u00eb? Our task shall take you far beyond these Crossroads; you've much to learn as yet.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"As I begin to have insights into my experiences, the Book reveals more. Are they \"your \"teachings within, Headmistress?\"\n Hecate : \n\"Not mine alone, though heed them anyway...\"\nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Umbral%20Flames\"&gt;Umbral Flames&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"I recall when I myself first grasped the Flames of Ygnium. I must have been about your age. Now you are possessed of their power.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"All it takes is a bit of light to cast a long shadow; isn't that so, Headmistress? I'll do my best to wield the Flames as you have taught.\"\n Hecate : \n\"In your \"own \"way, Melino\u00eb.\"\nAbout Nightmares.\n Hecate : \n\"Your dreams have troubled you again, I see. Despite your brave attempts to conceal it.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I can manage them, Headmistress, it's just... it's Chronos. I now hear him even when I'm still as death.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Then turn your nightmares into his. Your subconscious self is your greatest refuge. Let none there remain whom you do not permit.\"\nAbout Family.\nDialogue 01.\n Hecate : \n\"You always reminded me of your father, Melino\u00eb, but lately you remind me of your mother... more and more. The concern for others that you sometimes show... it can be an exploitable weakness.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I would never put any such concerns ahead of the task, Headmistress.\"\n Hecate : \n\"See that you don't! Although my remark was not intended as admonishment; it was my honor to have known your family... even if merely from the shadows.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"They'll be avenged.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"You always reminded me of your father, Melino\u00eb, but lately you remind me of your mother... more and more. The concern for others that you sometimes show... it can be an exploitable weakness.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I would never put any such concerns ahead of the task, Headmistress.\"\n Hecate : \n\"See that you don't! Although my remark was not intended as admonishment; it was my honor to have known your family... even if merely from the shadows.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"They'll be avenged.\"\nAbout &lt;a href=\"https%3A//hades.fandom.com/wiki/The_Crossroads%3Fso%3Dsearch%23Melino%25C3%25AB%27s_Tent%3A~%3Atext%3Da%2520piece%2520of%2520parchment%2520paper%2520with%2520an%2520unfinished%2520portrait%2520of%2520Melino%25C3%25AB%2520as%2520a%2520baby%2520surrounded%2520by%2520her%2520family\"&gt;The Family Portrait&lt;/a&gt;.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"The family portrait in my tent... I have been thinking on it more and more, I... never asked you where you got it from.\"\n Hecate : \n\"'Twould be stranger if you did, for the answer ought be obvious to you. Though, you would know the circumstances?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Yes, Headmistress, if you please. I know it was a time you would never wish to revisit, but it's important to me.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Of that I have no doubt. When Chronos stormed your father's House, I fled with but three things: Hypnos, because he was there; that family portrait, which pulled at my heart; and you.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Only the three...?\"\n Hecate : \n\"I had but an instant, and I am threefold.\"\nAbout Witchcraft.\n Hecate : \n\"With all your incanting as of late, I must needs caution you to not overextend. I know you want for every chant and glamour on the tip of your tongue, but they require space, and time.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Using the cauldron doesn't drain me as once it did. Though I know I mustn't be reckless.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Indeed, lest your fair \"right \"hand come to match your left. Although perhaps that boy-shade Icarus would fancy you more if that were so. Been gone awhile, hasn't he?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"He has...\"\nAbout The &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Cauldron&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue 01.\n Hecate : \n\"Once you're quite finished with the cauldron for the eve, I may have need of it myself... protective charms to be refreshed, wards reinforced...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"If you've a certain incantation in mind, might I be able to assist? \"The Invocation of the Dead, Concealment in Night's Embrace\", whichever...\"\n Hecate : \n\"You've your own matters to consider now, Melino\u00eb. Though if you're here in the vicinity whilst I'm chanting, your voice is always welcome, joined with mine.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Together we shine, Headmistress.\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"Hmm.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"I must say, you've been putting our old cauldron to good use. I see and sense the changes in t