 have for you.\"\n Hecate : \n\"...Set your sorrow well aside for now. I'll drink your Nectar and enjoy it, if you please.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I would.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Bath%20Salts\"&gt;Bath Salts&lt;/a&gt;.\n1st Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Headmistress, I was wondering if you might accompany me to the springs for a short while? If you're not overly preoccupied?\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"Eugh\", well, I do believe I could use a bit of a soak. I've more knots in my back than that tree! Let's be quick about it, then.\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"Ah\", but this is all right. Thank you for replenishing these waters! One of those details I had been meaning to get to, but... alas.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You're very welcome, Headmistress. I appreciate your saying so, as I half-thought you would admonish me for using magick and resources on this sort of thing.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Magick mostly \"is \"for self-improvement, Melino\u00eb. Not a shortcut, mind you. And if an occasional scalding-hot soak in the springs isn't self-improvement, then my concept of it must be very flawed.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I wish I could bring myself to relax. I feel like I'm wasting precious time while I'm here.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Time spent being good to oneself is never wasted... unless you overthink it overmuch! We are \"here. \"Seize the moment, ere it passes.\"\n Hecate : \n\"A shame we cannot cook indefinitely in those springs, but... a brief dip is better than none at all.\"\n2nd Time.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I was thinking of putting these purifying salts to use, Headmistress. Call it a cleansing ritual. Would you accompany me?\"\n Hecate : \n\"A visit to the springs ought rid us of unwanted thoughts for a while. Let us be cleansed together, then.\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"Mm. \"We're like two nettles boiling in a cauldron, aren't we?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I remember bathing in this spring when I was very small. You would ask me never to splash your hair, and I would do it anyway. You were so tolerant of me.\"\n H