 be complete. Yet, onward we must strive.\"\nAbout Other's Keepsakes.\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"What is that foul artifact you bear? \"Ah! \"An Eye of Nemesis. Warding against those harboring ill will. The sheer irony of it, coming from her.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I mean nothing untoward, Headmistress. The Eye is indiscriminate in its effect, and makes me match more strongly with my strongest foes.\"\n Hecate : \n\"'Tis a wonder this Eye does not cause the two of us to combust on the spot! Then take your vengeance, if you can!\"\n&lt;a href=\"Odysseus\"&gt;Odysseus&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"Blood and darkness, I can sense you've those accursed Knuckle Bones on you. I shall have to thank Odysseus for providing such a gift...\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"My Keepsake? I'm surprised these have any effect on you, Headmistress. I thought for certain you enchanted them yourself.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Odysseus has known his share of witches besides us. Well, I'm braced for impact; the Knuckle Bones strike first, and then, we fight.\"\n&lt;a href=\"Moros\"&gt;Moros&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"Do I detect an artifact from Moros? Something to bring Doom swiftly to your foes by forestalling your own. Seems rather handy, that.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I'm certain Lord Moros means you no offense. But his Keepsake is of benefit to me, and I'm to take every advantage that I can.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Correct. 'Tis no wonder Doom has come to stay with us for now. His presence lingers over every action that we take...\"\n&lt;a href=\"Medea\"&gt;Medea&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"The air hangs heavily about you here tonight. \"Ah! \"'Tis from the scrap of something that Medea gave to you. A gift more than a curse, I trust?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Her Keepsake, yes. A bit of fleece... sheep roam about Ephyra, but none with coats as black and brilliant as this. It's something special, I can tell.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Indeed it is, as fleeces go, at least. Medea is not quick to accept others into her circle; bit of a black sheep herself. But, aren't we all?\"\n&lt;a href=\"Eris\"&gt;Eris&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"\"Eugh...! \"Whatever foul Keepsake you decided to bring along for good fortune this eve, 'tis a horrid thing. Which sort of comrade would reward you thus?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It... was a gift from Eris, Headmistress. I know the effect isn't strictly to my benefit, or anyone's... but I just thought...\"\n Hecate : \n\"...That Eris was doing you a favor? Or has \"any \"sense of purpose other than to sow disorder where she can? You two make a strange match, Melino\u00eb. So shall \"this \"be.\"\nAbout Flattery.\n Hecate : \n\"Decided to take a break from all your recent outings to the surface, have you now?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"There's much to be done, both above and below. You always say the greatest teacher is \"out there\". But I always seem to find her here.\"\n Hecate : \n\"I taught you nothing of such flattery. One of Odysseus' tricks, perhaps! Let's see what others you have learned.\"\nAbout Failure.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"You must wear that veil so as not to betray your disappointment, Headmistress. All these failures yet you still do not admonish me?\"\n Hecate : \n\"Oh silence, Melino\u00eb. For your setbacks I've boundless patience, but for your petulance, I've none. You ought find a better catalyst for such inner turmoils, as I lack sympathy for them!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"That's fine...!\"\nAbout Solitude.\nDialogue 01.\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I didn't mean to keep you waiting long, Headmistress. Or do you always arrive at just the right instant?\"\n Hecate : \n\"A bit of solitude here hardly is a waste of time; I never merely wait. I've more matters to attend to in these woods, besides. But \"first...\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"We are alone; nary the baying of a single hound is to be heard. Selene high above shall have to be sufficient for an audience.\"\nAbout Silence.\n Hecate : \n\"'Tis a particularly quiet night. Observe the silence for a moment, ere we begin our little test of just how capable you have become.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"It does seem unusually still, and the Moon wanes. An ill portent, Headmistress? Our Shades should check up on your hounds...\"\n Hecate : \n\"No need, the hounds fend mostly for themselves. Like as not, they use this time to rest; as you'd be wise to do, now and again.\"\nAbout Repeated Wins.\nDialogue 01.\n Hecate : \n\"Strength; knowledge; patience. You have exhibited the three repeatedly. Well done.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Thank you, Headmistress. Though I continue learning from our every clash.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Good, because I've no intent to stand aside. Our craft is called a \"practice \"for a reason. Now, on your guard.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"You surpassed me before, yet I wonder: Was it your mastery over our craft, or did the Fates themselves perhaps provide a little \"nudge?\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Come, Headmistress. If I could be provoked \"that \"easily, I'd stand no chance at all. Not even if the Fates desired otherwise.\"\n Hecate : \n\"Good fortune seldom comes to those in no position to receive it. Show me your victory was no mere accident.\"\nAbout Battle (Close Call).\n Hecate : \n\"You almost had me last we clashed, although a narrow loss is nonetheless a loss. I expect you to follow through to victory this time.\"\nAbout Battle (Missed Fight).\n Hecate : \n\"I had expected your arrival here the prior eve, but 'twas not for me to cut short that attempt. However, I shan't hesitate to cut short \"this \"one.\"\nAbout Battle (Strictly Business).\n Hecate : \n\"So much ado of late, both on Olympus and below. Yet I would have you cast all your worldly troubles aside whilst here.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"My circumstances are what spur me on. Casting them aside shall be difficult, Headmistress...\"\n Hecate : \n\"I've no concern for \"difficult\". We've time enough to gaze upon our navels at the Crossroads. Here, we are adversaries. Nothing more.\"\nAbout Testing.\n Hecate : \n\"There you are. I cannot stay for long. Just long enough to put you to the test.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I got here as quickly as I could, Headmistress. And still you had to wait.\"\n Hecate : \n\"To wait is the practice of patience. Now, on to other practices, I think.\"\nAbout Respect.\n Hecate : \n\"Set your respect for me aside whilst here. You must give no such quarter to our enemies.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"But you are not my enemy, Headmistress. How am I to treat you as one?\"\n Hecate : \n\"\"How? \"Allow me to give you a demonstration, then.\"\nAbout Expectations.\n Hecate : \n\"Much is expected of you. So you must learn to bear that burden with grace.\"\nAbout Mission.\nDialogue 01.\n Hecate : \n\"I know your task is difficult, and also know you have it in you to succeed.\"\nDialogue 02.\n Hecate : \n\"Your task may be an honor, but the wisest whom you know shall not envy you for it.\"\nAbout Witchcraft.\n Hecate : \n\"Our craft leaves little room for doubt, yet some always remains; and even a little can be far too much.\"\nAbout Confidence.\n Hecate : \n\"If you lack confidence, then how are you to manifest your will? Be certain of your heart's desire.\"\nAbout Anger.\n Hecate : \n\"You're angry; let it out. Anger's not to be suppressed, nor misdirected. To be \"angry\"... is to be \"alive.\"\nDefeat.\nFirst Loss Against &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"You fought with diligence and with ferocity. But surely there is more for you to learn beyond this threshold.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I look forward to it, Headmistress. What about you? Can you not join me?\"\n Hecate : \n\"No; I dare not stray too far from our abode. Continue now your task. I shall await your safe return.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"Thank you, Headmistress...\"\nOther Losses.\nNo &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Cards\"&gt;Arcana Cards&lt;/a&gt; Loss.\n Hecate : \n\"The Arcana gave to you no benefit at all this eve and still you bested me. I know not whether to heap praise, or reprimand you for being such a little show-off! \"Hah!\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"I've gotten stronger...\"\nGiving the &lt;a href=\"Book%20of%20Shadows\"&gt;Book of Shadows&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"You have survived against me, and for \"that\", you're owed a gift. May you learn well through it, Melino\u00eb.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"The Book of Shadows...\"\nGiving the &lt;a href=\"Animal%20Familiars\"&gt;Animal Familiars&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Incantation&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"Do bring an animal Familiar along next time, if but to keep things livelier for me! We have the means to keep them safe, even in scuffles such as these.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"Faith of Familiar Spirits\"... this should work on Frinos, or perhaps...\"\nGiving the &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20Cards\"&gt;Arcana Cards&lt;/a&gt; Upgrade &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Incantation&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"You have grown physically quite strong... but spiritually, more is to be done. The Altar of Ashes; there is an incantation that may make your nightly meditations at it better spent.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"The Consecration of Ashes...\"\nGiving the &lt;a href=\"Nocturnal%20Arms\"&gt;Nocturnal Arms&lt;/a&gt; Upgrade &lt;a href=\"Cauldron\"&gt;Incantation&lt;/a&gt;.\n Hecate : \n\"To bear each of the Nocturnal Arms is a terrible responsibility. You've only begun to realize their nature; a certain incantation shall deepen your understanding.\"\n Melino\u00eb : \n\"\"The Aspects of Night and Darkness...\""}
{"id": "2504", "revid": "29110118", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2504", "title": "Hecate/Relationships", "text": "The Crossroads.\nMelino\u00eb.\n&lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;: Hecate's pupil.&lt;br&gt;Hecate has taken care of Melino\u00eb since she saved her from Chronos. She takes great pains to remind Melino\u00eb that she is \"not\" her mother, especially during Gifting dialogue.\nNemesis.\n&lt;a href=\"Nemesis\"&gt;Nemesis&lt;/a&gt;: Retribution Incarnate.&lt;br&gt;Unlike with Melino\u00eb, Hecate has a strained relationship with Nemesis. Hecate considers her a burden and sees her hot-headed behaviour as a detriment which is why she does not trust her with any important tasks. Hecate tells Melino\u00eb that if she had not sworn to take care of Nyx's children she would have casted Nemesis out.\nEris.\n&lt;a href=\"Eris\"&gt;Eris&lt;/a&gt;: Per the pact between Hecate and Nyx, all of Nyx's children are welcome at the Crossroads. Eris has the freedom to come and go from there as she pleases. However, she also goes out of her way to make life as irritating as possible for everyone else, using Hecate's cauldron to concoct explosives. Hecate appears to find Eris troublesome, as she is causing problems.\nThe Titans.\nChronos.\n&lt;a href=\"Chronos\"&gt;Chronos&lt;/a&gt;: Titan of Time&lt;br&gt;Like many of the &lt;a href=\"Chthonic%20Gods\"&gt;Chthonic Gods&lt;/a&gt;, Hecate hates Chronos for his usurpation of the Underworld. As she was charge by Hades to take care of the young Melino\u00eb she has trained Melino\u00eb all her life to kill him. During a dialogue with Melino\u00eb, Hecate implies that she fought Chronos at some point but was unable to defeat him due to him being stronger than her.\nSelene.\n&lt;a href=\"Selene\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt;: Moon Incarnate&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "4906", "revid": "47838920", "url": "https://hades.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4906", "title": "Hecuba", "text": "Hecuba is a black hound companion of &lt;a href=\"Hecate\"&gt;Hecate&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Animal%20Familiar\"&gt;Animal Familiar&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Melino%C3%AB\"&gt;Melino\u00eb&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacteristics and Personality.\nHecuba is loyal to Hecate and &lt;a href=\"Odysseus\"&gt;Odysseus&lt;/a&gt;, going out on patrols on her own and going as far as the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Mourning\"&gt;Fields of Mourning&lt;/a&gt; alone.\nShe also pledges her loyalty to Melino\u00eb, helping her in her quest.\nPhysical Description.\nHecuba is a green-eyes black hound with a silver colar and two golden bracelets on the front legs.\nHades II.\nOnce Hecuba can start being recruited, she is typically found in the same area as &lt;a href=\"Echo\"&gt;Echo&lt;/a&gt;, standing guard in front of the gates to the next area.\nAffinity.\nLike other Familiars, Hecuba possesses a tool function. She replaces the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Spade\"&gt;Silver Spade&lt;/a&gt;.\nBonds.\nAfter the initial &lt;a href=\"Witch%27s%20Delight\"&gt;Witch's Delight&lt;/a&gt; used to unlock her as a companion, further offerings can be used to strengthen bonds which make both of you stronger while together."}
